1947// Scalar-broadcast add that can be used for inner loop of more general
1948// broadcast add, so that, for example, scalar-broadcast with batch will still
1949// be fast.
1950inline void AddScalarBroadcast(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
1951 uint8 input1_data, const uint8* input2_data,
1952 uint8* output_data) {
1953 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
1954
1955 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("AddScalarBroadcast/8bit");
1956 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input1_offset, -256);
1957 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input2_offset, -256);
1958 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input1_offset, 256);
1959 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input2_offset, 256);
1960
1961 int i = 0;
1962
1963#ifdef USE_NEON
1964 const int32x4_t left_shift_dup = vdupq_n_s32(params.left_shift);
1965 const uint8x8_t output_activation_min_vector =
1966 vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_min);
1967 const uint8x8_t output_activation_max_vector =
1968 vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_max);
1969
1970 // Process broadcast scalar.
1971 const uint8x8_t input1_val_original = vdup_n_u8(input1_data);
1972 const int16x8_t input1_val_s16 =
1973 vreinterpretq_s16_u16(vmovl_u8(input1_val_original));
1974 const int16x8_t input1_val =
1975 vaddq_s16(input1_val_s16, vdupq_n_s16(params.input1_offset));
1976 const int16x4_t input1_val_high = vget_high_s16(input1_val);
1977 const int16x4_t input1_val_low = vget_low_s16(input1_val);
1978 int32x4_t x11 = vmovl_s16(input1_val_low);
1979 int32x4_t x12 = vmovl_s16(input1_val_high);
1980 x11 = vshlq_s32(x11, left_shift_dup);
1981 x12 = vshlq_s32(x12, left_shift_dup);
1982 x11 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(x11, params.input1_multiplier);
1983 x12 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(x12, params.input1_multiplier);
1984 const int32x4_t input1_shift_dup = vdupq_n_s32(params.input1_shift);
1985 x11 = vshlq_s32(x11, input1_shift_dup);
1986 x12 = vshlq_s32(x12, input1_shift_dup);
1987
1988 for (; i <= size - 8; i += 8) {
1989 const uint8x8_t input2_val_original = vld1_u8(input2_data + i);
1990 const int16x8_t input2_val_s16 =
1991 vreinterpretq_s16_u16(vmovl_u8(input2_val_original));
1992 const int16x8_t input2_val =
1993 vaddq_s16(input2_val_s16, vdupq_n_s16(params.input2_offset));
1994 const int16x4_t input2_val_high = vget_high_s16(input2_val);
1995 const int16x4_t input2_val_low = vget_low_s16(input2_val);
1996 int32x4_t x21 = vmovl_s16(input2_val_low);
1997 int32x4_t x22 = vmovl_s16(input2_val_high);
1998 x21 = vshlq_s32(x21, left_shift_dup);
1999 x22 = vshlq_s32(x22, left_shift_dup);
2000 x21 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(x21, params.input2_multiplier);
2001 x22 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(x22, params.input2_multiplier);
2002 const int32x4_t input2_shift_dup = vdupq_n_s32(params.input2_shift);
2003 x21 = vshlq_s32(x21, input2_shift_dup);
2004 x22 = vshlq_s32(x22, input2_shift_dup);
2005 int32x4_t s1 = vaddq_s32(x11, x21);
2006 int32x4_t s2 = vaddq_s32(x12, x22);
2007 s1 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(s1, params.output_multiplier);
2008 s2 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(s2, params.output_multiplier);
2009 s1 = RoundingDivideByPOT(s1, -params.output_shift);
2010 s2 = RoundingDivideByPOT(s2, -params.output_shift);
2011 const int16x4_t s1_narrowed = vmovn_s32(s1);
2012 const int16x4_t s2_narrowed = vmovn_s32(s2);
2013 const int16x8_t s = vaddq_s16(vcombine_s16(s1_narrowed, s2_narrowed),
2014 vdupq_n_s16(params.output_offset));
2015 const uint8x8_t clamped =
2016 vmax_u8(output_activation_min_vector,
2017 vmin_u8(output_activation_max_vector, vqmovun_s16(s)));
2018 vst1_u8(output_data + i, clamped);
2019 }
2020#endif // NEON
2021
2022 if (i < size) {
2023 // Process broadcast scalar.
2024 const int32 input1_val = params.input1_offset + input1_data;
2025 const int32 shifted_input1_val = input1_val * (1 << params.left_shift);
2026 const int32 scaled_input1_val =
2027 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplierSmallerThanOneExp(
2028 shifted_input1_val, params.input1_multiplier, params.input1_shift);
2029
2030 for (; i < size; ++i) {
2031 const int32 input2_val = params.input2_offset + input2_data[i];
2032 const int32 shifted_input2_val = input2_val * (1 << params.left_shift);
2033 const int32 scaled_input2_val =
2034 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplierSmallerThanOneExp(
2035 shifted_input2_val, params.input2_multiplier,
2036 params.input2_shift);
2037 const int32 raw_sum = scaled_input1_val + scaled_input2_val;
2038 const int32 raw_output =
2039 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplierSmallerThanOneExp(
2040 raw_sum, params.output_multiplier, params.output_shift) +
2041 params.output_offset;
2042 const int32 clamped_output =
2043 std::min(params.quantized_activation_max,
2044 std::max(params.quantized_activation_min, raw_output));
2045 output_data[i] = static_cast<uint8>(clamped_output);
2046 }
2047 }
2048}
2049
2050// Scalar-broadcast add that can be used for inner loop of more general
2051// broadcast add, so that, for example, scalar-broadcast with batch will still
2052// be fast.
2053inline void AddScalarBroadcast(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
2054 float broadcast_value, const float* input2_data,
2055 float* output_data) {
2056 int i = 0;
2057#ifdef USE_NEON
2058 const float32x4_t output_activation_min_vector =
2059 vdupq_n_f32(params.float_activation_min);
2060 const float32x4_t output_activation_max_vector =
2061 vdupq_n_f32(params.float_activation_max);
2062 const float32x4_t broadcast_value_dup = vdupq_n_f32(broadcast_value);
2063 for (; i <= size - 4; i += 4) {
2064 const float32x4_t input2_val_original = vld1q_f32(input2_data + i);
2065
2066 const float32x4_t output =
2067 vaddq_f32(input2_val_original, broadcast_value_dup);
2068
2069 const float32x4_t clamped =
2070 vmaxq_f32(output_activation_min_vector,
2071 vminq_f32(output_activation_max_vector, output));
2072 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, clamped);
2073 }
2074#endif // NEON
2075
2076 for (; i < size; ++i) {
2077 auto x = broadcast_value + input2_data[i];
2078 output_data[i] = ActivationFunctionWithMinMax(
2079 x, params.float_activation_min, params.float_activation_max);
2080 }
2081}
2082
2083inline void Add(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2084 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const uint8* input1_data,
2085 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const uint8* input2_data,
2086 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, uint8* output_data) {
2087 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(params.quantized_activation_min,
2088 params.quantized_activation_max);
2089 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Add/8bit");
2090 const int flat_size =
2091 MatchingElementsSize(input1_shape, input2_shape, output_shape);
2092
2093 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input1_offset, -256);
2094 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input2_offset, -256);
2095 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input1_offset, 256);
2096 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input2_offset, 256);
2097 AddElementwise(flat_size, params, input1_data, input2_data, output_data);
2098}
2099
2100inline void Add(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2101 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const int16* input1_data,
2102 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const int16* input2_data,
2103 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, int16* output_data) {
2104 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Add/Int16");
2105 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(params.quantized_activation_min,
2106 params.quantized_activation_max);
2107
2108 const int input1_shift = params.input1_shift;
2109 const int flat_size =
2110 MatchingElementsSize(input1_shape, input2_shape, output_shape);
2111 const int16 output_activation_min = params.quantized_activation_min;
2112 const int16 output_activation_max = params.quantized_activation_max;
2113
2114 TFLITE_DCHECK(input1_shift == 0 || params.input2_shift == 0);
2115 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(input1_shift, 0);
2116 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(params.input2_shift, 0);
2117 const int16* not_shift_input = input1_shift == 0 ? input1_data : input2_data;
2118 const int16* shift_input = input1_shift == 0 ? input2_data : input1_data;
2119 const int input_right_shift =
2120 input1_shift == 0 ? -params.input2_shift : -input1_shift;
2121
2122 for (int i = 0; i < flat_size; i++) {
2123 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
2124 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 0>;
2125
2126 F0 input_ready_scaled = F0::FromRaw(not_shift_input[i]);
2127 F0 scaled_input = F0::FromRaw(
2128 gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT(shift_input[i], input_right_shift));
2129 F0 result = gemmlowp::SaturatingAdd(scaled_input, input_ready_scaled);
2130 const int16 raw_output = result.raw();
2131 const int16 clamped_output = std::min(
2132 output_activation_max, std::max(output_activation_min, raw_output));
2133 output_data[i] = clamped_output;
2134 }
2135}
2136
2137inline void Add(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2138 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const int32* input1_data,
2139 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const int32* input2_data,
2140 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, int32* output_data) {
2141 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Add/int32");
2142
2143 auto input1_map = MapAsVector(input1_data, input1_shape);
2144 auto input2_map = MapAsVector(input2_data, input2_shape);
2145 auto output_map = MapAsVector(output_data, output_shape);
2146 if (input1_shape == input2_shape) {
2147 output_map.array() = (input1_map.array() + input2_map.array())
2148 .cwiseMax(params.quantized_activation_min)
2149 .cwiseMin(params.quantized_activation_max);
2150 } else if (input2_shape.FlatSize() == 1) {
2151 auto scalar = input2_data[0];
2152 output_map.array() = (input1_map.array() + scalar)
2153 .cwiseMax(params.quantized_activation_min)
2154 .cwiseMin(params.quantized_activation_max);
2155 } else if (input1_shape.FlatSize() == 1) {
2156 auto scalar = input1_data[0];
2157 output_map.array() = (scalar + input2_map.array())
2158 .cwiseMax(params.quantized_activation_min)
2159 .cwiseMin(params.quantized_activation_max);
2160 } else {
2161 reference_ops::BroadcastAdd4DSlow(params, input1_shape, input1_data,
2162 input2_shape, input2_data, output_shape,
2163 output_data);
2164 }
2165}
2166
2167template <typename T>
2168inline void BroadcastAddDispatch(
2169 const ArithmeticParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input1_shape,
2170 const T* input1_data, const RuntimeShape& input2_shape,
2171 const T* input2_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
2172 if (params.broadcast_category == BroadcastableOpCategory::kGenericBroadcast) {
2173 return BroadcastAdd4DSlow(params, input1_shape, input1_data, input2_shape,
2174 input2_data, output_shape, output_data);
2175 }
2176
2177 BinaryBroadcastFiveFold(
2178 params, input1_shape, input1_data, input2_shape, input2_data,
2179 output_shape, output_data,
2180 static_cast<void (*)(int, const ArithmeticParams&, const T*, const T*,
2181 T*)>(AddElementwise),
2182 static_cast<void (*)(int, const ArithmeticParams&, T, const T*, T*)>(
2183 AddScalarBroadcast));
2184}
2185
2186inline void BroadcastAddFivefold(const ArithmeticParams& unswitched_params,
2187 const RuntimeShape& unswitched_input1_shape,
2188 const uint8* unswitched_input1_data,
2189 const RuntimeShape& unswitched_input2_shape,
2190 const uint8* unswitched_input2_data,
2191 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
2192 uint8* output_data) {
2193 BroadcastAddDispatch(unswitched_params, unswitched_input1_shape,
2194 unswitched_input1_data, unswitched_input2_shape,
2195 unswitched_input2_data, output_shape, output_data);
2196}

2198inline void BroadcastAddFivefold(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2199 const RuntimeShape& unswitched_input1_shape,
2200 const float* unswitched_input1_data,
2201 const RuntimeShape& unswitched_input2_shape,
2202 const float* unswitched_input2_data,
2203 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
2204 float* output_data) {
2205 BroadcastAddDispatch(params, unswitched_input1_shape, unswitched_input1_data,
2206 unswitched_input2_shape, unswitched_input2_data,
2207 output_shape, output_data);
2208}
2209
2210inline void MulElementwise(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
2211 const float* input1_data, const float* input2_data,
2212 float* output_data) {
2213 const float output_activation_min = params.float_activation_min;
2214 const float output_activation_max = params.float_activation_max;
2215
2216 int i = 0;
2217#ifdef USE_NEON
2218 const auto activation_min = vdupq_n_f32(output_activation_min);
2219 const auto activation_max = vdupq_n_f32(output_activation_max);
2220 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
2221 auto a10 = vld1q_f32(input1_data + i);
2222 auto a11 = vld1q_f32(input1_data + i + 4);
2223 auto a12 = vld1q_f32(input1_data + i + 8);
2224 auto a13 = vld1q_f32(input1_data + i + 12);
2225 auto a20 = vld1q_f32(input2_data + i);
2226 auto a21 = vld1q_f32(input2_data + i + 4);
2227 auto a22 = vld1q_f32(input2_data + i + 8);
2228 auto a23 = vld1q_f32(input2_data + i + 12);
2229 auto x0 = vmulq_f32(a10, a20);
2230 auto x1 = vmulq_f32(a11, a21);
2231 auto x2 = vmulq_f32(a12, a22);
2232 auto x3 = vmulq_f32(a13, a23);
2233
2234 x0 = vmaxq_f32(activation_min, x0);
2235 x1 = vmaxq_f32(activation_min, x1);
2236 x2 = vmaxq_f32(activation_min, x2);
2237 x3 = vmaxq_f32(activation_min, x3);
2238 x0 = vminq_f32(activation_max, x0);
2239 x1 = vminq_f32(activation_max, x1);
2240 x2 = vminq_f32(activation_max, x2);
2241 x3 = vminq_f32(activation_max, x3);
2242
2243 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, x0);
2244 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 4, x1);
2245 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 8, x2);
2246 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 12, x3);
2247 }
2248 for (; i <= size - 4; i += 4) {
2249 auto a1 = vld1q_f32(input1_data + i);
2250 auto a2 = vld1q_f32(input2_data + i);
2251 auto x = vmulq_f32(a1, a2);
2252
2253 x = vmaxq_f32(activation_min, x);
2254 x = vminq_f32(activation_max, x);
2255
2256 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, x);
2257 }
2258#endif // NEON
2259
2260 for (; i < size; i++) {
2261 auto x = input1_data[i] * input2_data[i];
2262 output_data[i] = ActivationFunctionWithMinMax(x, output_activation_min,
2263 output_activation_max);
2264 }
2265}
2266
2267inline void Mul(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2268 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const float* input1_data,
2269 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const float* input2_data,
2270 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data) {
2271 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Mul");
2272
2273 const int flat_size =
2274 MatchingElementsSize(input1_shape, input2_shape, output_shape);
2275 MulElementwise(flat_size, params, input1_data, input2_data, output_data);
2276}

2278inline void Mul(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2279 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const int32* input1_data,
2280 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const int32* input2_data,
2281 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, int32* output_data) {
2282 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Mul/int32/activation");
2283
2284 const int flat_size =
2285 MatchingElementsSize(input1_shape, input2_shape, output_shape);
2286 const int32 output_activation_min = params.quantized_activation_min;
2287 const int32 output_activation_max = params.quantized_activation_max;
2288 for (int i = 0; i < flat_size; ++i) {
2289 output_data[i] = ActivationFunctionWithMinMax(
2290 input1_data[i] * input2_data[i], output_activation_min,
2291 output_activation_max);
2292 }
2293}
2294
2295inline void MulNoActivation(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2296 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape,
2297 const int32* input1_data,
2298 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape,
2299 const int32* input2_data,
2300 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
2301 int32* output_data) {
2302 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Mul/int32");
2303
2304 auto input1_map = MapAsVector(input1_data, input1_shape);
2305 auto input2_map = MapAsVector(input2_data, input2_shape);
2306 auto output_map = MapAsVector(output_data, output_shape);
2307 if (input1_shape == input2_shape) {
2308 output_map.array() = input1_map.array() * input2_map.array();
2309 } else if (input2_shape.FlatSize() == 1) {
2310 auto scalar = input2_data[0];
2311 output_map.array() = input1_map.array() * scalar;
2312 } else if (input1_shape.FlatSize() == 1) {
2313 auto scalar = input1_data[0];
2314 output_map.array() = scalar * input2_map.array();
2315 } else {
2316 reference_ops::BroadcastMul4DSlow(params, input1_shape, input1_data,
2317 input2_shape, input2_data, output_shape,
2318 output_data);
2319 }
2320}
2321
2322inline void Mul(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2323 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const int16* input1_data,
2324 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const int16* input2_data,
2325 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, int16* output_data) {
2326 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Mul/Int16/NoActivation");
2327 // This is a copy of the reference implementation. We do not currently have a
2328 // properly optimized version.
2329
2330 const int flat_size =
2331 MatchingElementsSize(input1_shape, input2_shape, output_shape);
2332
2333 for (int i = 0; i < flat_size; i++) {
2334 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
2335 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 0>;
2336
2337 F0 unclamped_result =
2338 F0::FromRaw(input1_data[i]) * F0::FromRaw(input2_data[i]);
2339 output_data[i] = unclamped_result.raw();
2340 }
2341}
2342
2343inline void Mul(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2344 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const int16* input1_data,
2345 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const int16* input2_data,
2346 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, uint8* output_data) {
2347 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Mul/Int16Uint8");
2348 // This is a copy of the reference implementation. We do not currently have a
2349 // properly optimized version.
2350 const int32 output_activation_min = params.quantized_activation_min;
2351 const int32 output_activation_max = params.quantized_activation_max;
2352 const int32 output_offset = params.output_offset;
2353 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(output_activation_min, output_activation_max);
2354
2355 const int flat_size =
2356 MatchingElementsSize(input1_shape, input2_shape, output_shape);
2357
2358 for (int i = 0; i < flat_size; i++) {
2359 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
2360 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 0>;
2361
2362 F0 unclamped_result =
2363 F0::FromRaw(input1_data[i]) * F0::FromRaw(input2_data[i]);
2364 int16 rescaled_result =
2365 gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT(unclamped_result.raw(), 8);
2366 int16 clamped_result =
2367 std::min<int16>(output_activation_max - output_offset, rescaled_result);
2368 clamped_result =
2369 std::max<int16>(output_activation_min - output_offset, clamped_result);
2370 output_data[i] = output_offset + clamped_result;
2371 }
2372}
2373
2374// Element-wise mul that can often be used for inner loop of broadcast Mul as
2375// well as the non-broadcast Mul.
2376inline void MulElementwise(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
2377 const uint8* input1_data, const uint8* input2_data,
2378 uint8* output_data) {
2379 int i = 0;
2380 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input1_offset, -256);
2381 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input1_offset, 256);
2382 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input2_offset, -256);
2383 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input2_offset, 256);
2384 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.output_offset, -256);
2385 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.output_offset, 256);
2386#ifdef USE_NEON
2387 const auto input1_offset_vector = vdupq_n_s16(params.input1_offset);
2388 const auto input2_offset_vector = vdupq_n_s16(params.input2_offset);
2389 const auto output_offset_vector = vdupq_n_s16(params.output_offset);
2390 const auto output_activation_min_vector =
2391 vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_min);
2392 const auto output_activation_max_vector =
2393 vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_max);
2394 const int left_shift = std::max(0, params.output_shift);
2395 const int right_shift = std::max(0, -params.output_shift);
2396 const int32x4_t left_shift_vec = vdupq_n_s32(left_shift);
2397 for (; i <= size - 8; i += 8) {
2398 // We load / store 8 at a time, multiplying as two sets of 4 int32s.
2399 const auto input1_val_original = vld1_u8(input1_data + i);
2400 const auto input2_val_original = vld1_u8(input2_data + i);
2401 const auto input1_val_s16 =
2402 vreinterpretq_s16_u16(vmovl_u8(input1_val_original));
2403 const auto input2_val_s16 =
2404 vreinterpretq_s16_u16(vmovl_u8(input2_val_original));
2405 const auto input1_val = vaddq_s16(input1_val_s16, input1_offset_vector);
2406 const auto input2_val = vaddq_s16(input2_val_s16, input2_offset_vector);
2407
2408 const auto input1_val_low = vget_low_s16(input1_val);
2409 const auto input1_val_high = vget_high_s16(input1_val);
2410 const auto input2_val_low = vget_low_s16(input2_val);
2411 const auto input2_val_high = vget_high_s16(input2_val);
2412
2413 auto p1 = vmull_s16(input2_val_low, input1_val_low);
2414 auto p2 = vmull_s16(input2_val_high, input1_val_high);
2415
2416 p1 = vshlq_s32(p1, left_shift_vec);
2417 p2 = vshlq_s32(p2, left_shift_vec);
2418 p1 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(p1, params.output_multiplier);
2419 p2 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(p2, params.output_multiplier);
2420 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
2421 p1 = RoundingDivideByPOT(p1, right_shift);
2422 p2 = RoundingDivideByPOT(p2, right_shift);
2423
2424 const auto p1_narrowed = vqmovn_s32(p1);
2425 const auto p2_narrowed = vqmovn_s32(p2);
2426 const auto p =
2427 vaddq_s16(vcombine_s16(p1_narrowed, p2_narrowed), output_offset_vector);
2428 const auto clamped =
2429 vmax_u8(output_activation_min_vector,
2430 vmin_u8(output_activation_max_vector, vqmovun_s16(p)));
2431 vst1_u8(output_data + i, clamped);
2432 }
2433#endif // NEON
2434
2435 for (; i < size; ++i) {
2436 const int32 input1_val = params.input1_offset + input1_data[i];
2437 const int32 input2_val = params.input2_offset + input2_data[i];
2438 const int32 unclamped_result =
2439 params.output_offset +
2440 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(input1_val * input2_val,
2441 params.output_multiplier,
2442 params.output_shift);
2443 const int32 clamped_output =
2444 std::min(params.quantized_activation_max,
2445 std::max(params.quantized_activation_min, unclamped_result));
2446 output_data[i] = static_cast<uint8>(clamped_output);
2447 }
2448}
2449
2450// Broadcast mul that can often be used for inner loop of broadcast Mul.
2451inline void MulSimpleBroadcast(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
2452 const uint8 broadcast_value,
2453 const uint8* input2_data, uint8* output_data) {
2454 const int16 input1_val = params.input1_offset + broadcast_value;
2455
2456 int i = 0;
2457 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input1_offset, -256);
2458 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input1_offset, 256);
2459 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input2_offset, -256);
2460 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input2_offset, 256);
2461 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.output_offset, -256);
2462 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.output_offset, 256);
2463#ifdef USE_NEON
2464 const auto input2_offset_vector = vdupq_n_s16(params.input2_offset);
2465 const auto output_offset_vector = vdupq_n_s16(params.output_offset);
2466 const auto output_activation_min_vector =
2467 vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_min);
2468 const auto output_activation_max_vector =
2469 vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_max);
2470 const int left_shift = std::max(0, params.output_shift);
2471 const int right_shift = std::max(0, -params.output_shift);
2472 const int32x4_t left_shift_vec = vdupq_n_s32(left_shift);
2473 for (; i <= size - 8; i += 8) {
2474 // We load / store 8 at a time, multiplying as two sets of 4 int32s.
2475 const auto input2_val_original = vld1_u8(input2_data + i);
2476 const auto input2_val_s16 =
2477 vreinterpretq_s16_u16(vmovl_u8(input2_val_original));
2478 const auto input2_val = vaddq_s16(input2_val_s16, input2_offset_vector);
2479
2480 const auto input2_val_low = vget_low_s16(input2_val);
2481 const auto input2_val_high = vget_high_s16(input2_val);
2482
2483 auto p1 = vmull_n_s16(input2_val_low, input1_val);
2484 auto p2 = vmull_n_s16(input2_val_high, input1_val);
2485
2486 p1 = vshlq_s32(p1, left_shift_vec);
2487 p2 = vshlq_s32(p2, left_shift_vec);
2488 p1 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(p1, params.output_multiplier);
2489 p2 = vqrdmulhq_n_s32(p2, params.output_multiplier);
2490 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
2491 p1 = RoundingDivideByPOT(p1, right_shift);
2492 p2 = RoundingDivideByPOT(p2, right_shift);
2493
2494 const auto p1_narrowed = vmovn_s32(p1);
2495 const auto p2_narrowed = vmovn_s32(p2);
2496 const auto p =
2497 vaddq_s16(vcombine_s16(p1_narrowed, p2_narrowed), output_offset_vector);
2498 const auto clamped =
2499 vmax_u8(output_activation_min_vector,
2500 vmin_u8(output_activation_max_vector, vqmovun_s16(p)));
2501 vst1_u8(output_data + i, clamped);
2502 }
2503#endif // NEON
2504
2505 for (; i < size; ++i) {
2506 const int32 input2_val = params.input2_offset + input2_data[i];
2507 const int32 unclamped_result =
2508 params.output_offset +
2509 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(input1_val * input2_val,
2510 params.output_multiplier,
2511 params.output_shift);
2512 const int32 clamped_output =
2513 std::min(params.quantized_activation_max,
2514 std::max(params.quantized_activation_min, unclamped_result));
2515 output_data[i] = static_cast<uint8>(clamped_output);
2516 }
2517}
2518
2519// Broadcast mul that can often be used for inner loop of broadcast Mul.
2520// This function will handle scalar_value (LHS) * vector_values (RHS).
2521// Since it's a float function, input params does not matter here.
2522inline void MulSimpleBroadcast(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
2523 const float broadcast_value,
2524 const float* input2_data, float* output_data) {
2525 int i = 0;
2526#ifdef USE_NEON
2527 const float32x4_t output_activation_min_vector =
2528 vdupq_n_f32(params.float_activation_min);
2529 const float32x4_t output_activation_max_vector =
2530 vdupq_n_f32(params.float_activation_max);
2531 const float32x4_t broadcast_value_dup = vdupq_n_f32(broadcast_value);
2532 for (; i <= size - 4; i += 4) {
2533 const float32x4_t input2_val_original = vld1q_f32(input2_data + i);
2534
2535 const float32x4_t output =
2536 vmulq_f32(input2_val_original, broadcast_value_dup);
2537
2538 const float32x4_t clamped =
2539 vmaxq_f32(output_activation_min_vector,
2540 vminq_f32(output_activation_max_vector, output));
2541 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, clamped);
2542 }
2543#endif // NEON
2544
2545 for (; i < size; ++i) {
2546 float x = broadcast_value * input2_data[i];
2547 output_data[i] = ActivationFunctionWithMinMax(
2548 x, params.float_activation_min, params.float_activation_max);
2549 }
2550}
2551
2552inline void Mul(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2553 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const uint8* input1_data,
2554 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const uint8* input2_data,
2555 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, uint8* output_data) {
2556 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(params.quantized_activation_min,
2557 params.quantized_activation_max);
2558 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Mul/8bit");
2559 const int flat_size =
2560 MatchingElementsSize(input1_shape, input2_shape, output_shape);
2561
2562 MulElementwise(flat_size, params, input1_data, input2_data, output_data);
2563}
2564
2565template <typename T>
2566inline void BroadcastMulDispatch(
2567 const ArithmeticParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input1_shape,
2568 const T* input1_data, const RuntimeShape& input2_shape,
2569 const T* input2_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
2570 if (params.broadcast_category == BroadcastableOpCategory::kGenericBroadcast) {
2571 return BroadcastMul4DSlow(params, input1_shape, input1_data, input2_shape,
2572 input2_data, output_shape, output_data);
2573 }
2574
2575 BinaryBroadcastFiveFold(
2576 params, input1_shape, input1_data, input2_shape, input2_data,
2577 output_shape, output_data,
2578 static_cast<void (*)(int, const ArithmeticParams&, const T*, const T*,
2579 T*)>(MulElementwise),
2580 static_cast<void (*)(int, const ArithmeticParams&, T, const T*, T*)>(
2581 MulSimpleBroadcast));
2582}
2583
2584inline void BroadcastMulFivefold(const ArithmeticParams& unswitched_params,
2585 const RuntimeShape& unswitched_input1_shape,
2586 const uint8* unswitched_input1_data,
2587 const RuntimeShape& unswitched_input2_shape,
2588 const uint8* unswitched_input2_data,
2589 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
2590 uint8* output_data) {
2591 BroadcastMulDispatch(unswitched_params, unswitched_input1_shape,
2592 unswitched_input1_data, unswitched_input2_shape,
2593 unswitched_input2_data, output_shape, output_data);
2594}
2595
2596inline void BroadcastMulFivefold(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2597 const RuntimeShape& unswitched_input1_shape,
2598 const float* unswitched_input1_data,
2599 const RuntimeShape& unswitched_input2_shape,
2600 const float* unswitched_input2_data,
2601 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
2602 float* output_data) {
2603 BroadcastMulDispatch(params, unswitched_input1_shape, unswitched_input1_data,
2604 unswitched_input2_shape, unswitched_input2_data,
2605 output_shape, output_data);
2606}
2607
2608// TODO(jiawen): We can implement BroadcastDiv on buffers of arbitrary
2609// dimensionality if the runtime code does a single loop over one dimension
2610// that handles broadcasting as the base case. The code generator would then
2611// generate max(D1, D2) nested for loops.
2612// TODO(benoitjacob): BroadcastDiv is intentionally duplicated from
2613// reference_ops.h. Once an optimized version is implemented and NdArrayDesc<T>
2614// is no longer referenced in this file, move NdArrayDesc<T> from types.h to
2615// reference_ops.h.
2616template <typename T, int N = 5>
2617void BroadcastDivSlow(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2618 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input1_shape,
2619 const T* input1_data,
2620 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input2_shape,
2621 const T* input2_data,
2622 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape,
2623 T* output_data) {
2624 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("BroadcastDivSlow");
2625 T output_activation_min;
2626 T output_activation_max;
2627 GetActivationParams(params, &output_activation_min, &output_activation_max);
2628
2629 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input1_shape.DimensionsCount(), N);
2630 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input2_shape.DimensionsCount(), N);
2631 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_output_shape.DimensionsCount(), N);
2632
2633 NdArrayDesc<N> desc1;
2634 NdArrayDesc<N> desc2;
2635 NdArrayDesc<N> output_desc;
2636 NdArrayDescsForElementwiseBroadcast(unextended_input1_shape,
2637 unextended_input2_shape, &desc1, &desc2);
2638 CopyDimsToDesc(RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(N, unextended_output_shape),
2639 &output_desc);
2640
2641 // In Tensorflow, the dimensions are canonically named (batch_number, row,
2642 // col, channel), with extents (batches, height, width, depth), with the
2643 // trailing dimension changing most rapidly (channels has the smallest stride,
2644 // typically 1 element).
2645 //
2646 // In generated C code, we store arrays with the dimensions reversed. The
2647 // first dimension has smallest stride.
2648 //
2649 // We name our variables by their Tensorflow convention, but generate C code
2650 // nesting loops such that the innermost loop has the smallest stride for the
2651 // best cache behavior.
2652 auto div_func = [&](int indexes[N]) {
2653 output_data[SubscriptToIndex(output_desc, indexes)] =
2654 ActivationFunctionWithMinMax(
2655 input1_data[SubscriptToIndex(desc1, indexes)] /
2656 input2_data[SubscriptToIndex(desc2, indexes)],
2657 output_activation_min, output_activation_max);
2658 };
2659 NDOpsHelper<N>(output_desc, div_func);
2660}
2661
2662// TODO: BroadcastDiv is intentionally duplicated from reference_ops.h.
2663// For more details see the comment above the generic version of
2664// BroadcastDivSlow.
2665template <int N = 5>
2666inline void BroadcastDivSlow(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2667 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input1_shape,
2668 const uint8* input1_data,
2669 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input2_shape,
2670 const uint8* input2_data,
2671 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape,
2672 uint8* output_data) {
2673 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input1_shape.DimensionsCount(), N);
2674 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input2_shape.DimensionsCount(), N);
2675 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_output_shape.DimensionsCount(), N);
2676
2677 NdArrayDesc<N> desc1;
2678 NdArrayDesc<N> desc2;
2679 NdArrayDesc<N> output_desc;
2680 NdArrayDescsForElementwiseBroadcast(unextended_input1_shape,
2681 unextended_input2_shape, &desc1, &desc2);
2682 CopyDimsToDesc(RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(N, unextended_output_shape),
2683 &output_desc);
2684
2685 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input1_offset, -256);
2686 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input1_offset, 256);
2687 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.input2_offset, -256);
2688 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.input2_offset, 256);
2689 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(params.output_offset, -256);
2690 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(params.output_offset, 256);
2691
2692 auto div_func = [&](int indexes[N]) {
2693 const int32 input1_val =
2694 params.input1_offset + input1_data[SubscriptToIndex(desc1, indexes)];
2695 const int32 input2_val =
2696 params.input2_offset + input2_data[SubscriptToIndex(desc2, indexes)];
2697 TFLITE_DCHECK_NE(input2_val, 0);
2698 int recip_shift;
2699 const int32 input2_inv =
2700 (input2_val > 0) ? GetReciprocal(input2_val, 31, &recip_shift)
2701 : -GetReciprocal(-input2_val, 31, &recip_shift);
2702 const int headroom = CountLeadingSignBits(input1_val);
2703 const int32 unscaled_quotient = MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplierGreaterThanOne(
2704 input1_val, input2_inv, headroom);
2705 const int total_shift = params.output_shift - recip_shift - headroom;
2706 const int32 unclamped_result =
2707 params.output_offset +
2708 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplierSmallerThanOneExp(
2709 unscaled_quotient, params.output_multiplier, total_shift);
2710 const int32 clamped_output =
2711 std::min(params.quantized_activation_max,
2712 std::max(params.quantized_activation_min, unclamped_result));
2713 output_data[SubscriptToIndex(output_desc, indexes)] =
2714 static_cast<uint8>(clamped_output);
2715 };
2716 NDOpsHelper<N>(output_desc, div_func);
2717}
2718
2719template <typename T>
2720inline void SubWithActivation(
2721 const ArithmeticParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input1_shape,
2722 const T* input1_data, const RuntimeShape& input2_shape,
2723 const T* input2_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
2724 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("SubWithActivation_optimized");
2725 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input1_shape.FlatSize(), input2_shape.FlatSize());
2726 auto input1_map = MapAsVector(input1_data, input1_shape);
2727 auto input2_map = MapAsVector(input2_data, input2_shape);
2728 auto output_map = MapAsVector(output_data, output_shape);
2729 T activation_min, activation_max;
2730 GetActivationParams(params, &activation_min, &activation_max);
2731 output_map.array() = (input1_map.array() - input2_map.array())
2732 .cwiseMin(activation_max)
2733 .cwiseMax(activation_min);
2734}
2735
2736inline void SubNonBroadcast(const ArithmeticParams& params,
2737 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape,
2738 const float* input1_data,
2739 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape,
2740 const float* input2_data,
2741 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
2742 float* output_data) {
2743 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("SubNonBroadcast");
2744 SubWithActivation<float>(params, input1_shape, input1_data, input2_shape,
2745 input2_data, output_shape, output_data);
2746}
2747
2748template <typename T>
2749void Sub(const ArithmeticParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input1_shape,
2750 const T* input1_data, const RuntimeShape& input2_shape,
2751 const T* input2_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
2752 T* output_data) {
2753 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Sub");
2754
2755 auto input1_map = MapAsVector(input1_data, input1_shape);
2756 auto input2_map = MapAsVector(input2_data, input2_shape);
2757 auto output_map = MapAsVector(output_data, output_shape);
2758 if (input1_shape == input2_shape) {
2759 output_map.array() = input1_map.array() - input2_map.array();
2760 } else if (input1_shape.FlatSize() == 1) {
2761 auto scalar = input1_data[0];
2762 output_map.array() = scalar - input2_map.array();
2763 } else if (input2_shape.FlatSize() == 1) {
2764 auto scalar = input2_data[0];
2765 output_map.array() = input1_map.array() - scalar;
2766 } else {
2767 BroadcastSubSlow(params, input1_shape, input1_data, input2_shape,
2768 input2_data, output_shape, output_data);
2769 }
2770}
2771
2772inline void LstmCell(
2773 const LstmCellParams& params, const RuntimeShape& unextended_input_shape,
2774 const float* input_data, const RuntimeShape& unextended_prev_activ_shape,
2775 const float* prev_activ_data, const RuntimeShape& weights_shape,
2776 const float* weights_data, const RuntimeShape& unextended_bias_shape,
2777 const float* bias_data, const RuntimeShape& unextended_prev_state_shape,
2778 const float* prev_state_data,
2779 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_state_shape, float* output_state_data,
2780 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_activ_shape, float* output_activ_data,
2781 const RuntimeShape& unextended_concat_temp_shape, float* concat_temp_data,
2782 const RuntimeShape& unextended_activ_temp_shape, float* activ_temp_data,
2783 CpuBackendContext* cpu_backend_context) {
2784 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("LstmCell");
2785 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2786 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_prev_activ_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2787 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_bias_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2788 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_prev_state_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2789 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_output_state_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2790 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_output_activ_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2791 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_concat_temp_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2792 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_activ_temp_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2793 const RuntimeShape input_shape =
2794 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_input_shape);
2795 const RuntimeShape prev_activ_shape =
2796 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_prev_activ_shape);
2797 const RuntimeShape bias_shape =
2798 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_bias_shape);
2799 const RuntimeShape prev_state_shape =
2800 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_prev_state_shape);
2801 const RuntimeShape output_state_shape =
2802 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_output_state_shape);
2803 const RuntimeShape output_activ_shape =
2804 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_output_activ_shape);
2805 const RuntimeShape concat_temp_shape =
2806 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_concat_temp_shape);
2807 const RuntimeShape activ_temp_shape =
2808 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_activ_temp_shape);
2809 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(weights_shape.DimensionsCount(), 2);
2810
2811 const int weights_dim_count = weights_shape.DimensionsCount();
2812 MatchingDim( // batches
2813 input_shape, 0, prev_activ_shape, 0, prev_state_shape, 0,
2814 output_state_shape, 0, output_activ_shape, 0);
2815 MatchingDim( // height
2816 input_shape, 1, prev_activ_shape, 1, prev_state_shape, 1,
2817 output_state_shape, 1, output_activ_shape, 1);
2818 MatchingDim( // width
2819 input_shape, 2, prev_activ_shape, 2, prev_state_shape, 2,
2820 output_state_shape, 2, output_activ_shape, 2);
2821 const int input_depth = input_shape.Dims(3);
2822 const int prev_activ_depth = prev_activ_shape.Dims(3);
2823 const int total_input_depth = prev_activ_depth + input_depth;
2824 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(weights_shape.Dims(weights_dim_count - 1),
2825 total_input_depth);
2826 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(FlatSizeSkipDim(bias_shape, 3), 1);
2827 const int intern_activ_depth =
2828 MatchingDim(weights_shape, weights_dim_count - 2, bias_shape, 3);
2829 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(weights_shape.FlatSize(),
2830 intern_activ_depth * total_input_depth);
2831 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(intern_activ_depth % 4, 0);
2832 const int output_depth =
2833 MatchingDim(prev_state_shape, 3, prev_activ_shape, 3, output_state_shape,
2834 3, output_activ_shape, 3);
2835 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_depth, intern_activ_depth / 4);
2836
2837 // Concatenate prev_activ and input data together
2838 std::vector<float const*> concat_input_arrays_data;
2839 std::vector<RuntimeShape const*> concat_input_arrays_shapes;
2840 concat_input_arrays_data.push_back(input_data);
2841 concat_input_arrays_data.push_back(prev_activ_data);
2842 concat_input_arrays_shapes.push_back(&input_shape);
2843 concat_input_arrays_shapes.push_back(&prev_activ_shape);
2844 tflite::ConcatenationParams concat_params;
2845 concat_params.axis = 3;
2846 concat_params.inputs_count = concat_input_arrays_data.size();
2847 Concatenation(concat_params, &(concat_input_arrays_shapes[0]),
2848 &(concat_input_arrays_data[0]), concat_temp_shape,
2849 concat_temp_data);
2850
2851 // Fully connected
2852 tflite::FullyConnectedParams fc_params;
2853 fc_params.float_activation_min = std::numeric_limits<float>::lowest();
2854 fc_params.float_activation_max = std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
2855 fc_params.lhs_cacheable = false;
2856 fc_params.rhs_cacheable = false;
2857 FullyConnected(fc_params, concat_temp_shape, concat_temp_data, weights_shape,
2858 weights_data, bias_shape, bias_data, activ_temp_shape,
2859 activ_temp_data, cpu_backend_context);
2860
2861 // Map raw arrays to Eigen arrays so we can use Eigen's optimized array
2862 // operations.
2863 ArrayMap<float> activ_temp_map =
2864 MapAsArrayWithLastDimAsRows(activ_temp_data, activ_temp_shape);
2865 auto input_gate_sm = activ_temp_map.block(0 * output_depth, 0, output_depth,
2866 activ_temp_map.cols());
2867 auto new_input_sm = activ_temp_map.block(1 * output_depth, 0, output_depth,
2868 activ_temp_map.cols());
2869 auto forget_gate_sm = activ_temp_map.block(2 * output_depth, 0, output_depth,
2870 activ_temp_map.cols());
2871 auto output_gate_sm = activ_temp_map.block(3 * output_depth, 0, output_depth,
2872 activ_temp_map.cols());
2873 ArrayMap<const float> prev_state_map =
2874 MapAsArrayWithLastDimAsRows(prev_state_data, prev_state_shape);
2875 ArrayMap<float> output_state_map =
2876 MapAsArrayWithLastDimAsRows(output_state_data, output_state_shape);
2877 ArrayMap<float> output_activ_map =
2878 MapAsArrayWithLastDimAsRows(output_activ_data, output_activ_shape);
2879
2880 // Combined memory state and final output calculation
2881 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label2("MemoryStateAndFinalOutput");
2882 output_state_map =
2883 input_gate_sm.unaryExpr(Eigen::internal::scalar_logistic_op<float>()) *
2884 new_input_sm.tanh() +
2885 forget_gate_sm.unaryExpr(Eigen::internal::scalar_logistic_op<float>()) *
2886 prev_state_map;
2887 output_activ_map =
2888 output_gate_sm.unaryExpr(Eigen::internal::scalar_logistic_op<float>()) *
2889 output_state_map.tanh();
2890}
2891
2892template <int StateIntegerBits>
2893inline void LstmCell(
2894 const LstmCellParams& params, const RuntimeShape& unextended_input_shape,
2895 const uint8* input_data_uint8,
2896 const RuntimeShape& unextended_prev_activ_shape,
2897 const uint8* prev_activ_data_uint8, const RuntimeShape& weights_shape,
2898 const uint8* weights_data_uint8, const RuntimeShape& unextended_bias_shape,
2899 const int32* bias_data_int32,
2900 const RuntimeShape& unextended_prev_state_shape,
2901 const int16* prev_state_data_int16,
2902 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_state_shape,
2903 int16* output_state_data_int16,
2904 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_activ_shape,
2905 uint8* output_activ_data_uint8,
2906 const RuntimeShape& unextended_concat_temp_shape,
2907 uint8* concat_temp_data_uint8,
2908 const RuntimeShape& unextended_activ_temp_shape,
2909 int16* activ_temp_data_int16, CpuBackendContext* cpu_backend_context) {
2910 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label(
2911 "LstmCell/quantized (8bit external, 16bit internal)");
2912 int32 weights_zero_point = params.weights_zero_point;
2913 int32 accum_multiplier = params.accum_multiplier;
2914 int accum_shift = params.accum_shift;
2915 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2916 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_prev_activ_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2917 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_bias_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2918 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_prev_state_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2919 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_output_state_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2920 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_output_activ_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2921 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_concat_temp_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2922 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_activ_temp_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
2923 const RuntimeShape input_shape =
2924 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_input_shape);
2925 const RuntimeShape prev_activ_shape =
2926 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_prev_activ_shape);
2927 const RuntimeShape bias_shape =
2928 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_bias_shape);
2929 const RuntimeShape prev_state_shape =
2930 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_prev_state_shape);
2931 const RuntimeShape output_state_shape =
2932 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_output_state_shape);
2933 const RuntimeShape output_activ_shape =
2934 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_output_activ_shape);
2935 const RuntimeShape concat_temp_shape =
2936 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_concat_temp_shape);
2937 const RuntimeShape activ_temp_shape =
2938 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_activ_temp_shape);
2939 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(weights_shape.DimensionsCount(), 2);
2940
2941 // Gather dimensions information, and perform consistency checks.
2942 const int weights_dim_count = weights_shape.DimensionsCount();
2943 const int outer_size = MatchingFlatSizeSkipDim(
2944 input_shape, 3, prev_activ_shape, prev_state_shape, output_state_shape,
2945 output_activ_shape);
2946 const int input_depth = input_shape.Dims(3);
2947 const int prev_activ_depth = prev_activ_shape.Dims(3);
2948 const int total_input_depth = prev_activ_depth + input_depth;
2949 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(weights_shape.Dims(weights_dim_count - 1),
2950 total_input_depth);
2951 const int intern_activ_depth =
2952 MatchingDim(weights_shape, weights_dim_count - 2, bias_shape, 3);
2953 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(weights_shape.FlatSize(),
2954 intern_activ_depth * total_input_depth);
2955 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(FlatSizeSkipDim(bias_shape, 3), 1);
2956 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(intern_activ_depth % 4, 0);
2957 const int output_depth =
2958 MatchingDim(prev_state_shape, 3, prev_activ_shape, 3, output_state_shape,
2959 3, output_activ_shape, 3);
2960 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_depth, intern_activ_depth / 4);
2961 const int fc_batches = FlatSizeSkipDim(activ_temp_shape, 3);
2962 const int fc_output_depth =
2963 MatchingDim(weights_shape, weights_dim_count - 2, activ_temp_shape, 3);
2964 const int fc_accum_depth = total_input_depth;
2965 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(fc_output_depth, 4 * output_depth);
2966
2967 // Depth-concatenate prev_activ and input data together.
2968 uint8 const* concat_input_arrays_data[2] = {input_data_uint8,
2969 prev_activ_data_uint8};
2970 const RuntimeShape* concat_input_arrays_shapes[2] = {&input_shape,
2971 &prev_activ_shape};
2972 tflite::ConcatenationParams concat_params;
2973 concat_params.axis = 3;
2974 concat_params.inputs_count = 2;
2975 Concatenation(concat_params, concat_input_arrays_shapes,
2976 concat_input_arrays_data, concat_temp_shape,
2977 concat_temp_data_uint8);
2978
2979 // Implementation of the fully connected node inside the LSTM cell.
2980 // The operands are 8-bit integers, the accumulators are internally 32bit
2981 // integers, and the output is 16-bit fixed-point with 3 integer bits so
2982 // the output range is [-2^3, 2^3] == [-8, 8]. The rationale for that
2983 // is explained in the function comment above.
2984 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<uint8> lhs_params;
2985 lhs_params.rows = fc_output_depth;
2986 lhs_params.cols = fc_accum_depth;
2987 lhs_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kRowMajor;
2988 lhs_params.zero_point = weights_zero_point;
2989 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<uint8> rhs_params;
2990 rhs_params.rows = fc_accum_depth;
2991 rhs_params.cols = fc_batches;
2992 rhs_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kColMajor;
2993 rhs_params.zero_point = 128;
2994 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<int16> dst_params;
2995 dst_params.rows = fc_output_depth;
2996 dst_params.cols = fc_batches;
2997 dst_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kColMajor;
2998 dst_params.zero_point = 0;
2999 cpu_backend_gemm::GemmParams<int32, int16> gemm_params;
3000 gemm_params.bias = bias_data_int32;
3001 gemm_params.multiplier_fixedpoint = accum_multiplier;
3002 gemm_params.multiplier_exponent = accum_shift;
3003 cpu_backend_gemm::Gemm(
3004 lhs_params, weights_data_uint8, rhs_params, concat_temp_data_uint8,
3005 dst_params, activ_temp_data_int16, gemm_params, cpu_backend_context);
3006
3007 // Rest of the LSTM cell: tanh and logistic math functions, and some adds
3008 // and muls, all done in 16-bit fixed-point.
3009 const int16* input_gate_input_ptr = activ_temp_data_int16;
3010 const int16* input_modulation_gate_input_ptr =
3011 activ_temp_data_int16 + output_depth;
3012 const int16* forget_gate_input_ptr = activ_temp_data_int16 + 2 * output_depth;
3013 const int16* output_gate_input_ptr = activ_temp_data_int16 + 3 * output_depth;
3014 const int16* prev_state_ptr = prev_state_data_int16;
3015 int16* output_state_data_ptr = output_state_data_int16;
3016 uint8* output_activ_data_ptr = output_activ_data_uint8;
3017
3018 for (int b = 0; b < outer_size; ++b) {
3019 int c = 0;
3020#ifdef GEMMLOWP_NEON
3021 for (; c <= output_depth - 8; c += 8) {
3022 // Define the fixed-point data types that we will use here. All use
3023 // int16 as the underlying integer type i.e. all are 16-bit fixed-point.
3024 // They only differ by the number of integral vs. fractional bits,
3025 // determining the range of values that they can represent.
3026 //
3027 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
3028 // This is the return type of math functions such as tanh, logistic,
3029 // whose range is in [-1, 1].
3030 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 0>;
3031 // F3 uses 3 integer bits, range [-8, 8].
3032 // This is the range of the previous fully-connected node's output,
3033 // which is our input here.
3034 using F3 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 3>;
3035 // FS uses StateIntegerBits integer bits, range [-2^StateIntegerBits,
3036 // 2^StateIntegerBits]. It's used to represent the internal state, whose
3037 // number of integer bits is currently dictated by the model. See comment
3038 // on the StateIntegerBits template parameter above.
3039 using FS = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, StateIntegerBits>;
3040 // Implementation of input gate, using fixed-point logistic function.
3041 F3 input_gate_input = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(input_gate_input_ptr));
3042 input_gate_input_ptr += 8;
3043 F0 input_gate_output = gemmlowp::logistic(input_gate_input);
3044 // Implementation of input modulation gate, using fixed-point tanh
3045 // function.
3046 F3 input_modulation_gate_input =
3047 F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(input_modulation_gate_input_ptr));
3048 input_modulation_gate_input_ptr += 8;
3049 F0 input_modulation_gate_output =
3050 gemmlowp::tanh(input_modulation_gate_input);
3051 // Implementation of forget gate, using fixed-point logistic function.
3052 F3 forget_gate_input = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(forget_gate_input_ptr));
3053 forget_gate_input_ptr += 8;
3054 F0 forget_gate_output = gemmlowp::logistic(forget_gate_input);
3055 // Implementation of output gate, using fixed-point logistic function.
3056 F3 output_gate_input = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(output_gate_input_ptr));
3057 output_gate_input_ptr += 8;
3058 F0 output_gate_output = gemmlowp::logistic(output_gate_input);
3059 // Implementation of internal multiplication nodes, still in fixed-point.
3060 F0 input_times_input_modulation =
3061 input_gate_output * input_modulation_gate_output;
3062 FS prev_state = FS::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(prev_state_ptr));
3063 prev_state_ptr += 8;
3064 FS prev_state_times_forget_state = forget_gate_output * prev_state;
3065 // Implementation of internal addition node, saturating.
3066 FS new_state = gemmlowp::SaturatingAdd(
3067 gemmlowp::Rescale<StateIntegerBits>(input_times_input_modulation),
3068 prev_state_times_forget_state);
3069 // Implementation of last internal Tanh node, still in fixed-point.
3070 // Since a Tanh fixed-point implementation is specialized for a given
3071 // number or integer bits, and each specialization can have a substantial
3072 // code size, and we already used above a Tanh on an input with 3 integer
3073 // bits, and per the table in the above function comment there is no
3074 // significant accuracy to be lost by clamping to [-8, +8] for a
3075 // 3-integer-bits representation, let us just do that. This helps people
3076 // porting this to targets where code footprint must be minimized.
3077 F3 new_state_f3 = gemmlowp::Rescale<3>(new_state);
3078 F0 output_activ_int16 = output_gate_output * gemmlowp::tanh(new_state_f3);
3079 // Store the new internal state back to memory, as 16-bit integers.
3080 // Note: here we store the original value with StateIntegerBits, not
3081 // the rescaled 3-integer-bits value fed to tanh.
3082 vst1q_s16(output_state_data_ptr, new_state.raw());
3083 output_state_data_ptr += 8;
3084 // Down-scale the output activations to 8-bit integers, saturating,
3085 // and store back to memory.
3086 int16x8_t rescaled_output_activ =
3087 gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT(output_activ_int16.raw(), 8);
3088 int8x8_t int8_output_activ = vqmovn_s16(rescaled_output_activ);
3089 uint8x8_t uint8_output_activ =
3090 vadd_u8(vdup_n_u8(128), vreinterpret_u8_s8(int8_output_activ));
3091 vst1_u8(output_activ_data_ptr, uint8_output_activ);
3092 output_activ_data_ptr += 8;
3093 }
3094#endif
3095 for (; c < output_depth; ++c) {
3096 // Define the fixed-point data types that we will use here. All use
3097 // int16 as the underlying integer type i.e. all are 16-bit fixed-point.
3098 // They only differ by the number of integral vs. fractional bits,
3099 // determining the range of values that they can represent.
3100 //
3101 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
3102 // This is the return type of math functions such as tanh, logistic,
3103 // whose range is in [-1, 1].
3104 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 0>;
3105 // F3 uses 3 integer bits, range [-8, 8].
3106 // This is the range of the previous fully-connected node's output,
3107 // which is our input here.
3108 using F3 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 3>;
3109 // FS uses StateIntegerBits integer bits, range [-2^StateIntegerBits,
3110 // 2^StateIntegerBits]. It's used to represent the internal state, whose
3111 // number of integer bits is currently dictated by the model. See comment
3112 // on the StateIntegerBits template parameter above.
3113 using FS = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, StateIntegerBits>;
3114 // Implementation of input gate, using fixed-point logistic function.
3115 F3 input_gate_input = F3::FromRaw(*input_gate_input_ptr++);
3116 F0 input_gate_output = gemmlowp::logistic(input_gate_input);
3117 // Implementation of input modulation gate, using fixed-point tanh
3118 // function.
3119 F3 input_modulation_gate_input =
3120 F3::FromRaw(*input_modulation_gate_input_ptr++);
3121 F0 input_modulation_gate_output =
3122 gemmlowp::tanh(input_modulation_gate_input);
3123 // Implementation of forget gate, using fixed-point logistic function.
3124 F3 forget_gate_input = F3::FromRaw(*forget_gate_input_ptr++);
3125 F0 forget_gate_output = gemmlowp::logistic(forget_gate_input);
3126 // Implementation of output gate, using fixed-point logistic function.
3127 F3 output_gate_input = F3::FromRaw(*output_gate_input_ptr++);
3128 F0 output_gate_output = gemmlowp::logistic(output_gate_input);
3129 // Implementation of internal multiplication nodes, still in fixed-point.
3130 F0 input_times_input_modulation =
3131 input_gate_output * input_modulation_gate_output;
3132 FS prev_state = FS::FromRaw(*prev_state_ptr++);
3133 FS prev_state_times_forget_state = forget_gate_output * prev_state;
3134 // Implementation of internal addition node, saturating.
3135 FS new_state = gemmlowp::SaturatingAdd(
3136 gemmlowp::Rescale<StateIntegerBits>(input_times_input_modulation),
3137 prev_state_times_forget_state);
3138 // Implementation of last internal Tanh node, still in fixed-point.
3139 // Since a Tanh fixed-point implementation is specialized for a given
3140 // number or integer bits, and each specialization can have a substantial
3141 // code size, and we already used above a Tanh on an input with 3 integer
3142 // bits, and per the table in the above function comment there is no
3143 // significant accuracy to be lost by clamping to [-8, +8] for a
3144 // 3-integer-bits representation, let us just do that. This helps people
3145 // porting this to targets where code footprint must be minimized.
3146 F3 new_state_f3 = gemmlowp::Rescale<3>(new_state);
3147 F0 output_activ_int16 = output_gate_output * gemmlowp::tanh(new_state_f3);
3148 // Store the new internal state back to memory, as 16-bit integers.
3149 // Note: here we store the original value with StateIntegerBits, not
3150 // the rescaled 3-integer-bits value fed to tanh.
3151 *output_state_data_ptr++ = new_state.raw();
3152 // Down-scale the output activations to 8-bit integers, saturating,
3153 // and store back to memory.
3154 int16 rescaled_output_activ =
3155 gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT(output_activ_int16.raw(), 8);
3156 int16 clamped_output_activ =
3157 std::max<int16>(-128, std::min<int16>(127, rescaled_output_activ));
3158 *output_activ_data_ptr++ = 128 + clamped_output_activ;
3159 }
3160 input_gate_input_ptr += 3 * output_depth;
3161 input_modulation_gate_input_ptr += 3 * output_depth;
3162 forget_gate_input_ptr += 3 * output_depth;
3163 output_gate_input_ptr += 3 * output_depth;
3164 }
3165}
3166
3167inline int NodeOffset(int b, int h, int w, int height, int width) {
3168 return (b * height + h) * width + w;
3169}
3170
3171inline void AveragePool(const PoolParams& params,
3172 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
3173 const float* input_data,
3174 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data) {
3175 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("AveragePool");
3176 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3177 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3178 const int batches = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
3179 const int input_height = input_shape.Dims(1);
3180 const int input_width = input_shape.Dims(2);
3181 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
3182 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
3183 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
3184 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
3185
3186 // TODO(benoitjacob) make this a proper reference impl without Eigen!
3187 const auto in_mat = MapAsMatrixWithLastDimAsRows(input_data, input_shape);
3188 auto out_mat = MapAsMatrixWithLastDimAsRows(output_data, output_shape);
3189 // TODO(benoitjacob) get rid of the dynamic memory allocation here!
3190 Eigen::VectorXf out_count(out_mat.cols());
3191 out_count.setZero();
3192 // Prefill the output to 0.
3193 out_mat.setZero();
3194 for (int b = 0; b < batches; ++b) {
3195 for (int h = 0; h < input_height; ++h) {
3196 for (int w = 0; w < input_width; ++w) {
3197 // (h_start, h_end) * (w_start, w_end) is the range that the input
3198 // vector projects to.
3199 int hpad = h + params.padding_values.height;
3200 int wpad = w + params.padding_values.width;
3201 int h_start = (hpad < params.filter_height)
3202 ? 0
3203 : (hpad - params.filter_height) / stride_height + 1;
3204 int h_end = std::min(hpad / stride_height + 1, output_height);
3205 int w_start = (wpad < params.filter_width)
3206 ? 0
3207 : (wpad - params.filter_width) / stride_width + 1;
3208 int w_end = std::min(wpad / stride_width + 1, output_width);
3209 // compute elementwise sum
3210 for (int ph = h_start; ph < h_end; ++ph) {
3211 for (int pw = w_start; pw < w_end; ++pw) {
3212 int out_offset = NodeOffset(b, ph, pw, output_height, output_width);
3213 out_mat.col(out_offset) +=
3214 in_mat.col(NodeOffset(b, h, w, input_height, input_width));
3215 out_count(out_offset)++;
3216 }
3217 }
3218 }
3219 }
3220 }
3221 // Divide the output by the actual number of elements being averaged over
3222 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(out_count.minCoeff(), 0);
3223 out_mat.array().rowwise() /= out_count.transpose().array();
3224
3225 const int flat_size = output_shape.FlatSize();
3226 for (int i = 0; i < flat_size; ++i) {
3227 output_data[i] = ActivationFunctionWithMinMax(output_data[i],
3228 params.float_activation_min,
3229 params.float_activation_max);
3230 }
3231}
3232
3233inline void AveragePool(const PoolParams& params,
3234 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
3235 const uint8* input_data,
3236 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, uint8* output_data) {
3237 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("AveragePool/8bit");
3238
3239 // Here, and in other pooling ops, in order to maintain locality of reference,
3240 // to minimize some recalculations, and to load into NEON vector registers, we
3241 // use an inner loop down the depth. Since depths can be large and hence we
3242 // would need arbitrarily large temporary storage, we divide the work up into
3243 // depth tranches just within the batch loop.
3244 static constexpr int kPoolingAccTrancheSize = 256;
3245
3246 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(params.quantized_activation_min,
3247 params.quantized_activation_max);
3248 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3249 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3250 const int batches = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
3251 const int depth = MatchingDim(input_shape, 3, output_shape, 3);
3252 const int input_height = input_shape.Dims(1);
3253 const int input_width = input_shape.Dims(2);
3254 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
3255 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
3256 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
3257 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
3258
3259 uint32 acc[kPoolingAccTrancheSize];
3260 for (int batch = 0; batch < batches; ++batch) {
3261 // We proceed through the depth in tranches (see comment above). The
3262 // depth_base is the depth at the beginning of the tranche. The
3263 // tranche_depth is the depth dimension of the tranche.
3264 for (int depth_base = 0; depth_base < depth;
3265 depth_base += kPoolingAccTrancheSize) {
3266 const int tranche_depth =
3267 std::min(depth - depth_base, kPoolingAccTrancheSize);
3268 for (int out_y = 0; out_y < output_height; ++out_y) {
3269 for (int out_x = 0; out_x < output_width; ++out_x) {
3270 const int in_x_origin =
3271 (out_x * stride_width) - params.padding_values.width;
3272 const int in_y_origin =
3273 (out_y * stride_height) - params.padding_values.height;
3274 const int filter_x_start = std::max(0, -in_x_origin);
3275 const int filter_x_end =
3276 std::min(params.filter_width, input_width - in_x_origin);
3277 const int filter_y_start = std::max(0, -in_y_origin);
3278 const int filter_y_end =
3279 std::min(params.filter_height, input_height - in_y_origin);
3280 const int filter_count =
3281 (filter_x_end - filter_x_start) * (filter_y_end - filter_y_start);
3282 memset(acc, 0, tranche_depth * sizeof(acc[0]));
3283 const uint8* input_ptr =
3284 input_data + depth_base +
3285 depth * (in_x_origin +
3286 input_width * (in_y_origin + input_height * batch));
3287 for (int fy = filter_y_start; fy < filter_y_end; fy++) {
3288 const uint8* input_row_ptr =
3289 input_ptr + depth * (fy * input_width + filter_x_start);
3290 for (int fx = filter_x_start; fx < filter_x_end; fx++) {
3291 const uint8* input_channel_ptr = input_row_ptr;
3292 int channel = 0;
3293#ifdef USE_NEON
3294 for (; channel <= tranche_depth - 16; channel += 16) {
3295 uint16x4_t acc_reg[4];
3296 uint8x16_t input_reg = vld1q_u8(input_channel_ptr);
3297 input_channel_ptr += 16;
3298 acc_reg[0] = vget_low_u16(vmovl_u8(vget_low_u8(input_reg)));
3299 acc_reg[1] = vget_high_u16(vmovl_u8(vget_low_u8(input_reg)));
3300 acc_reg[2] = vget_low_u16(vmovl_u8(vget_high_u8(input_reg)));
3301 acc_reg[3] = vget_high_u16(vmovl_u8(vget_high_u8(input_reg)));
3302 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3303 vst1q_u32(
3304 acc + channel + 4 * i,
3305 vaddw_u16(vld1q_u32(acc + channel + 4 * i), acc_reg[i]));
3306 }
3307 }
3308 for (; channel <= tranche_depth - 8; channel += 8) {
3309 uint16x4_t acc_reg[2];
3310 uint16x8_t input_reg = vmovl_u8(vld1_u8(input_channel_ptr));
3311 input_channel_ptr += 8;
3312 acc_reg[0] = vget_low_u16(input_reg);
3313 acc_reg[1] = vget_high_u16(input_reg);
3314 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
3315 vst1q_u32(
3316 acc + channel + 4 * i,
3317 vaddw_u16(vld1q_u32(acc + channel + 4 * i), acc_reg[i]));
3318 }
3319 }
3320#endif
3321 for (; channel < tranche_depth; ++channel) {
3322 acc[channel] += *input_channel_ptr++;
3323 }
3324 input_row_ptr += depth;
3325 }
3326 }
3327 uint8* output_ptr = output_data + Offset(output_shape, batch, out_y,
3328 out_x, depth_base);
3329 int channel = 0;
3330#ifdef USE_NEON
3331#define AVGPOOL_DIVIDING_BY(FILTER_COUNT) \
3332 if (filter_count == FILTER_COUNT) { \
3333 for (; channel <= tranche_depth - 8; channel += 8) { \
3334 uint16 buf[8]; \
3335 for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) { \
3336 buf[i] = (acc[channel + i] + FILTER_COUNT / 2) / FILTER_COUNT; \
3337 } \
3338 uint8x8_t buf8 = vqmovn_u16(vld1q_u16(buf)); \
3339 buf8 = vmin_u8(buf8, vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_max)); \
3340 buf8 = vmax_u8(buf8, vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_min)); \
3341 vst1_u8(output_ptr + channel, buf8); \
3342 } \
3343 }
3344 AVGPOOL_DIVIDING_BY(9)
3345 AVGPOOL_DIVIDING_BY(15)
3346#undef AVGPOOL_DIVIDING_BY
3347 for (; channel <= tranche_depth - 8; channel += 8) {
3348 uint16 buf[8];
3349 for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
3350 buf[i] = (acc[channel + i] + filter_count / 2) / filter_count;
3351 }
3352 uint8x8_t buf8 = vqmovn_u16(vld1q_u16(buf));
3353 buf8 = vmin_u8(buf8, vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_max));
3354 buf8 = vmax_u8(buf8, vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_min));
3355 vst1_u8(output_ptr + channel, buf8);
3356 }
3357#endif
3358 for (; channel < tranche_depth; ++channel) {
3359 uint16 a = (acc[channel] + filter_count / 2) / filter_count;
3360 a = std::max<uint16>(a, params.quantized_activation_min);
3361 a = std::min<uint16>(a, params.quantized_activation_max);
3362 output_ptr[channel] = static_cast<uint8>(a);
3363 }
3364 }
3365 }
3366 }
3367 }
3368}
3369
3370inline void MaxPool(const PoolParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
3371 const float* input_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
3372 float* output_data) {
3373 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("MaxPool");
3374 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3375 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3376 const int batches = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
3377 const int input_height = input_shape.Dims(1);
3378 const int input_width = input_shape.Dims(2);
3379 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
3380 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
3381 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
3382 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
3383
3384 const auto in_mat = MapAsMatrixWithLastDimAsRows(input_data, input_shape);
3385 auto out_mat = MapAsMatrixWithLastDimAsRows(output_data, output_shape);
3386 // Prefill the output to minimum representable float value
3387 out_mat.setConstant(std::numeric_limits<float>::lowest());
3388 for (int b = 0; b < batches; ++b) {
3389 for (int h = 0; h < input_height; ++h) {
3390 for (int w = 0; w < input_width; ++w) {
3391 // (h_start, h_end) * (w_start, w_end) is the range that the input
3392 // vector projects to.
3393 int hpad = h + params.padding_values.height;
3394 int wpad = w + params.padding_values.width;
3395 int h_start = (hpad < params.filter_height)
3396 ? 0
3397 : (hpad - params.filter_height) / stride_height + 1;
3398 int h_end = std::min(hpad / stride_height + 1, output_height);
3399 int w_start = (wpad < params.filter_width)
3400 ? 0
3401 : (wpad - params.filter_width) / stride_width + 1;
3402 int w_end = std::min(wpad / stride_width + 1, output_width);
3403 // compute elementwise sum
3404 for (int ph = h_start; ph < h_end; ++ph) {
3405 for (int pw = w_start; pw < w_end; ++pw) {
3406 int out_offset = NodeOffset(b, ph, pw, output_height, output_width);
3407 out_mat.col(out_offset) =
3408 out_mat.col(out_offset)
3409 .cwiseMax(in_mat.col(
3410 NodeOffset(b, h, w, input_height, input_width)));
3411 }
3412 }
3413 }
3414 }
3415 }
3416 const int flat_size = output_shape.FlatSize();
3417 for (int i = 0; i < flat_size; ++i) {
3418 output_data[i] = ActivationFunctionWithMinMax(output_data[i],
3419 params.float_activation_min,
3420 params.float_activation_max);
3421 }
3422}
3423
3424inline void MaxPool(const PoolParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
3425 const uint8* input_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
3426 uint8* output_data) {
3427 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("MaxPool/8bit");
3428
3429 // Here, and in other pooling ops, in order to maintain locality of reference,
3430 // to minimize some recalculations, and to load into NEON vector registers, we
3431 // use an inner loop down the depth. Since depths can be large and hence we
3432 // would need arbitrarily large temporary storage, we divide the work up into
3433 // depth tranches just within the batch loop.
3434 static constexpr int kPoolingAccTrancheSize = 256;
3435
3436 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(params.quantized_activation_min,
3437 params.quantized_activation_max);
3438 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3439 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3440 const int batches = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
3441 const int depth = MatchingDim(input_shape, 3, output_shape, 3);
3442 const int input_height = input_shape.Dims(1);
3443 const int input_width = input_shape.Dims(2);
3444 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
3445 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
3446 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
3447 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
3448
3449 uint8 acc[kPoolingAccTrancheSize];
3450 for (int batch = 0; batch < batches; ++batch) {
3451 // We proceed through the depth in tranches (see comment above). The
3452 // depth_base is the depth at the beginning of the tranche. The
3453 // tranche_depth is the depth dimension of the tranche.
3454 for (int depth_base = 0; depth_base < depth;
3455 depth_base += kPoolingAccTrancheSize) {
3456 const int tranche_depth =
3457 std::min(depth - depth_base, kPoolingAccTrancheSize);
3458 for (int out_y = 0; out_y < output_height; ++out_y) {
3459 for (int out_x = 0; out_x < output_width; ++out_x) {
3460 const int in_x_origin =
3461 (out_x * stride_width) - params.padding_values.width;
3462 const int in_y_origin =
3463 (out_y * stride_height) - params.padding_values.height;
3464 const int filter_x_start = std::max(0, -in_x_origin);
3465 const int filter_x_end =
3466 std::min(params.filter_width, input_width - in_x_origin);
3467 const int filter_y_start = std::max(0, -in_y_origin);
3468 const int filter_y_end =
3469 std::min(params.filter_height, input_height - in_y_origin);
3470 memset(acc, 0, tranche_depth * sizeof(acc[0]));
3471 const uint8* input_ptr =
3472 input_data + depth_base +
3473 depth * (in_x_origin +
3474 input_width * (in_y_origin + input_height * batch));
3475 for (int fy = filter_y_start; fy < filter_y_end; fy++) {
3476 const uint8* input_row_ptr =
3477 input_ptr + depth * (fy * input_width + filter_x_start);
3478 for (int fx = filter_x_start; fx < filter_x_end; fx++) {
3479 const uint8* input_channel_ptr = input_row_ptr;
3480 int channel = 0;
3481#ifdef USE_NEON
3482 for (; channel <= tranche_depth - 16; channel += 16) {
3483 uint8x16_t acc_reg = vld1q_u8(acc + channel);
3484 uint8x16_t input_reg = vld1q_u8(input_channel_ptr);
3485 input_channel_ptr += 16;
3486 acc_reg = vmaxq_u8(acc_reg, input_reg);
3487 vst1q_u8(acc + channel, acc_reg);
3488 }
3489
3490 for (; channel <= tranche_depth - 8; channel += 8) {
3491 uint8x8_t acc_reg = vld1_u8(acc + channel);
3492 uint8x8_t input_reg = vld1_u8(input_channel_ptr);
3493 input_channel_ptr += 8;
3494 acc_reg = vmax_u8(acc_reg, input_reg);
3495 vst1_u8(acc + channel, acc_reg);
3496 }
3497#endif
3498 for (; channel < tranche_depth; ++channel) {
3499 acc[channel] = std::max(acc[channel], *input_channel_ptr++);
3500 }
3501 input_row_ptr += depth;
3502 }
3503 }
3504 uint8* output_ptr = output_data + Offset(output_shape, batch, out_y,
3505 out_x, depth_base);
3506 int channel = 0;
3507#ifdef USE_NEON
3508 for (; channel <= tranche_depth - 16; channel += 16) {
3509 uint8x16_t a = vld1q_u8(acc + channel);
3510 a = vminq_u8(a, vdupq_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_max));
3511 a = vmaxq_u8(a, vdupq_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_min));
3512 vst1q_u8(output_ptr + channel, a);
3513 }
3514 for (; channel <= tranche_depth - 8; channel += 8) {
3515 uint8x8_t a = vld1_u8(acc + channel);
3516 a = vmin_u8(a, vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_max));
3517 a = vmax_u8(a, vdup_n_u8(params.quantized_activation_min));
3518 vst1_u8(output_ptr + channel, a);
3519 }
3520#endif
3521 for (; channel < tranche_depth; ++channel) {
3522 uint8 a = acc[channel];
3523 a = std::max<uint8>(a, params.quantized_activation_min);
3524 a = std::min<uint8>(a, params.quantized_activation_max);
3525 output_ptr[channel] = static_cast<uint8>(a);
3526 }
3527 }
3528 }
3529 }
3530 }
3531}
3532
3533inline void L2Pool(const PoolParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
3534 const float* input_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
3535 float* output_data) {
3536 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("L2Pool");
3537 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3538 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
3539 const int batches = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
3540 const int input_height = input_shape.Dims(1);
3541 const int input_width = input_shape.Dims(2);
3542 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
3543 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
3544 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
3545 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
3546 // Actually carry out L2 Pool. Code is written in forward mode: we go through
3547 // the input values once, and write to all the pooled regions that it maps to.
3548 const auto in_mat = MapAsMatrixWithLastDimAsRows(input_data, input_shape);
3549 auto out_mat = MapAsMatrixWithLastDimAsRows(output_data, output_shape);
3550 Eigen::VectorXf in_square(in_mat.rows());
3551 Eigen::VectorXf out_count(out_mat.cols());
3552 out_count.setZero();
3553 // Prefill the output to 0.
3554 out_mat.setZero();
3555 for (int b = 0; b < batches; ++b) {
3556 for (int h = 0; h < input_height; ++h) {
3557 for (int w = 0; w < input_width; ++w) {
3558 // (h_start, h_end) * (w_start, w_end) is the range that the input
3559 // vector projects to.
3560 const int hpad = h + params.padding_values.height;
3561 const int wpad = w + params.padding_values.width;
3562 const int h_start =
3563 (hpad < params.filter_height)
3564 ? 0
3565 : (hpad - params.filter_height) / stride_height + 1;
3566 const int h_end = std::min(hpad / stride_height + 1, output_height);
3567 const int w_start =
3568 (wpad < params.filter_width)
3569 ? 0
3570 : (wpad - params.filter_width) / stride_width + 1;
3571 const int w_end = std::min(wpad / stride_width + 1, output_width);
3572 // pre-compute square
3573 const int in_offset = w + input_width * (h + input_height * b);
3574 in_square =
3575 in_mat.col(in_offset).array() * in_mat.col(in_offset).array();
3576 // compute elementwise sum of squares
3577 for (int ph = h_start; ph < h_end; ++ph) {
3578 for (int pw = w_start; pw < w_end; ++pw) {
3579 const int out_offset = pw + output_width * (ph + output_height * b);
3580 out_mat.col(out_offset) += in_square;
3581 out_count(out_offset)++;
3582 }
3583 }
3584 }
3585 }
3586 }
3587
3588 out_count = out_count.array().inverse();
3589 out_mat =
3590 (out_mat.array().rowwise() * out_count.transpose().array()).cwiseSqrt();
3591
3592 const int flat_size = output_shape.FlatSize();
3593 for (int i = 0; i < flat_size; ++i) {
3594 output_data[i] = ActivationFunctionWithMinMax(output_data[i],
3595 params.float_activation_min,
3596 params.float_activation_max);
3597 }
3598}
3599
3600inline void LocalResponseNormalization(
3601 const tflite::LocalResponseNormalizationParams& op_params,
3602 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const float* input_data,
3603 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data) {
3604 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("LocalResponseNormalization");
3605 MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
3606
3607 const auto data_in = MapAsMatrixWithLastDimAsRows(input_data, input_shape);
3608 auto data_out = MapAsMatrixWithLastDimAsRows(output_data, output_shape);
3609
3610 // Carry out local response normalization, vector by vector.
3611 // Since the data are stored column major, making row-wise operation
3612 // probably not memory efficient anyway, we do an explicit for loop over
3613 // the columns.
3614 const int double_range = op_params.range * 2;
3615 Eigen::VectorXf padded_square(data_in.rows() + double_range);
3616 padded_square.setZero();
3617 const float bias = op_params.bias;
3618 for (int r = 0; r < data_in.cols(); ++r) {
3619 // Do local response normalization for data_in(:, r)
3620 // first, compute the square and store them in buffer for repeated use
3621 padded_square.block(op_params.range, 0, data_in.rows(), 1) =
3622 data_in.col(r).cwiseProduct(data_in.col(r)) * op_params.alpha;
3623 // Then, compute the scale and writes them to data_out
3624 float accumulated_scale = 0;
3625 for (int i = 0; i < double_range; ++i) {
3626 accumulated_scale += padded_square(i);
3627 }
3628 for (int i = 0; i < data_in.rows(); ++i) {
3629 accumulated_scale += padded_square(i + double_range);
3630 data_out(i, r) = bias + accumulated_scale;
3631 accumulated_scale -= padded_square(i);
3632 }
3633 }
3634
3635 // In a few cases, the pow computation could benefit from speedups.
3636 if (op_params.beta == 1) {
3637 data_out.array() = data_in.array() * data_out.array().inverse();
3638 } else if (op_params.beta == 0.5f) {
3639 data_out.array() = data_in.array() * data_out.array().sqrt().inverse();
3640 } else {
3641 data_out.array() = data_in.array() * data_out.array().pow(-op_params.beta);
3642 }
3643}
3644
3645inline void SoftmaxImpl(const SoftmaxParams& params,
3646 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
3647 const float* input_data,
3648 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data,
3649 int start_batch, int end_batch) {
3650 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Softmax/Impl");
3651 MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
3652
3653 const int logit_size = input_shape.Dims(input_shape.DimensionsCount() - 1);
3654 const MatrixMap<const float> in_mat(input_data + logit_size * start_batch,
3655 logit_size, end_batch - start_batch);
3656 MatrixMap<float> out_mat(output_data + logit_size * start_batch, logit_size,
3657 end_batch - start_batch);
3658 // Compute the exponential first, removing the max coefficient for numerical
3659 // stability.
3660 out_mat =
3661 (in_mat.rowwise() - in_mat.colwise().maxCoeff()).array() * params.beta;
3662 // We are separating out the exp function so that exp can be vectorized.
3663 out_mat = out_mat.array().exp();
3664 // Normalize to get the activations.
3665 Eigen::Array<float, 1, Eigen::Dynamic> scale =
3666 out_mat.array().colwise().sum().inverse();
3667 out_mat.array().rowwise() *= scale;
3668}
3669
3670struct SoftmaxWorkerTask : cpu_backend_threadpool::Task {
3671 SoftmaxWorkerTask(const SoftmaxParams& params,
3672 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const float* input_data,
3673 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data,
3674 int start_batch, int end_batch)
3675 : params(params),
3676 input_shape(input_shape),
3677 input_data(input_data),
3678 output_shape(output_shape),
3679 output_data(output_data),
3680 start_batch(start_batch),
3681 end_batch(end_batch) {}
3682 void Run() override {
3683 SoftmaxImpl(params, input_shape, input_data, output_shape, output_data,
3684 start_batch, end_batch);
3685 }
3686
3687 private:
3688 const tflite::SoftmaxParams& params;
3689 const RuntimeShape& input_shape;
3690 const float* input_data;
3691 const RuntimeShape& output_shape;
3692 float* output_data;
3693 int start_batch;
3694 int end_batch;
3695};
3696
3697inline void Softmax(const SoftmaxParams& params,
