3698 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const float* input_data,
3699 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data,
3700 CpuBackendContext* cpu_backend_context = nullptr) {
3701 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Softmax");
3702
3703 // We picture softmax input as a 2-D matrix while the last dim is the logit
3704 // dim, and the rest dims will be the batch dim for the 2-D matrix.
3705 const int batch_size =
3706 FlatSizeSkipDim(input_shape, input_shape.DimensionsCount() - 1);
3707 constexpr int kMinBatchPerThread = 8;
3708 int thread_count = batch_size / kMinBatchPerThread;
3709 thread_count = thread_count > 0 ? thread_count : 1;
3710 const int capped_thread_count =
3711 cpu_backend_context == nullptr
3712 ? 1
3713 : std::min(thread_count, cpu_backend_context->max_num_threads());
3714 if (capped_thread_count == 1) {
3715 SoftmaxImpl(params, input_shape, input_data, output_shape, output_data, 0,
3716 batch_size);
3717 } else {
3718 std::vector<SoftmaxWorkerTask> tasks;
3719 // TODO(b/131746020) don't create new heap allocations every time.
3720 // At least we make it a single heap allocation by using reserve().
3721 tasks.reserve(capped_thread_count);
3722 int batch_start = 0;
3723 for (int i = 0; i < capped_thread_count; ++i) {
3724 // Try to distribute the tasks as even as possible.
3725 int batch_end =
3726 batch_start + (batch_size - batch_start) / (capped_thread_count - i);
3727 tasks.emplace_back(params, input_shape, input_data, output_shape,
3728 output_data, batch_start, batch_end);
3729 batch_start = batch_end;
3730 }
3731 cpu_backend_threadpool::Execute(tasks.size(), tasks.data(),
3732 cpu_backend_context);
3733 }
3734}
3735
3736template <typename T>
3737inline int32_t QuantizeSoftmaxOutput(float prob_rescaled, int32_t zero_point) {
3738 const int32_t prob_rnd = static_cast<int32_t>(std::round(prob_rescaled));
3739 return prob_rnd + zero_point;
3740}
3741
3742#if !__aarch64__
3743// With ARM64, rounding is faster than add + truncation.
3744template <>
3745inline int32_t QuantizeSoftmaxOutput<uint8_t>(float prob_rescaled,
3746 int32_t zero_point) {
3747 return static_cast<int32_t>(prob_rescaled + 0.5f);
3748}
3749#endif
3750
3751inline void PopulateSoftmaxLookupTable(SoftmaxParams* data, float input_scale,
3752 float beta) {
3753 const float scale = -input_scale * beta;
3754 const int32_t max_uint8 = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
3755 for (int32_t val = 0; val <= max_uint8; ++val) {
3756 data->table[max_uint8 - val] = expf(scale * val);
3757 }
3758}
3759
3760template <typename In, typename Out>
3761inline void Softmax(const SoftmaxParams& params,
3762 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const In* input_data,
3763 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, Out* output_data) {
3764 const int trailing_dim = input_shape.DimensionsCount() - 1;
3765 const int excluding_last_dim =
3766 MatchingFlatSizeSkipDim(input_shape, trailing_dim, output_shape);
3767 const int last_dim =
3768 MatchingDim(input_shape, trailing_dim, output_shape, trailing_dim);
3769
3770 const int32_t clamp_max = std::numeric_limits<Out>::max();
3771 const int32_t clamp_min = std::numeric_limits<Out>::min();
3772 for (int i = 0; i < excluding_last_dim; ++i) {
3773 int32_t max_val = std::numeric_limits<In>::min();
3774 // Find max quantized value.
3775 for (int j = 0; j < last_dim; ++j) {
3776 max_val = std::max(max_val, static_cast<int32_t>(input_data[j]));
3777 }
3778
3779 float sum_exp = 0.0f;
3780 const int32_t max_uint8 = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
3781 const float* table_offset = &params.table[max_uint8 - max_val];
3782 // Calculate normalizer sum(exp(x)).
3783 for (int j = 0; j < last_dim; ++j) {
3784 sum_exp += table_offset[input_data[j]];
3785 }
3786
3787 const float inv_sum_exp = 1.0f / (sum_exp * params.scale);
3788 // Normalize and quantize probabilities.
3789 for (int j = 0; j < last_dim; ++j) {
3790 const float prob_rescaled = table_offset[input_data[j]] * inv_sum_exp;
3791 const int32_t prob_quantized =
3792 QuantizeSoftmaxOutput<Out>(prob_rescaled, params.zero_point);
3793 output_data[j] = static_cast<Out>(
3794 std::max(std::min(clamp_max, prob_quantized), clamp_min));
3795 }
3796 input_data += last_dim;
3797 output_data += last_dim;
3798 }
3799}
3800
3801// Here's the softmax LUT optimization strategy:
3802// For softmax, we can do some mathmetically equivalent transformation:
3803//
3804// softmax(x) = e^x / sum(e^x, 0...n) ===> equals to
3805// softmax(x) = e^(x - CONST) / sum(e^(x - CONST), 0...n)
3806//
3807// For quantization, `x` in our case is (input_q - input_zp) * input_s
3808// For uint8 case (int8 can be handled similarly), the range is [0, 255]
3809//
3810// so if we let
3811// CONST = (255 - input_zp) * input_s
3812// then we will have:
3813// softmax(x) = e^((input_q - 255) * input_s) --------- (1)
3814// /
3815// sum(e^(input_q - 255) * input_s, 0...n) -------- (2)
3816//
3817// the good thing about (1) is it's within the range of (0, 1), so we can
3818// approximate its result with uint16.
3819// (1) = uint8_out * 1 / 2^16.
3820//
3821// so (1) is lookup_uint8_table(input_zp) * 1 / 2^16.
3822// then (2) is essentially the following:
3823// sum(lookup_uint8_table(input_zp), 0...n) / 2^16.
3824//
3825// since (output_q - output_zp) * output_s = softmax(x)
3826// output_q = lookup_uint8_table(input_zp)
3827// /
3828// (sum(lookup_uint8_table(input_zp), 0...n) * output_s)
3829// +
3830// output_zp
3831//
3832// We can actually further improve the performance by using uint8 instead of
3833// uint16. But that we may lose some accuracy, so we need to pay attention
3834// to that.
3835inline void PopulateSoftmaxUInt8LookupTable(SoftmaxParams* data,
3836 float input_scale, float beta) {
3837 const float scale = input_scale * beta;
3838 const int32_t max_uint8 = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
3839 const int32_t max_uint16 = std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max();
3840
3841 for (int32_t val = 0; val <= max_uint8; ++val) {
3842 float input_to_exp = scale * (val - max_uint8);
3843 int32_t temp = static_cast<int>(expf(input_to_exp) * max_uint16 + 0.5);
3844 temp = std::min(max_uint16, temp);
3845 uint8_t part1 = temp >> 8;
3846 uint8_t part2 = temp & 0xff;
3847 data->uint8_table1[val] = static_cast<uint8_t>(part1);
3848 data->uint8_table2[val] = static_cast<uint8_t>(part2);
3849 }
3850}
3851
3852inline int FindMaxValue(int size, const uint8_t* input_data, uint8_t offset) {
3853 int32_t max_val = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min();
3854 int j = 0;
3855#ifdef TFLITE_SOFTMAX_USE_UINT16_LUT
3856 uint8x16_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_u8(max_val);
3857 uint8x16_t offset_dup = vdupq_n_u8(offset);
3858 for (; j <= size - 16; j += 16) {
3859 uint8x16_t input_value = vld1q_u8(input_data + j);
3860 input_value = veorq_u8(input_value, offset_dup);
3861 max_val_dup = vmaxq_u8(input_value, max_val_dup);
3862 }
3863 max_val = std::max(max_val, static_cast<int32>(vmaxvq_u8(max_val_dup)));
3864#endif
3865
3866 for (; j < size; ++j) {
3867 max_val = std::max(max_val, static_cast<int32_t>(input_data[j] ^ offset));
3868 }
3869 return max_val;
3870}
3871
3872#ifdef USE_NEON
3873// Value_to_store layout:
3874// [high_high, high_low, low_high, low_low].
3875inline void StoreValue(int32x4x4_t value_to_store, int8_t* output) {
3876 const int16x8_t result_1 = vcombine_s16(vqmovn_s32(value_to_store.val[1]),
3877 vqmovn_s32(value_to_store.val[0]));
3878 const int16x8_t result_2 = vcombine_s16(vqmovn_s32(value_to_store.val[3]),
3879 vqmovn_s32(value_to_store.val[2]));
3880 const int8x16_t result =
3881 vcombine_s8(vqmovn_s16(result_2), vqmovn_s16(result_1));
3882 vst1q_s8(output, result);
3883}
3884
3885// Value_to_store layout:
3886// [high_high, high_low, low_high, low_low].
3887inline void StoreValue(int32x4x4_t value_to_store, uint8_t* output) {
3888 const uint16x8_t result_1 =
3889 vcombine_u16(vqmovn_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_s32(value_to_store.val[1])),
3890 vqmovn_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_s32(value_to_store.val[0])));
3891 const uint16x8_t result_2 =
3892 vcombine_u16(vqmovn_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_s32(value_to_store.val[3])),
3893 vqmovn_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_s32(value_to_store.val[2])));
3894 const uint8x16_t result =
3895 vcombine_u8(vqmovn_u16(result_2), vqmovn_u16(result_1));
3896 vst1q_u8(output, result);
3897}
3898
3899#endif
3900
3901template <typename In, typename Out>
3902inline void SoftmaxInt8LUT(const SoftmaxParams& params,
3903 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
3904 const In* input_data,
3905 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, Out* output_data) {
3906 const int trailing_dim = input_shape.DimensionsCount() - 1;
3907 const int excluding_last_dim =
3908 MatchingFlatSizeSkipDim(input_shape, trailing_dim, output_shape);
3909 const int last_dim =
3910 MatchingDim(input_shape, trailing_dim, output_shape, trailing_dim);
3911
3912 const int32_t clamp_max = std::numeric_limits<Out>::max();
3913 const int32_t clamp_min = std::numeric_limits<Out>::min();
3914
3915 // Offset is used to interpret the input data "correctly".
3916 // If the input is uint8, the data will be unchanged.
3917 // If the input is int8, since it will be reinterpret as uint8.
3918 // e.g.,
3919 // int8 127 will be applied "offset" to become 255 in uint8.
3920 uint8_t offset = 0;
3921 if (std::is_same<In, int8>::value) {
3922 offset = 0x80;
3923 }
3924
3925 const uint8_t* input_data_uint = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(input_data);
3926
3927#ifdef TFLITE_SOFTMAX_USE_UINT16_LUT
3928 // This code uses ARM64-only instructions.
3929 // TODO(b/143709993): Port to ARMv7
3930
3931 // Load the tables into registers. (4*4 128-bit registers)
3932 uint8x16x4_t table1[4];
3933 table1[0] = vld1q_u8_x4(params.uint8_table1 + 16 * 4 * 0);
3934 table1[1] = vld1q_u8_x4(params.uint8_table1 + 16 * 4 * 1);
3935 table1[2] = vld1q_u8_x4(params.uint8_table1 + 16 * 4 * 2);
3936 table1[3] = vld1q_u8_x4(params.uint8_table1 + 16 * 4 * 3);
3937
3938 uint8x16x4_t table2[4];
3939 table2[0] = vld1q_u8_x4(params.uint8_table2 + 16 * 4 * 0);
3940 table2[1] = vld1q_u8_x4(params.uint8_table2 + 16 * 4 * 1);
3941 table2[2] = vld1q_u8_x4(params.uint8_table2 + 16 * 4 * 2);
3942 table2[3] = vld1q_u8_x4(params.uint8_table2 + 16 * 4 * 3);
3943#endif
3944
3945 for (int i = 0; i < excluding_last_dim; ++i) {
3946 // Find max quantized value.
3947 int32_t max_val = FindMaxValue(last_dim, input_data_uint, offset);
3948
3949 int32 sum_exp = 0;
3950 const int32_t max_uint8 = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
3951 const uint8_t table_offset = max_uint8 - max_val;
3952
3953 // Calculate normalizer sum(exp(x)).
3954 int sum_j = 0;
3955#ifdef TFLITE_SOFTMAX_USE_UINT16_LUT
3956 uint8x16_t table_offset_dup = vdupq_n_u8(table_offset);
3957 uint8x16_t offset_dup = vdupq_n_u8(offset);
3958 uint32x4_t sum_4 = vdupq_n_u32(0);
3959 const int multiplier_shift = 8;
3960 for (; sum_j <= last_dim - 16; sum_j += 16) {
3961 uint8x16_t input_value = vld1q_u8(input_data_uint + sum_j);
3962 input_value = veorq_u8(input_value, offset_dup);
3963 input_value = vaddq_u8(input_value, table_offset_dup);
3964
3965 const uint8x16_t output1 = aarch64_lookup_vector(table1, input_value);
3966 const uint8x16_t output2 = aarch64_lookup_vector(table2, input_value);
3967
3968 uint16x8_t exp_value1 =
3969 vshll_n_u8(vget_high_u8(output1), multiplier_shift);
3970 uint16x8_t exp_value2 =
3971 vshll_n_u8(vget_low_u8(output1), multiplier_shift);
3972
3973 exp_value1 = vaddw_u8(exp_value1, vget_high_u8(output2));
3974 exp_value2 = vaddw_u8(exp_value2, vget_low_u8(output2));
3975
3976 sum_4 = vpadalq_u16(sum_4, exp_value1);
3977 sum_4 = vpadalq_u16(sum_4, exp_value2);
3978 }
3979 int temp = vgetq_lane_u32(sum_4, 0) + vgetq_lane_u32(sum_4, 1) +
3980 vgetq_lane_u32(sum_4, 2) + vgetq_lane_u32(sum_4, 3);
3981 sum_exp += temp;
3982
3983#endif
3984 for (; sum_j < last_dim; ++sum_j) {
3985 const uint8_t index = (input_data_uint[sum_j] ^ offset) + table_offset;
3986
3987 uint8_t part1 = params.uint8_table1[index];
3988 uint8_t part2 = params.uint8_table2[index];
3989 sum_exp += ((part1 << 8) + part2);
3990 }
3991
3992 const float inv_sum_exp = 1.0f / (sum_exp * params.scale);
3993
3994 int32 multiplier, shift;
3995 QuantizeMultiplier(inv_sum_exp, &multiplier, &shift);
3996
3997 // Normalize and quantize probabilities.
3998 int j = 0;
3999#ifdef TFLITE_SOFTMAX_USE_UINT16_LUT
4000 const int32x4_t output_zp_dup = vdupq_n_s32(params.zero_point);
4001 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(clamp_max);
4002 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(clamp_min);
4003
4004 for (; j <= last_dim - 16; j += 16) {
4005 uint8x16_t input_value = vld1q_u8(input_data_uint + j);
4006 input_value = veorq_u8(input_value, offset_dup);
4007 input_value = vaddq_u8(input_value, table_offset_dup);
4008
4009 const uint8x16_t output1 = aarch64_lookup_vector(table1, input_value);
4010 const uint8x16_t output2 = aarch64_lookup_vector(table2, input_value);
4011
4012 uint16x8_t exp_value1 =
4013 vshll_n_u8(vget_high_u8(output1), multiplier_shift);
4014 uint16x8_t exp_value2 =
4015 vshll_n_u8(vget_low_u8(output1), multiplier_shift);
4016
4017 exp_value1 = vaddw_u8(exp_value1, vget_high_u8(output2));
4018 exp_value2 = vaddw_u8(exp_value2, vget_low_u8(output2));
4019
4020 int32x4x4_t output_value;
4021 output_value.val[0] =
4022 vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_high_u16(exp_value1)));
4023 output_value.val[1] =
4024 vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_low_u16(exp_value1)));
4025 output_value.val[2] =
4026 vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_high_u16(exp_value2)));
4027 output_value.val[3] =
4028 vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_low_u16(exp_value2)));
4029
4030 int32x4x4_t temp_val =
4031 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier4Rows(output_value, multiplier, shift);
4032
4033 temp_val.val[0] = vaddq_s32(temp_val.val[0], output_zp_dup);
4034 temp_val.val[1] = vaddq_s32(temp_val.val[1], output_zp_dup);
4035 temp_val.val[2] = vaddq_s32(temp_val.val[2], output_zp_dup);
4036 temp_val.val[3] = vaddq_s32(temp_val.val[3], output_zp_dup);
4037
4038 temp_val.val[0] =
4039 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(temp_val.val[0], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
4040 temp_val.val[1] =
4041 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(temp_val.val[1], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
4042 temp_val.val[2] =
4043 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(temp_val.val[2], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
4044 temp_val.val[3] =
4045 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(temp_val.val[3], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
4046
4047 StoreValue(temp_val, output_data + j);
4048 }
4049#endif
4050 for (; j < last_dim; ++j) {
4051 const uint8_t index = (input_data_uint[j] ^ offset) + table_offset;
4052 const uint8_t part1 = params.uint8_table1[index];
4053 const uint8_t part2 = params.uint8_table2[index];
4054 const int32_t exp_value = (part1 << 8) + part2;
4055 const int32_t output_value =
4056 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(exp_value, multiplier, shift);
4057
4058 output_data[j] = static_cast<Out>(std::max(
4059 std::min(clamp_max, output_value + params.zero_point), clamp_min));
4060 }
4061 input_data_uint += last_dim;
4062 output_data += last_dim;
4063 }
4064}
4065
4066inline void LogSoftmax(const SoftmaxParams& params,
4067 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const float* input_data,
4068 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data) {
4069 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("LogSoftmax");
4070 const int trailing_dim = input_shape.DimensionsCount() - 1;
4071 const int outer_size =
4072 MatchingFlatSizeSkipDim(input_shape, trailing_dim, output_shape);
4073 const int depth =
4074 MatchingDim(input_shape, trailing_dim, output_shape, trailing_dim);
4075
4076 for (int i = 0; i < outer_size; ++i) {
4077 VectorMap<const float> block_input(input_data + i * depth, depth, 1);
4078 VectorMap<float> block_output(output_data + i * depth, depth, 1);
4079 // Find max element value which we'll use to ensure numerical stability
4080 // taking advantage of the following equality:
4081 // log(exp(x[i])/sum(exp(x[i]))) == log(exp(x[i]+C)/sum(exp(x[i]+C)))
4082 const float max = block_input.maxCoeff();
4083 const float log_sum = std::log((block_input.array() - max).exp().sum());
4084 block_output = block_input.array() - max - log_sum;
4085 }
4086}
4087
4088// Backwards compatibility. Less optimized than below version.
4089inline void LogSoftmax(const SoftmaxParams& params,
4090 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const uint8* input_data,
4091 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, uint8* output_data) {
4092 reference_ops::LogSoftmax(params, input_shape, input_data, output_shape,
4093 output_data);
4094}
4095
4096// Compute LogSoftmax as (x - x_max) - ln(sum(e^(x_i - x_max)...)
4097// as done in tf.nn.log_softmax to prevent underflow and overflow.
4098// This is in contrast to just log(softmax(x))
4099//
4100// To handle quantization, first dequantize the inputs (from doing
4101// e^(input scale * val) where we ignore the zero point since it cancels
4102// out during subtraction due to the ln) and do a rescale at the end to int8.
4103//
4104// Notably this makes use of float and is intended as the optimized
4105// form for quantized execution on CPU. For a fully integer version,
4106// see the reference op.
4107//
4108// TODO(tflite): notes for optimization:
4109// 1) See if e^ is also bottleneck in the reference fully-integer
4110// version and apply lookup there and compare.
4111template <typename T>
4112inline void LogSoftmax(const SoftmaxParams& params, float input_scale,
4113 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
4114 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
4115 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("LogSoftmax");
4116 const int trailing_dim = input_shape.DimensionsCount() - 1;
4117 const int excluding_last_dim =
4118 MatchingFlatSizeSkipDim(input_shape, trailing_dim, output_shape);
4119 const int last_dim =
4120 MatchingDim(input_shape, trailing_dim, output_shape, trailing_dim);
4121
4122 const int32_t clamp_max = std::numeric_limits<T>::max();
4123 const int32_t clamp_min = std::numeric_limits<T>::min();
4124
4125 int32_t zero_point_offset = 0;
4126 if (std::is_same<T, int8_t>::value) {
4127 zero_point_offset = 128;
4128 }
4129 for (int i = 0; i < excluding_last_dim; ++i) {
4130 T max_val = std::numeric_limits<T>::min();
4131 // Find max quantized value.
4132 for (int j = 0; j < last_dim; ++j) {
4133 max_val = std::max(max_val, input_data[j]);
4134 }
4135
4136 float sum_exp = 0.0f;
4137 const int32_t max_q8 = std::numeric_limits<T>::max();
4138 // Offset into table to compute exp(scale*(x - xmax)) instead of
4139 // exp(scale*(x)) to prevent overflow.
4140 const float* table_offset = &params.table[max_q8 - max_val];
4141 // Calculate sum(exp(scale*(x - x_max))).
4142 for (int j = 0; j < last_dim; ++j) {
4143 sum_exp += table_offset[input_data[j]];
4144 }
4145 const float log_sum_exp = std::log(sum_exp);
4146
4147 // params.scale is the output scale.
4148 const float scale = input_scale / params.scale;
4149 const float precomputed =
4150 (input_scale * (max_val + zero_point_offset) + log_sum_exp) /
4151 params.scale;
4152 for (int j = 0; j < last_dim; ++j) {
4153 // Equivalent to (input_scale * (input_data[j] - max_val) - log_sum_exp) /
4154 // output_scale.
4155 const float log_prob = scale * input_data[j] - precomputed;
4156
4157 // TODO(tflite): look into better solution.
4158 // Use std::rint over std::round (which is used in
4159 // FakeQuant) since it's multiple times faster on tested arm32.
4160 const int32_t prob_quantized = std::rint(log_prob) + params.zero_point;
4161 output_data[j] = static_cast<T>(
4162 std::max(std::min(clamp_max, prob_quantized), clamp_min));
4163 }
4164 input_data += last_dim;
4165 output_data += last_dim;
4166 }
4167}
4168
4169inline void Logistic(const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const float* input_data,
4170 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data) {
4171 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Logistic");
4172 auto input_map = MapAsVector(input_data, input_shape);
4173 auto output_map = MapAsVector(output_data, output_shape);
4174 output_map.array() =
4175 input_map.array().unaryExpr(Eigen::internal::scalar_logistic_op<float>());
4176}
4177
4178// Convenience version that allows, for example, generated-code calls to be
4179// uniform between data types.
4180inline void Logistic(const LogisticParams&, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
4181 const float* input_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4182 float* output_data) {
4183 // Drop params: not needed.
4184 Logistic(input_shape, input_data, output_shape, output_data);
4185}
4186
4187inline void Logistic(const LogisticParams& params,
4188 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const int16* input_data,
4189 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, int16* output_data) {
4190 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Logistic/Int16");
4191 const int flat_size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
4192
4193 for (int i = 0; i < flat_size; i++) {
4194 }
4195
4196 int c = 0;
4197 const int16* input_data_ptr = input_data;
4198 int16* output_data_ptr = output_data;
4199#ifdef GEMMLOWP_NEON
4200 {
4201 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
4202 // This is the return type of math functions such as tanh, logistic,
4203 // whose range is in [-1, 1].
4204 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 0>;
4205 // F3 uses 3 integer bits, range [-8, 8], the input range expected here.
4206 using F3 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 3>;
4207
4208 for (; c <= flat_size - 16; c += 16) {
4209 F3 input0 = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr));
4210 F3 input1 = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr + 8));
4211 F0 output0 = gemmlowp::logistic(input0);
4212 F0 output1 = gemmlowp::logistic(input1);
4213 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr, output0.raw());
4214 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr + 8, output1.raw());
4215
4216 input_data_ptr += 16;
4217 output_data_ptr += 16;
4218 }
4219 for (; c <= flat_size - 8; c += 8) {
4220 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr));
4221 F0 output = gemmlowp::logistic(input);
4222 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr, output.raw());
4223
4224 input_data_ptr += 8;
4225 output_data_ptr += 8;
4226 }
4227 }
4228#endif
4229#ifdef GEMMLOWP_SSE4
4230 {
4231 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
4232 // This is the return type of math functions such as tanh, logistic,
4233 // whose range is in [-1, 1].
4234 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<gemmlowp::int16x8_m128i, 0>;
4235 // F3 uses 3 integer bits, range [-8, 8], the input range expected here.
4236 using F3 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<gemmlowp::int16x8_m128i, 3>;
4237
4238 for (; c <= flat_size - 16; c += 16) {
4239 F3 input0 = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(
4240 _mm_loadu_si128(reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr))));
4241 F3 input1 = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(_mm_loadu_si128(
4242 reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr + 8))));
4243 F0 output0 = gemmlowp::logistic(input0);
4244 F0 output1 = gemmlowp::logistic(input1);
4245 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr),
4246 output0.raw().v);
4247 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr + 8),
4248 output1.raw().v);
4249 input_data_ptr += 16;
4250 output_data_ptr += 16;
4251 }
4252 for (; c <= flat_size - 8; c += 8) {
4253 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(
4254 _mm_loadu_si128(reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr))));
4255 F0 output = gemmlowp::logistic(input);
4256 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr),
4257 output.raw().v);
4258 input_data_ptr += 8;
4259 output_data_ptr += 8;
4260 }
4261 }
4262#endif
4263
4264 {
4265 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
4266 // This is the return type of math functions such as tanh, logistic,
4267 // whose range is in [-1, 1].
4268 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 0>;
4269 // F3 uses 3 integer bits, range [-8, 8], the input range expected here.
4270 using F3 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 3>;
4271
4272 for (; c < flat_size; ++c) {
4273 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(*input_data_ptr);
4274 F0 output = gemmlowp::logistic(input);
4275 *output_data_ptr = output.raw();
4276
4277 ++input_data_ptr;
4278 ++output_data_ptr;
4279 }
4280 }
4281}
4282
4283inline void Tanh(const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const float* input_data,
4284 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data) {
4285 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Tanh");
4286 auto input_map = MapAsVector(input_data, input_shape);
4287 auto output_map = MapAsVector(output_data, output_shape);
4288 output_map.array() = input_map.array().tanh();
4289}

4291// Convenience version that allows, for example, generated-code calls to be
4292// uniform between data types.
4293inline void Tanh(const TanhParams&, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
4294 const float* input_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4295 float* output_data) {
4296 // Drop params: not needed.
4297 Tanh(input_shape, input_data, output_shape, output_data);
4298}
4299
4300inline void Tanh(const TanhParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
4301 const int16* input_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4302 int16* output_data) {
4303 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Tanh/Int16");
4304 const int input_left_shift = params.input_left_shift;
4305 // Support for shifts is limited until we have a parameterized version of
4306 // SaturatingRoundingMultiplyByPOT().
4307 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(input_left_shift, 0);
4308 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(input_left_shift, 1);
4309
4310 const int flat_size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
4311
4312 int c = 0;
4313 const int16* input_data_ptr = input_data;
4314 int16* output_data_ptr = output_data;
4315#ifdef GEMMLOWP_NEON
4316 {
4317 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
4318 // This is the return type of math functions such as tanh, logistic,
4319 // whose range is in [-1, 1].
4320 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 0>;
4321 // F3 uses 3 integer bits, range [-8, 8], the input range expected here.
4322 using F3 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 3>;
4323
4324 if (input_left_shift == 0) {
4325 for (; c <= flat_size - 16; c += 16) {
4326 F3 input0 = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr));
4327 F3 input1 = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr + 8));
4328 F0 output0 = gemmlowp::tanh(input0);
4329 F0 output1 = gemmlowp::tanh(input1);
4330 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr, output0.raw());
4331 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr + 8, output1.raw());
4332
4333 input_data_ptr += 16;
4334 output_data_ptr += 16;
4335 }
4336 for (; c <= flat_size - 8; c += 8) {
4337 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr));
4338 F0 output = gemmlowp::tanh(input);
4339 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr, output.raw());
4340
4341 input_data_ptr += 8;
4342 output_data_ptr += 8;
4343 }
4344 } else {
4345 for (; c <= flat_size - 16; c += 16) {
4346 F3 input0 = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingMultiplyByPOT<1>(
4347 vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr)));
4348 F3 input1 = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingMultiplyByPOT<1>(
4349 vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr + 8)));
4350 F0 output0 = gemmlowp::tanh(input0);
4351 F0 output1 = gemmlowp::tanh(input1);
4352 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr, output0.raw());
4353 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr + 8, output1.raw());
4354
4355 input_data_ptr += 16;
4356 output_data_ptr += 16;
4357 }
4358 for (; c <= flat_size - 8; c += 8) {
4359 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingMultiplyByPOT<1>(
4360 vld1q_s16(input_data_ptr)));
4361 F0 output = gemmlowp::tanh(input);
4362 vst1q_s16(output_data_ptr, output.raw());
4363
4364 input_data_ptr += 8;
4365 output_data_ptr += 8;
4366 }
4367 }
4368 }
4369#endif
4370#ifdef GEMMLOWP_SSE4
4371 {
4372 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
4373 // This is the return type of math functions such as tanh, logistic,
4374 // whose range is in [-1, 1].
4375 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<gemmlowp::int16x8_m128i, 0>;
4376 // F3 uses 3 integer bits, range [-8, 8], the input range expected here.
4377 using F3 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<gemmlowp::int16x8_m128i, 3>;
4378
4379 if (input_left_shift == 0) {
4380 for (; c <= flat_size - 16; c += 16) {
4381 F3 input0 = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(
4382 _mm_loadu_si128(reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr))));
4383 F3 input1 = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(_mm_loadu_si128(
4384 reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr + 8))));
4385 F0 output0 = gemmlowp::tanh(input0);
4386 F0 output1 = gemmlowp::tanh(input1);
4387 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr),
4388 output0.raw().v);
4389 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr + 8),
4390 output1.raw().v);
4391
4392 input_data_ptr += 16;
4393 output_data_ptr += 16;
4394 }
4395 for (; c <= flat_size - 8; c += 8) {
4396 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(
4397 _mm_loadu_si128(reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr))));
4398 F0 output = gemmlowp::tanh(input);
4399 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr),
4400 output.raw().v);
4401 input_data_ptr += 8;
4402 output_data_ptr += 8;
4403 }
4404 } else {
4405 for (; c <= flat_size - 16; c += 16) {
4406 F3 input0 = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingMultiplyByPOT<1>(
4407 gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(_mm_loadu_si128(
4408 reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr)))));
4409 F3 input1 = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingMultiplyByPOT<1>(
4410 gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(_mm_loadu_si128(
4411 reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr + 8)))));
4412 F0 output0 = gemmlowp::tanh(input0);
4413 F0 output1 = gemmlowp::tanh(input1);
4414 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr),
4415 output0.raw().v);
4416 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr + 8),
4417 output1.raw().v);
4418
4419 input_data_ptr += 16;
4420 output_data_ptr += 16;
4421 }
4422 for (; c <= flat_size - 8; c += 8) {
4423 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingMultiplyByPOT<1>(
4424 gemmlowp::to_int16x8_m128i(_mm_loadu_si128(
4425 reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(input_data_ptr)))));
4426 F0 output = gemmlowp::tanh(input);
4427 _mm_storeu_si128(reinterpret_cast<__m128i*>(output_data_ptr),
4428 output.raw().v);
4429 input_data_ptr += 8;
4430 output_data_ptr += 8;
4431 }
4432 }
4433 }
4434#endif
4435
4436 {
4437 // F0 uses 0 integer bits, range [-1, 1].
4438 // This is the return type of math functions such as tanh, logistic,
4439 // whose range is in [-1, 1].
4440 using F0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 0>;
4441 // F3 uses 3 integer bits, range [-8, 8], the input range expected here.
4442 using F3 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<std::int16_t, 3>;
4443
4444 if (input_left_shift == 0) {
4445 for (; c < flat_size; ++c) {
4446 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(*input_data_ptr);
4447 F0 output = gemmlowp::tanh(input);
4448 *output_data_ptr = output.raw();
4449
4450 ++input_data_ptr;
4451 ++output_data_ptr;
4452 }
4453 } else {
4454 for (; c < flat_size; ++c) {
4455 F3 input = F3::FromRaw(
4456 gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingMultiplyByPOT<1>(*input_data_ptr));
4457 F0 output = gemmlowp::tanh(input);
4458 *output_data_ptr = output.raw();
4459
4460 ++input_data_ptr;
4461 ++output_data_ptr;
4462 }
4463 }
4464 }
4465}

4491
4492// Helper methods for BatchToSpaceND.
4493// `spatial_index_dim` specifies post-crop offset index in this spatial
4494// dimension, i.e. spatial offset introduced by flattening batch to spatial
4495// dimension minus the crop size at beginning. `block_shape_dim` is the block
4496// size in current dimension. `input_dim` and `output_dim` are input and output
4497// size of BatchToSpaceND operation in current dimension.
4498// Output start index is inclusive and end index is exclusive.
4499inline void GetIndexRange(int spatial_index_dim, int block_shape_dim,
4500 int input_dim, int output_dim, int* start_index,
4501 int* end_index) {
4502 // (*start_index) * block_shape_dim is effectively rounded up to the next
4503 // multiple of block_shape_dim by the integer division.
4504 *start_index =
4505 std::max(0, (-spatial_index_dim + block_shape_dim - 1) / block_shape_dim);
4506 // Similarly, (*end_index) * block_shape_dim is rounded up too (note that
4507 // end_index is exclusive).
4508 *end_index = std::min(
4509 input_dim,
4510 (output_dim - spatial_index_dim + block_shape_dim - 1) / block_shape_dim);
4511}
4512
4513template <typename T>
4514inline void BatchToSpaceND(
4515 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input1_shape, const T* input1_data,
4516 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input2_shape, const int32* block_shape_data,
4517 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input3_shape, const int32* crops_data,
4518 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape, T* output_data) {
4519 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("BatchToSpaceND");
4520
4521 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(unextended_input1_shape.DimensionsCount(), 3);
4522 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input1_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
4523 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(unextended_input1_shape.DimensionsCount(),
4524 unextended_output_shape.DimensionsCount());
4525
4526 // Extends the input/output shape from 3D to 4D if needed, NHC -> NH1C.
4527 auto extend_shape = [](const RuntimeShape& shape) {
4528 if (shape.DimensionsCount() == 4) {
4529 return shape;
4530 }
4531 RuntimeShape new_shape(4, 1);
4532 new_shape.SetDim(0, shape.Dims(0));
4533 new_shape.SetDim(1, shape.Dims(1));
4534 new_shape.SetDim(3, shape.Dims(2));
4535 return new_shape;
4536 };
4537 const RuntimeShape input1_shape = extend_shape(unextended_input1_shape);
4538 const RuntimeShape output_shape = extend_shape(unextended_output_shape);
4539
4540 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
4541 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
4542 const int output_batch_size = output_shape.Dims(0);
4543
4544 const int depth = input1_shape.Dims(3);
4545 const int input_width = input1_shape.Dims(2);
4546 const int input_height = input1_shape.Dims(1);
4547 const int input_batch_size = input1_shape.Dims(0);
4548
4549 const int block_shape_height = block_shape_data[0];
4550 const int block_shape_width =
4551 unextended_input1_shape.DimensionsCount() == 4 ? block_shape_data[1] : 1;
4552 const int crops_top = crops_data[0];
4553 const int crops_left =
4554 unextended_input1_shape.DimensionsCount() == 4 ? crops_data[2] : 0;
4555
4556 for (int in_batch = 0; in_batch < input_batch_size; ++in_batch) {
4557 const int out_batch = in_batch % output_batch_size;
4558 const int spatial_offset = in_batch / output_batch_size;
4559
4560 int in_h_start = 0;
4561 int in_h_end = 0;
4562 // GetIndexRange ensures start and end indices are in [0, output_height).
4563 GetIndexRange(spatial_offset / block_shape_width - crops_top,
4564 block_shape_height, input_height, output_height, &in_h_start,
4565 &in_h_end);
4566
4567 for (int in_h = in_h_start; in_h < in_h_end; ++in_h) {
4568 const int out_h = in_h * block_shape_height +
4569 spatial_offset / block_shape_width - crops_top;
4570 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(out_h, 0);
4571 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(out_h, output_height);
4572
4573 int in_w_start = 0;
4574 int in_w_end = 0;
4575 // GetIndexRange ensures start and end indices are in [0, output_width).
4576 GetIndexRange(spatial_offset % block_shape_width - crops_left,
4577 block_shape_width, input_width, output_width, &in_w_start,
4578 &in_w_end);
4579
4580 for (int in_w = in_w_start; in_w < in_w_end; ++in_w) {
4581 const int out_w = in_w * block_shape_width +
4582 spatial_offset % block_shape_width - crops_left;
4583 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(out_w, 0);
4584 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(out_w, output_width);
4585 T* out = output_data + Offset(output_shape, out_batch, out_h, out_w, 0);
4586 const T* in =
4587 input1_data + Offset(input1_shape, in_batch, in_h, in_w, 0);
4588 memcpy(out, in, depth * sizeof(T));
4589 }
4590 }
4591 }
4592}
4593
4594template <typename T>
4595void TypedMemset(void* ptr, T value, size_t num) {
4596 // Optimization for common cases where memset() will suffice.
4597 if (value == 0 || std::is_same<T, uint8_t>::value) {
4598 memset(ptr, value, num * sizeof(T));
4599 } else {
4600 // Default implementation for cases where memset() will not preserve the
4601 // bytes, e.g., typically when sizeof(T) > sizeof(uint8_t).
4602 char* pos = static_cast<char*>(ptr);
4603 for (size_t i = 0; i < num; ++i) {
4604 memcpy(pos, &value, sizeof(T));
4605 pos = pos + sizeof(T);
4606 }
4607 }
4608}
4609
4610// This makes heavy use of Offset, along with conditional branches. There may be
4611// opportunities for improvement.
4612//
4613// There are two versions of pad: Pad and PadV2. In PadV2 there is a second
4614// scalar input that provides the padding value. Therefore pad_value_ptr can be
4615// equivalent to a simple input1_data. For Pad, it should point to a zero
4616// value.
4617//
4618// Note that two typenames are required, so that T=P=int32 is considered a
4619// specialization distinct from P=int32.
4620template <typename T, typename P>
4621inline void PadImpl(const tflite::PadParams& op_params,
4622 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
4623 const P* pad_value_ptr, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4624 T* output_data) {
4625 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Pad4DSlowImpl");
4626 const RuntimeShape ext_input_shape =
4627 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, input_shape);
4628 const RuntimeShape ext_output_shape =
4629 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, output_shape);
4630 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(op_params.left_padding_count, 4);
4631 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(op_params.right_padding_count, 4);
4632
4633 // Pad kernels are limited to max 4 dimensions. Copy inputs so we can pad them
4634 // to 4 dims (yes, we are "padding the padding").
4635 std::vector<int> left_padding_copy(4, 0);
4636 const int left_padding_extend = 4 - op_params.left_padding_count;
4637 for (int i = 0; i < op_params.left_padding_count; ++i) {
4638 left_padding_copy[left_padding_extend + i] = op_params.left_padding[i];
4639 }
4640 std::vector<int> right_padding_copy(4, 0);
4641 const int right_padding_extend = 4 - op_params.right_padding_count;
4642 for (int i = 0; i < op_params.right_padding_count; ++i) {
4643 right_padding_copy[right_padding_extend + i] = op_params.right_padding[i];
4644 }
4645
4646 const int output_batch = ext_output_shape.Dims(0);
4647 const int output_height = ext_output_shape.Dims(1);
4648 const int output_width = ext_output_shape.Dims(2);
4649 const int output_depth = ext_output_shape.Dims(3);
4650
4651 const int left_b_padding = left_padding_copy[0];
4652 const int left_h_padding = left_padding_copy[1];
4653 const int left_w_padding = left_padding_copy[2];
4654 const int left_d_padding = left_padding_copy[3];
4655
4656 const int right_b_padding = right_padding_copy[0];
4657 const int right_h_padding = right_padding_copy[1];
4658 const int right_w_padding = right_padding_copy[2];
4659 const int right_d_padding = right_padding_copy[3];
4660
4661 const int input_depth = ext_input_shape.Dims(3);
4662 const T pad_value = *pad_value_ptr;
4663
4664 if (left_b_padding != 0) {
4665 TypedMemset<T>(
4666 output_data, pad_value,
4667 left_b_padding * output_height * output_width * output_depth);
4668 }
4669 for (int out_b = left_b_padding; out_b < output_batch - right_b_padding;
4670 ++out_b) {
4671 if (left_h_padding != 0) {
4672 TypedMemset<T>(output_data + Offset(ext_output_shape, out_b, 0, 0, 0),
4673 pad_value, left_h_padding * output_width * output_depth);
4674 }
4675 for (int out_h = left_h_padding; out_h < output_height - right_h_padding;
4676 ++out_h) {
4677 if (left_w_padding != 0) {
4678 TypedMemset<T>(
4679 output_data + Offset(ext_output_shape, out_b, out_h, 0, 0),
4680 pad_value, left_w_padding * output_depth);
4681 }
4682 for (int out_w = left_w_padding; out_w < output_width - right_w_padding;
4683 ++out_w) {
4684 if (left_d_padding != 0) {
4685 TypedMemset<T>(
4686 output_data + Offset(ext_output_shape, out_b, out_h, out_w, 0),
4687 pad_value, left_d_padding);
4688 }
4689
4690 T* out = output_data +
4691 Offset(ext_output_shape, out_b, out_h, out_w, left_d_padding);
4692 const T* in = input_data +
4693 Offset(ext_input_shape, out_b - left_b_padding,
4694 out_h - left_h_padding, out_w - left_w_padding, 0);
4695 memcpy(out, in, input_depth * sizeof(T));
4696
4697 if (right_d_padding != 0) {
4698 TypedMemset<T>(
4699 output_data + Offset(ext_output_shape, out_b, out_h, out_w,
4700 output_depth - right_d_padding),
4701 pad_value, right_d_padding);
4702 }
4703 }
4704 if (right_w_padding != 0) {
4705 TypedMemset<T>(output_data + Offset(ext_output_shape, out_b, out_h,
4706 output_width - right_w_padding, 0),
4707 pad_value, right_w_padding * output_depth);
4708 }
4709 }
4710 if (right_h_padding != 0) {
4711 TypedMemset<T>(
4712 output_data + Offset(ext_output_shape, out_b,
4713 output_height - right_h_padding, 0, 0),
4714 pad_value, right_h_padding * output_width * output_depth);
4715 }
4716 }
4717 if (right_b_padding != 0) {
4718 TypedMemset<T>(
4719 output_data +
4720 Offset(ext_output_shape, output_batch - right_b_padding, 0, 0, 0),
4721 pad_value,
4722 right_b_padding * output_height * output_width * output_depth);
4723 }
4724}
4725
4726template <typename T, typename P>
4727inline void Pad(const tflite::PadParams& op_params,
4728 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
4729 const P* pad_value_ptr, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4730 T* output_data) {
4731 PadImpl(op_params, input_shape, input_data, pad_value_ptr, output_shape,
4732 output_data);
4733}
4734
4735// The second (pad-value) input can be int32 when, say, the first is uint8.
4736template <typename T>
4737inline void Pad(const tflite::PadParams& op_params,
4738 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
4739 const int32* pad_value_ptr, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4740 T* output_data) {
4741 const T converted_pad_value = static_cast<T>(*pad_value_ptr);
4742 PadImpl(op_params, input_shape, input_data, &converted_pad_value,
4743 output_shape, output_data);
4744}
4745
4746// This version avoids conflicting template matching.
4747template <>
4748inline void Pad(const tflite::PadParams& op_params,
4749 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const int32* input_data,
4750 const int32* pad_value_ptr, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4751 int32* output_data) {
4752 PadImpl(op_params, input_shape, input_data, pad_value_ptr, output_shape,
4753 output_data);
4754}
4755
4756// TODO(b/117643175): Optimize. (This is an introductory copy of standard Pad.)
4757//
4758// This pad requires that (a) left and right paddings are in the 4D patterns
4759// {0, h_pad, w_pad, 0}, and (b) memset can be used: *pad_value_ptr == 0 and/or
4760// T is uint8.
4761//
4762// There are two versions of pad: Pad and PadV2. In PadV2 there is a second
4763// scalar input that provides the padding value. Therefore pad_value_ptr can be
4764// equivalent to a simple input1_data. For Pad, it should point to a zero
4765// value.
4766//
4767// Note that two typenames are required, so that T=P=int32 is considered a
4768// specialization distinct from P=int32.
4769template <typename T, typename P>
4770inline void PadImageStyleMemset(const tflite::PadParams& op_params,
4771 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
4772 const T* input_data, const P* pad_value_ptr,
4773 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4774 T* output_data) {
4775 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("PadImageStyle");
4776 const RuntimeShape ext_input_shape =
4777 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, input_shape);
4778 const RuntimeShape ext_output_shape =
4779 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, output_shape);
4780 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(op_params.left_padding_count, 4);
4781 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(op_params.right_padding_count, 4);
4782
4783 // Pad kernels are limited to max 4 dimensions. Copy inputs so we can pad them
4784 // to 4 dims (yes, we are "padding the padding").
4785 std::vector<int> left_padding_copy(4, 0);
4786 const int left_padding_extend = 4 - op_params.left_padding_count;
4787 for (int i = 0; i < op_params.left_padding_count; ++i) {
4788 left_padding_copy[left_padding_extend + i] = op_params.left_padding[i];
4789 }
4790 std::vector<int> right_padding_copy(4, 0);
4791 const int right_padding_extend = 4 - op_params.right_padding_count;
4792 for (int i = 0; i < op_params.right_padding_count; ++i) {
4793 right_padding_copy[right_padding_extend + i] = op_params.right_padding[i];
4794 }
4795 // The following padding restrictions are contractual requirements, and
4796 // embody what it means for a padding op to be "image-style".
4797 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(left_padding_copy[0], 0);
4798 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(left_padding_copy[3], 0);
4799 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(right_padding_copy[0], 0);
4800 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(right_padding_copy[3], 0);
4801
4802 const int batch = MatchingDim(ext_input_shape, 0, ext_output_shape, 0);
4803 const int output_height = ext_output_shape.Dims(1);
4804 const int output_width = ext_output_shape.Dims(2);
4805 const int input_height = ext_input_shape.Dims(1);
4806 const int input_width = ext_input_shape.Dims(2);
4807 const int depth = MatchingDim(ext_input_shape, 3, ext_output_shape, 3);
4808
4809 const int left_h_padding = left_padding_copy[1];
4810 const int left_w_padding = left_padding_copy[2];
4811 const int right_h_padding = right_padding_copy[1];
4812 const int right_w_padding = right_padding_copy[2];
4813
4814 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_height,
4815 input_height + left_h_padding + right_h_padding);
4816 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_width,
4817 input_width + left_w_padding + right_w_padding);
4818
4819 const T pad_value = *pad_value_ptr;
4820 const int top_block_size = left_h_padding * output_width * depth;
4821 const size_t num_top_block_bytes = top_block_size * sizeof(T);
4822 const int bottom_block_size = right_h_padding * output_width * depth;
4823 const size_t num_bottom_block_bytes = bottom_block_size * sizeof(T);
4824 const int left_blocks_size = left_w_padding * depth;
4825 const size_t num_left_block_bytes = left_blocks_size * sizeof(T);
4826 const int right_blocks_size = right_w_padding * depth;
4827 const size_t num_right_block_bytes = right_blocks_size * sizeof(T);
4828 const int inner_line_size = input_width * depth;
4829 const size_t num_inner_line_bytes = inner_line_size * sizeof(T);
4830
4831 if (input_height == 0) {
4832 memset(output_data, pad_value,
4833 num_top_block_bytes + num_bottom_block_bytes);
4834 } else {
4835 for (int i = 0; i < batch; ++i) {
4836 // For each image in the batch, apply the top padding, then iterate
4837 // through rows, then apply the bottom padding.
4838 //
4839 // By unwinding one iteration, we can combine the first left-margin
4840 // padding with the top padding, and the last right-margin padding with
4841 // the bottom padding.
4842 memset(output_data, pad_value,
4843 num_top_block_bytes + num_left_block_bytes);
4844 output_data += top_block_size + left_blocks_size;
4845 memcpy(output_data, input_data, num_inner_line_bytes);
4846 input_data += inner_line_size;
4847 output_data += inner_line_size;
4848 // One iteration unwound.
4849 // Unwinding this loop affords the opportunity to reorder the loop work
4850 // and hence combine memset() calls.
4851 //
4852 // Before unwinding:
4853 // for (int j = 0; j < input_height; ++j) {
4854 // // Pad on left, copy central data, pad on right.
4855 // memset(output_data, pad_value, num_left_block_bytes);
4856 // output_data += left_blocks_size;
4857 // memcpy(output_data, input_data, num_inner_line_bytes);
4858 // input_data += inner_line_size;
4859 // output_data += inner_line_size;
4860 // memset(output_data, pad_value, num_right_block_bytes);
4861 // output_data += right_blocks_size;
4862 // }
4863 for (int j = 1; j < input_height; ++j) {
4864 memset(output_data, pad_value,
4865 num_right_block_bytes + num_left_block_bytes);
4866 output_data += right_blocks_size + left_blocks_size;
4867 memcpy(output_data, input_data, num_inner_line_bytes);
4868 input_data += inner_line_size;
4869 output_data += inner_line_size;
4870 }
4871 memset(output_data, pad_value,
4872 num_right_block_bytes + num_bottom_block_bytes);
4873 output_data += right_blocks_size + bottom_block_size;
4874 }
4875 }
4876}
4877
4878template <typename T, typename P>
4879inline void PadImageStyle(const tflite::PadParams& op_params,
4880 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
4881 const P* pad_value_ptr,
4882 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
4883 reference_ops::PadImageStyle(op_params, input_shape, input_data,
4884 pad_value_ptr, output_shape, output_data);
4885}

4888inline void PadImageStyle(const tflite::PadParams& op_params,
4889 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
4890 const uint8* input_data, const P* pad_value_ptr,
4891 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,

4897template <typename P>
4898inline void PadImageStyle(const tflite::PadParams& op_params,
4899 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
4900 const float* input_data, const P* pad_value_ptr,
4901 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4902 float* output_data) {
4903 const float converted_pad_value = static_cast<float>(*pad_value_ptr);
4904 if (converted_pad_value == 0.0f) {
4905 PadImageStyleMemset(op_params, input_shape, input_data, pad_value_ptr,
4906 output_shape, output_data);
4907 } else {
4908 PadImpl(op_params, input_shape, input_data, pad_value_ptr, output_shape,
4909 output_data);
4910 }

4912
4913template <typename T>
4914inline void Slice(const tflite::SliceParams& op_params,
4915 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
4916 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
4917 SequentialTensorWriter<T>* writer) {
4918 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Slice");
4919 const RuntimeShape ext_shape = RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(5, input_shape);
4920 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(op_params.begin_count, 5);
4921 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(op_params.size_count, 5);
4922 const int begin_count = op_params.begin_count;
4923 const int size_count = op_params.size_count;
4924 // We front-pad the begin and size vectors.
4925 std::array<int, 5> start;
4926 std::array<int, 5> stop;
4927 for (int i = 0; i < 5; ++i) {
4928 int padded_i = 5 - i;
4929 start[i] =
4930 begin_count < padded_i ? 0 : op_params.begin[begin_count - padded_i];
4931 stop[i] =
4932 (size_count < padded_i || op_params.size[size_count - padded_i] == -1)
4933 ? ext_shape.Dims(i)
4934 : start[i] + op_params.size[size_count - padded_i];
4935 }
4936
4937 for (int i0 = start[0]; i0 < stop[0]; ++i0) {
4938 for (int i1 = start[1]; i1 < stop[1]; ++i1) {
4939 for (int i2 = start[2]; i2 < stop[2]; ++i2) {
4940 for (int i3 = start[3]; i3 < stop[3]; ++i3) {
4941 const int len = stop[4] - start[4];
4942 if (len > 0)
4943 writer->WriteN(Offset(ext_shape, i0, i1, i2, i3, start[4]), len);
4944 }
4945 }
4946 }
4947 }
4948}
4949
4950template <typename T>
4951inline void Slice(const tflite::SliceParams& op_params,
4952 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
4953 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
4954 SequentialTensorWriter<T> writer(input_data, output_data);
4955 return Slice(op_params, input_shape, output_shape, &writer);
4956}
4957
4958template <typename T>
4959inline void Slice(const tflite::SliceParams& op_params,
4960 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const TfLiteTensor* input,
4961 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, TfLiteTensor* output) {
4962 SequentialTensorWriter<T> writer(input, output);
4963 return Slice(op_params, input_shape, output_shape, &writer);
4964}
4965
4966// Note: This implementation is only optimized for the case where the inner
4967// stride == 1.
4968template <typename T>
4969inline void StridedSlice(const tflite::StridedSliceParams& op_params,
4970 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input_shape,
4971 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape,
4972 SequentialTensorWriter<T>* writer) {
4973 using strided_slice::LoopCondition;
4974 using strided_slice::StartForAxis;
4975 using strided_slice::StopForAxis;
4976
4977 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("StridedSlice");
4978
4979 // Note that the output_shape is not used herein.
4980 tflite::StridedSliceParams params_copy = op_params;
4981
4982 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 5);
4983 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 5);
4984 const RuntimeShape input_shape =
4985 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(5, unextended_input_shape);
4986 const RuntimeShape output_shape =
4987 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(5, unextended_output_shape);
4988
4989 // Reverse and pad to 5 dimensions because that is what the runtime code
4990 // requires (ie. all shapes must be 5D and are given backwards).
4991 strided_slice::StridedSlicePadIndices(&params_copy, 5);
4992
4993 const int start_0 = StartForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 0);
4994 const int stop_0 = StopForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 0, start_0);
4995 const int start_1 = StartForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 1);
4996 const int stop_1 = StopForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 1, start_1);
4997 const int start_2 = StartForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 2);
4998 const int stop_2 = StopForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 2, start_2);
4999 const int start_3 = StartForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 3);
5000 const int stop_3 = StopForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 3, start_3);
5001 const int start_4 = StartForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 4);
5002 const int stop_4 = StopForAxis(params_copy, input_shape, 4, start_4);
5003 const bool inner_stride_is_1 = params_copy.strides[4] == 1;
5004
5005 for (int offset_0 = start_0 * input_shape.Dims(1),
5006 end_0 = stop_0 * input_shape.Dims(1),
5007 step_0 = params_copy.strides[0] * input_shape.Dims(1);
5008 !LoopCondition(offset_0, end_0, params_copy.strides[0]);
5009 offset_0 += step_0) {
5010 for (int offset_1 = (offset_0 + start_1) * input_shape.Dims(2),
5011 end_1 = (offset_0 + stop_1) * input_shape.Dims(2),
5012 step_1 = params_copy.strides[1] * input_shape.Dims(2);
5013 !LoopCondition(offset_1, end_1, params_copy.strides[1]);
5014 offset_1 += step_1) {
5015 for (int offset_2 = (offset_1 + start_2) * input_shape.Dims(3),
5016 end_2 = (offset_1 + stop_2) * input_shape.Dims(3),
5017 step_2 = params_copy.strides[2] * input_shape.Dims(3);
5018 !LoopCondition(offset_2, end_2, params_copy.strides[2]);
5019 offset_2 += step_2) {
5020 for (int offset_3 = (offset_2 + start_3) * input_shape.Dims(4),
5021 end_3 = (offset_2 + stop_3) * input_shape.Dims(4),
5022 step_3 = params_copy.strides[3] * input_shape.Dims(4);
5023 !LoopCondition(offset_3, end_3, params_copy.strides[3]);
5024 offset_3 += step_3) {
5025 // When the stride is 1, the inner loop is equivalent to the
5026 // optimized slice inner loop. Otherwise, it is identical to the
5027 // strided_slice reference implementation inner loop.
5028 if (inner_stride_is_1) {
5029 const int len = stop_4 - start_4;
5030 if (len > 0) {
5031 writer->WriteN(offset_3 + start_4, len);
5032 }
5033 } else {
5034 for (int offset_4 = offset_3 + start_4, end_4 = offset_3 + stop_4;
5035 !LoopCondition(offset_4, end_4, params_copy.strides[4]);
5036 offset_4 += params_copy.strides[4]) {
5037 writer->Write(offset_4);
5038 }
5039 }
5040 }
5041 }
5042 }
5043 }
5044}
5045
5046template <typename T>
5047inline void StridedSlice(const tflite::StridedSliceParams& op_params,
5048 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input_shape,
5049 const T* input_data,
5050 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape,
5051 T* output_data) {
5052 SequentialTensorWriter<T> writer(input_data, output_data);
5053 StridedSlice<T>(op_params, unextended_input_shape, unextended_output_shape,
5054 &writer);
5055}
5056
5057template <typename T>
5058inline void StridedSlice(const tflite::StridedSliceParams& op_params,
5059 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input_shape,
5060 const TfLiteTensor* input,
5061 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape,
5062 TfLiteTensor* output) {
5063 SequentialTensorWriter<T> writer(input, output);
5064 StridedSlice<T>(op_params, unextended_input_shape, unextended_output_shape,
5065 &writer);
5066}

5068template <typename T>
5069void Minimum(const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const T* input1_data,
5070 const T* input2_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
5071 T* output_data) {
5072 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("TensorFlowMinimum");
5073 auto input1_map = MapAsVector(input1_data, input1_shape);
5074 auto output_map = MapAsVector(output_data, output_shape);
5075 auto min_value = input2_data[0];
5076 output_map.array() = input1_map.array().min(min_value);
5077}
5078
5079// Convenience version that allows, for example, generated-code calls to be
5080// the same as other binary ops.
5081template <typename T>
5082inline void Minimum(const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const T* input1_data,
5083 const RuntimeShape&, const T* input2_data,
5084 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
5085 // Drop shape of second input: not needed.
5086 Minimum(input1_shape, input1_data, input2_data, output_shape, output_data);
5087}
5088
5089template <typename T>
5090void Maximum(const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const T* input1_data,
5091 const T* input2_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
5092 T* output_data) {
5093 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("TensorFlowMaximum");
5094 auto input1_map = MapAsVector(input1_data, input1_shape);
5095 auto output_map = MapAsVector(output_data, output_shape);
5096 auto max_value = input2_data[0];
5097 output_map.array() = input1_map.array().max(max_value);
5098}

5104 const RuntimeShape&, const T* input2_data,
