5109
5110template <typename T>
5111void TransposeIm2col(const ConvParams& params, uint8 zero_byte,
5112 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
5113 const RuntimeShape& filter_shape,
5114 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* im2col_data) {
5115 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("TransposeIm2col");
5116 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
5117 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
5118 const int pad_width = params.padding_values.width;
5119 const int pad_height = params.padding_values.height;
5120 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5121 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(filter_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5122 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5123 TFLITE_DCHECK(im2col_data);
5124
5125 const int batches = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
5126 const int input_height = input_shape.Dims(1);
5127 const int input_width = input_shape.Dims(2);
5128 const int input_depth = MatchingDim(input_shape, 3, filter_shape, 3);
5129 const int filter_height = filter_shape.Dims(1);
5130 const int filter_width = filter_shape.Dims(2);
5131 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
5132 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
5133 MatchingDim(output_shape, 3, filter_shape, 0); // output_depth
5134
5135 // Construct the MxN sized im2col matrix.
5136 // The rows M, are sub-ordered B x H x W
5137 const RuntimeShape row_shape({1, batches, output_height, output_width});
5138 // The columns, N, are sub-ordered Kh x Kw x Din
5139 const RuntimeShape col_shape({1, filter_height, filter_width, input_depth});
5140 // Use dimensions M and N to construct dims for indexing directly into im2col
5141 const RuntimeShape im2col_shape(
5142 {1, 1, row_shape.FlatSize(), col_shape.FlatSize()});
5143
5144 // Build the im2col matrix by looping through all the input pixels,
5145 // computing their influence on the output, rather than looping through all
5146 // the output pixels. We therefore must initialize the im2col array to zero.
5147 // This is potentially inefficient because we subsequently overwrite bytes
5148 // set here. However, in practice memset is very fast and costs negligible.
5149 memset(im2col_data, zero_byte, im2col_shape.FlatSize() * sizeof(T));
5150
5151 // Loop through the output batches
5152 for (int batch = 0; batch < batches; ++batch) {
5153 // Loop through input pixels one at a time.
5154 for (int in_y = 0; in_y < input_height; ++in_y) {
5155 for (int in_x = 0; in_x < input_width; ++in_x) {
5156 // Loop through the output pixels it will influence
5157 const int out_x_origin = (in_x * stride_width) - pad_width;
5158 const int out_y_origin = (in_y * stride_height) - pad_height;
5159 for (int filter_y = 0; filter_y < filter_height; ++filter_y) {
5160 const int out_y = out_y_origin + filter_y;
5161 // Is output pixel within height bounds?
5162 if ((out_y >= 0) && (out_y < output_height)) {
5163 for (int filter_x = 0; filter_x < filter_width; ++filter_x) {
5164 const int out_x = out_x_origin + filter_x;
5165 // Is output pixel within width bounds?
5166 if ((out_x >= 0) && (out_x < output_width)) {
5167 // Copy the input elements of this pixel
5168 T const* src =
5169 input_data + Offset(input_shape, batch, in_y, in_x, 0);
5170 int row_offset = Offset(row_shape, 0, batch, out_y, out_x);
5171 int col_offset = Offset(col_shape, 0, filter_y, filter_x, 0);
5172 T* dst = im2col_data +
5173 Offset(im2col_shape, 0, 0, row_offset, col_offset);
5174 memcpy(dst, src, input_depth * sizeof(T));
5175 }
5176 }
5177 }
5178 }
5179 }
5180 }
5181 }
5182}
5183
5184// Returns in 'im_data' (assumes to be zero-initialized) image patch in storage
5185// order (height, width, depth), constructed from patches in 'col_data', which
5186// is required to be in storage order (out_height * out_width, filter_height,
5187// filter_width, in_depth). Implementation by Yangqing Jia (jiayq).
5188// Copied from //tensorflow/core/kernels/conv_grad_input_ops.cc
5189template <typename T>
5190void Col2im(const T* col_data, const int depth, const int height,
5191 const int width, const int filter_h, const int filter_w,
5192 const int pad_t, const int pad_l, const int pad_b, const int pad_r,
5193 const int stride_h, const int stride_w, T* im_data) {
5194 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Col2im");
5195 int height_col = (height + pad_t + pad_b - filter_h) / stride_h + 1;
5196 int width_col = (width + pad_l + pad_r - filter_w) / stride_w + 1;
5197 int h_pad = -pad_t;
5198 for (int h = 0; h < height_col; ++h) {
5199 int w_pad = -pad_l;
5200 for (int w = 0; w < width_col; ++w) {
5201 T* im_patch_data = im_data + (h_pad * width + w_pad) * depth;
5202 for (int ih = h_pad; ih < h_pad + filter_h; ++ih) {
5203 for (int iw = w_pad; iw < w_pad + filter_w; ++iw) {
5204 if (ih >= 0 && ih < height && iw >= 0 && iw < width) {
5205 // TODO(andydavis) Vectorize this loop (if compiler does not).
5206 for (int i = 0; i < depth; ++i) {
5207 im_patch_data[i] += col_data[i];
5208 }
5209 }
5210 im_patch_data += depth;
5211 col_data += depth;
5212 }
5213 // Jump over remaining number of depth.
5214 im_patch_data += depth * (width - filter_w);
5215 }
5216 w_pad += stride_w;
5217 }
5218 h_pad += stride_h;
5219 }
5220}
5221
5222template <typename T>
5223void BiasAdd(T* im_data, const T* bias_data, const int batch_size,
5224 const int height, const int width, const int depth) {
5225 if (bias_data) {
5226 for (int n = 0; n < batch_size; ++n) {
5227 for (int h = 0; h < height; ++h) {
5228 for (int w = 0; w < width; ++w) {
5229 for (int d = 0; d < depth; ++d) {
5230 im_data[d] += bias_data[d];
5231 }
5232 im_data += depth;
5233 }
5234 }
5235 }
5236 }
5237}
5238
5239// TransposeConvV2 expect the weights in HWOI order.
5240inline void TransposeConvV2(
5241 const ConvParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
5242 const float* input_data, const RuntimeShape& hwoi_ordered_filter_shape,
5243 const float* hwoi_ordered_filter_data, const RuntimeShape& bias_shape,
5244 const float* bias_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
5245 float* const output_data, const RuntimeShape& col2im_shape,
5246 float* col2im_data, CpuBackendContext* cpu_backend_context) {
5247 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("TransposeConvV2/float");
5248 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5249 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(hwoi_ordered_filter_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5250 TFLITE_DCHECK(col2im_data);
5251 TFLITE_DCHECK(hwoi_ordered_filter_data);
5252
5253 const int batch_size = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
5254 const int input_image_size = input_shape.Dims(1) * input_shape.Dims(2);
5255 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
5256 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
5257 const int output_image_size = output_height * output_width;
5258 const int input_depth =
5259 MatchingDim(input_shape, 3, hwoi_ordered_filter_shape, 3);
5260 const int output_depth =
5261 MatchingDim(output_shape, 3, hwoi_ordered_filter_shape, 2);
5262 const int input_offset = input_image_size * input_depth;
5263 const int output_offset = output_image_size * output_depth;
5264
5265 const int filter_height = hwoi_ordered_filter_shape.Dims(0);
5266 const int filter_width = hwoi_ordered_filter_shape.Dims(1);
5267 const int padding_top = params.padding_values.height;
5268 const int padding_bottom =
5269 params.padding_values.height + params.padding_values.height_offset;
5270 const int padding_left = params.padding_values.width;
5271 const int padding_right =
5272 params.padding_values.width + params.padding_values.width_offset;
5273 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
5274 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
5275
5276 const int hwoi_ordered_filter_total_size =
5277 filter_height * filter_width * output_depth;
5278
5279 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<float> lhs_params;
5280 lhs_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kRowMajor;
5281 lhs_params.rows = hwoi_ordered_filter_total_size;
5282 lhs_params.cols = input_depth;
5283 float* output_data_p = output_data;
5284 std::fill_n(output_data, output_offset * batch_size, 0.0f);
5285 for (int i = 0; i < batch_size; ++i) {
5286 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<float> rhs_params;
5287 rhs_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kColMajor;
5288 rhs_params.rows = input_depth;
5289 rhs_params.cols = input_image_size;
5290 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<float> dst_params;
5291 dst_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kColMajor;
5292 dst_params.rows = hwoi_ordered_filter_total_size;
5293 dst_params.cols = input_image_size;
5294 cpu_backend_gemm::GemmParams<float, float> gemm_params;
5295 cpu_backend_gemm::Gemm(lhs_params, hwoi_ordered_filter_data, rhs_params,
5296 input_data + input_offset * i, dst_params,
5297 col2im_data, gemm_params, cpu_backend_context);
5298
5299 Col2im(col2im_data, output_depth, output_height, output_width,
5300 filter_height, filter_width, padding_top, padding_left,
5301 padding_bottom, padding_right, stride_height, stride_width,
5302 output_data_p);
5303 output_data_p += output_offset;
5304 }
5305 output_data_p = output_data;
5306 BiasAdd(output_data_p, bias_data, batch_size, output_height, output_width,
5307 output_depth);
5308}
5309
5310inline void Quantize(int32_t multiplier, int32_t shift, int32_t total_size,
5311 int32_t output_zp, int32_t* scratch, uint8_t* output) {
5312 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Quantize/uint8");
5313 int i = 0;
5314 const int32_t output_min = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min();
5315 const int32_t output_max = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
5316
5317#ifdef USE_NEON
5318 const int32x4_t output_zp_dup = vdupq_n_s32(output_zp);
5319 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(output_max);
5320 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(output_min);
5321
5322 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
5323 using gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul;
5324
5325 for (; i <= total_size - 16; i += 16) {
5326 int32x4x4_t scratch_val;
5327 scratch_val.val[0] = vld1q_s32(scratch + i);
5328 scratch_val.val[1] = vld1q_s32(scratch + i + 4);
5329 scratch_val.val[2] = vld1q_s32(scratch + i + 8);
5330 scratch_val.val[3] = vld1q_s32(scratch + i + 12);
5331
5332 int32x4x4_t temp_val =
5333 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier4Rows(scratch_val, multiplier, shift);
5334
5335 temp_val.val[0] = vaddq_s32(temp_val.val[0], output_zp_dup);
5336 temp_val.val[1] = vaddq_s32(temp_val.val[1], output_zp_dup);
5337 temp_val.val[2] = vaddq_s32(temp_val.val[2], output_zp_dup);
5338 temp_val.val[3] = vaddq_s32(temp_val.val[3], output_zp_dup);
5339
5340 temp_val.val[0] =
5341 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(temp_val.val[0], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5342 temp_val.val[1] =
5343 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(temp_val.val[1], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5344 temp_val.val[2] =
5345 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(temp_val.val[2], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5346 temp_val.val[3] =
5347 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(temp_val.val[3], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5348
5349 const uint16x8_t result_1 =
5350 vcombine_u16(vqmovn_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_s32(temp_val.val[0])),
5351 vqmovn_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_s32(temp_val.val[1])));
5352 const uint16x8_t result_2 =
5353 vcombine_u16(vqmovn_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_s32(temp_val.val[2])),
5354 vqmovn_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_s32(temp_val.val[3])));
5355 const uint8x16_t result =
5356 vcombine_u8(vqmovn_u16(result_1), vqmovn_u16(result_2));
5357 vst1q_u8(output + i, result);
5358 }
5359#endif
5360 for (; i < total_size; ++i) {
5361 int32_t temp = MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(scratch[i], multiplier, shift);
5362 temp += output_zp;
5363 if (temp > output_max) {
5364 temp = output_max;
5365 }
5366 if (temp < output_min) {
5367 temp = output_min;
5368 }
5369 output[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(temp);
5370 }
5371}
5372
5373inline void Quantize(const int32_t* multiplier, const int32_t* shift,
5374 int32_t channel_size, int32_t total_size,
5375 int32_t output_zp, int32_t output_min, int32_t output_max,
5376 int32_t* scratch, int8_t* output) {
5377 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Quantize/int8");
5378
5379 // Here we're trying to quantize the raw accumulators:
5380 // output_channels
5381 // data data data data data
5382 // rows data data data data data
5383 // data data data data data
5384 // ....
5385 //
5386 // In order to minimize the reload of the multipliers & shifts, once we load
5387 // the multipliers & shifts, we load & quantize the raw accumulators for every
5388 // row.
5389#ifdef USE_NEON
5390 const int32x4_t output_offset_vec = vdupq_n_s32(output_zp);
5391 const int32x4_t output_activation_min_vec = vdupq_n_s32(output_min);
5392 const int32x4_t output_activation_max_vec = vdupq_n_s32(output_max);
5393 const int32x4_t zeros = vdupq_n_s32(0);
5394#endif
5395
5396 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(total_size % channel_size, 0);
5397 const int32_t rows = total_size / channel_size;
5398
5399 int c = 0;
5400
5401#ifdef USE_NEON
5402 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
5403 for (; c <= channel_size - 8; c += 8) {
5404 int32x4_t out_shift_1 = vld1q_s32(shift + c);
5405 int32x4_t out_shift_2 = vld1q_s32(shift + c + 4);
5406 int32x4_t left_shift_1 = vmaxq_s32(out_shift_1, zeros);
5407 int32x4_t left_shift_2 = vmaxq_s32(out_shift_2, zeros);
5408
5409 // Right shift will be performed as left shift with negative values.
5410 int32x4_t right_shift_1 = vminq_s32(out_shift_1, zeros);
5411 int32x4_t right_shift_2 = vminq_s32(out_shift_2, zeros);
5412
5413 int32x4_t out_mul_1 = vld1q_s32(multiplier + c);
5414 int32x4_t out_mul_2 = vld1q_s32(multiplier + c + 4);
5415 for (int n = 0; n < rows; ++n) {
5416 int loc = n * channel_size + c;
5417 int32x4_t acc_1 = vld1q_s32(scratch + loc);
5418 int32x4_t acc_2 = vld1q_s32(scratch + loc + 4);
5419
5420 // Saturating Rounding Doubling High Mul.
5421 acc_1 = vshlq_s32(acc_1, left_shift_1);
5422 acc_1 = vqrdmulhq_s32(acc_1, out_mul_1);
5423 acc_2 = vshlq_s32(acc_2, left_shift_2);
5424 acc_2 = vqrdmulhq_s32(acc_2, out_mul_2);
5425
5426 // Rounding Dividing By POT.
5427 acc_1 = vrshlq_s32(acc_1, right_shift_1);
5428 acc_2 = vrshlq_s32(acc_2, right_shift_2);
5429
5430 // Add the output offset.
5431 acc_1 = vaddq_s32(acc_1, output_offset_vec);
5432 acc_2 = vaddq_s32(acc_2, output_offset_vec);
5433
5434 // Apply the activation function.
5435 acc_1 = vmaxq_s32(acc_1, output_activation_min_vec);
5436 acc_1 = vminq_s32(acc_1, output_activation_max_vec);
5437 acc_2 = vmaxq_s32(acc_2, output_activation_min_vec);
5438 acc_2 = vminq_s32(acc_2, output_activation_max_vec);
5439
5440 // Saturating cast to int8 and store to destination.
5441 const int16x4_t acc_s16_1 = vqmovn_s32(acc_1);
5442 const int16x4_t acc_s16_2 = vqmovn_s32(acc_2);
5443 const int16x8_t res_s16 = vcombine_s16(acc_s16_1, acc_s16_2);
5444 const int8x8_t res_s8 = vqmovn_s16(res_s16);
5445 vst1_s8(output + loc, res_s8);
5446 }
5447 }
5448
5449#endif // USE_NEON
5450 // Handle leftover values, one by one. This is very slow.
5451 for (; c < channel_size; c++) {
5452 for (int n = 0; n < rows; ++n) {
5453 int loc = n * channel_size + c;
5454 int32 acc = scratch[loc];
5455 acc = MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(acc, multiplier[c], shift[c]);
5456 acc += output_zp;
5457 acc = std::max(acc, output_min);
5458 acc = std::min(acc, output_max);
5459 output[loc] = static_cast<int8>(acc);
5460 }
5461 }
5462}
5463
5464// TransposeConvV2 expect the weights in HWOI order.
5465inline void TransposeConvV2(
5466 const ConvParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
5467 const uint8_t* input_data, const RuntimeShape& hwoi_ordered_filter_shape,
5468 const uint8_t* hwoi_ordered_filter_data, const RuntimeShape& bias_shape,
5469 const int32* bias_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
5470 uint8_t* output_data, const RuntimeShape& col2im_shape,
5471 int32_t* col2im_data, int32_t* scratch_data,
5472 CpuBackendContext* cpu_backend_context) {
5473 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("TransposeConvV2/uint8");
5474 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5475 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(hwoi_ordered_filter_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5476 TFLITE_DCHECK(col2im_data);
5477 TFLITE_DCHECK(hwoi_ordered_filter_data);
5478
5479 const int batch_size = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
5480 const int input_image_size = input_shape.Dims(1) * input_shape.Dims(2);
5481 const int output_height = output_shape.Dims(1);
5482 const int output_width = output_shape.Dims(2);
5483 const int output_image_size = output_height * output_width;
5484 const int input_depth =
5485 MatchingDim(input_shape, 3, hwoi_ordered_filter_shape, 3);
5486 const int output_depth =
5487 MatchingDim(output_shape, 3, hwoi_ordered_filter_shape, 2);
5488 const int input_offset = input_image_size * input_depth;
5489 const int output_offset = output_image_size * output_depth;
5490
5491 const int filter_height = hwoi_ordered_filter_shape.Dims(0);
5492 const int filter_width = hwoi_ordered_filter_shape.Dims(1);
5493 const int padding_top = params.padding_values.height;
5494 const int padding_bottom =
5495 params.padding_values.height + params.padding_values.height_offset;
5496 const int padding_left = params.padding_values.width;
5497 const int padding_right =
5498 params.padding_values.width + params.padding_values.width_offset;
5499 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
5500 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
5501
5502 const int hwoi_ordered_filter_total_size =
5503 filter_height * filter_width * output_depth;
5504
5505 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<uint8_t> lhs_params;
5506 lhs_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kRowMajor;
5507 lhs_params.rows = hwoi_ordered_filter_total_size;
5508 lhs_params.cols = input_depth;
5509 lhs_params.zero_point = -params.weights_offset;
5510
5511 int32_t* scratch_data_p = scratch_data;
5512 std::fill_n(scratch_data, output_offset * batch_size, static_cast<int32>(0));
5513 for (int i = 0; i < batch_size; ++i) {
5514 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<uint8_t> rhs_params;
5515 rhs_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kColMajor;
5516 rhs_params.rows = input_depth;
5517 rhs_params.cols = input_image_size;
5518 rhs_params.zero_point = -params.input_offset;
5519
5520 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<int32_t> dst_params;
5521 dst_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kColMajor;
5522 dst_params.rows = hwoi_ordered_filter_total_size;
5523 dst_params.cols = input_image_size;
5524
5525 cpu_backend_gemm::GemmParams<int32_t, int32_t> gemm_params;
5526 cpu_backend_gemm::Gemm(lhs_params, hwoi_ordered_filter_data, rhs_params,
5527 input_data + input_offset * i, dst_params,
5528 col2im_data, gemm_params, cpu_backend_context);
5529
5530 Col2im(col2im_data, output_depth, output_height, output_width,
5531 filter_height, filter_width, padding_top, padding_left,
5532 padding_bottom, padding_right, stride_height, stride_width,
5533 scratch_data_p);
5534
5535 scratch_data_p += output_offset;
5536 }
5537 scratch_data_p = scratch_data;
5538 BiasAdd(scratch_data_p, bias_data, batch_size, output_height, output_width,
5539 output_depth);
5540
5541 Quantize(params.output_multiplier, params.output_shift,
5542 output_shape.FlatSize(), params.output_offset, scratch_data,
5543 output_data);
5544}
5545
5546// Integer-only version of ResizeNearestNeighbor. Since scales are represented
5547// in fixed-point and thus approximated, |in_x| or |in_y| may differ from the
5548// reference version. Debug checks are in place to test if this occurs.
5549// NOTE: If align_corners or half_pixel_centers is true, we use the reference
5550// version.
5551inline void ResizeNearestNeighbor(
5552 const tflite::ResizeNearestNeighborParams& op_params,
5553 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input_shape, const uint8* input_data,
5554 const RuntimeShape& output_size_shape, const int32* output_size_data,
5555 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape, uint8* output_data) {
5556 if (op_params.align_corners || op_params.half_pixel_centers) {
5557 // TODO(b/149823713): Add support for align_corners & half_pixel_centers in
5558 // this kernel.
5559 reference_ops::ResizeNearestNeighbor(
5560 op_params, unextended_input_shape, input_data, output_size_shape,
5561 output_size_data, unextended_output_shape, output_data);
5562 return;
5563 }
5564 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5565 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unextended_output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 4);
5566
5567 const RuntimeShape input_shape =
5568 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_input_shape);
5569 const RuntimeShape output_shape =
5570 RuntimeShape::ExtendedShape(4, unextended_output_shape);
5571
5572 int32 batches = MatchingDim(input_shape, 0, output_shape, 0);
5573 int32 input_height = input_shape.Dims(1);
5574 int32 input_width = input_shape.Dims(2);
5575 int32 depth = MatchingDim(input_shape, 3, output_shape, 3);
5576
5577 // The Tensorflow version of this op allows resize on the width and height
5578 // axis only.
5579 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_size_shape.FlatSize(), 2);
5580 int32 output_height = output_size_data[0];
5581 int32 output_width = output_size_data[1];
5582
5583 // Convert scales to fixed-point with 16 fractional bits. We add 1 as an
5584 // error factor and to avoid zero scales. For example, with input_height = 1,
5585 // output_height = 3, the float scaling factor would be non-zero at 1/3.
5586 // With fixed-point, this is zero.
5587 int32 height_scale = (input_height << 16) / output_height + 1;
5588 int32 width_scale = (input_width << 16) / output_width + 1;
5589
5590 const int col_offset = input_shape.Dims(3);
5591 const int row_offset = input_shape.Dims(2) * col_offset;
5592 const int batch_offset = input_shape.Dims(1) * row_offset;
5593
5594 const uint8* input_ptr = input_data;
5595 uint8* output_ptr = output_data;
5596 for (int b = 0; b < batches; ++b) {
5597 for (int y = 0; y < output_height; ++y) {
5598 int32 in_y = std::min((y * height_scale) >> 16, input_height - 1);
5599 // Check offset calculation is the same as the reference version. See
5600 // function comment for details. We check using a non-float version of:
5601 // TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(in_y, std::floor(y * (static_cast<float>(input_height)
5602 // / output_height)));
5603 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(y * input_height, output_height + in_y * output_height);
5604 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(y * input_height, in_y * output_height);
5605 const uint8* y_input_ptr = input_ptr + in_y * row_offset;
5606 for (int x = 0; x < output_width; ++x) {
5607 int32 in_x = std::min((x * width_scale) >> 16, input_width - 1);
5608 // Check offset calculation is the same as the reference version. See
5609 // function comment for details. We check using a non-float version of:
5610 // TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(in_y,
5611 // std::floor(y * (static_cast<float>(input_width)
5612 // / output_width)));
5613 TFLITE_DCHECK_LT(x * input_width, output_width + in_x * output_width);
5614 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(x * input_width, in_x * output_width);
5615 const uint8* x_input_ptr = y_input_ptr + in_x * col_offset;
5616 memcpy(output_ptr, x_input_ptr, depth);
5617 output_ptr += depth;
5618 }
5619 }
5620 input_ptr += batch_offset;
5621 }
5622}
5623
5624template <typename input_type, typename output_type>
5625inline void Requantize(const input_type* input_data, int32_t size,
5626 int32_t effective_scale_multiplier,
5627 int32_t effective_scale_shift, int32_t input_zeropoint,
5628 int32_t output_zeropoint, output_type* output_data) {
5629 reference_ops::Requantize(input_data, size, effective_scale_multiplier,
5630 effective_scale_shift, input_zeropoint,
5631 output_zeropoint, output_data);
5632}
5633
5634template <>
5635inline void Requantize<int8_t, uint8_t>(const int8_t* input_data, int32_t size,
5636 int32_t effective_scale_multiplier,
5637 int32_t effective_scale_shift,
5638 int32_t input_zeropoint,
5639 int32_t output_zeropoint,
5640 uint8_t* output_data) {
5641 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Requantize/Int8ToUint8");
5642
5643 static constexpr int32_t kMinOutput = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min();
5644 static constexpr int32_t kMaxOutput = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
5645
5646 int i = 0;
5647#ifdef USE_NEON
5648 // Constants.
5649 const int32x4_t input_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(-input_zeropoint);
5650 const int32x4_t output_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(output_zeropoint);
5651 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(kMinOutput);
5652 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(kMaxOutput);
5653
5654 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
5655 const int8x16_t input_vec = vld1q_s8(input_data + i);
5656 const int16x8_t first_half = vmovl_s8(vget_low_s8(input_vec));
5657 const int16x8_t second_half = vmovl_s8(vget_high_s8(input_vec));
5658 int32x4x4_t input;
5659 input.val[0] = vmovl_s16(vget_low_s16(first_half));
5660 input.val[1] = vmovl_s16(vget_high_s16(first_half));
5661 input.val[2] = vmovl_s16(vget_low_s16(second_half));
5662 input.val[3] = vmovl_s16(vget_high_s16(second_half));
5663 input.val[0] = vaddq_s32(input.val[0], input_zero_point_dup);
5664 input.val[1] = vaddq_s32(input.val[1], input_zero_point_dup);
5665 input.val[2] = vaddq_s32(input.val[2], input_zero_point_dup);
5666 input.val[3] = vaddq_s32(input.val[3], input_zero_point_dup);
5667
5668 int32x4x4_t result = MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier4Rows(
5669 input, effective_scale_multiplier, effective_scale_shift);
5670
5671 result.val[0] = vaddq_s32(result.val[0], output_zero_point_dup);
5672 result.val[1] = vaddq_s32(result.val[1], output_zero_point_dup);
5673 result.val[2] = vaddq_s32(result.val[2], output_zero_point_dup);
5674 result.val[3] = vaddq_s32(result.val[3], output_zero_point_dup);
5675 result.val[0] =
5676 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[0], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5677 result.val[1] =
5678 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[1], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5679 result.val[2] =
5680 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[2], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5681 result.val[3] =
5682 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[3], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5683
5684 const uint32x4_t result_val_1_unsigned =
5685 vreinterpretq_u32_s32(result.val[0]);
5686 const uint32x4_t result_val_2_unsigned =
5687 vreinterpretq_u32_s32(result.val[1]);
5688 const uint32x4_t result_val_3_unsigned =
5689 vreinterpretq_u32_s32(result.val[2]);
5690 const uint32x4_t result_val_4_unsigned =
5691 vreinterpretq_u32_s32(result.val[3]);
5692
5693 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_1 = vqmovn_u32(result_val_1_unsigned);
5694 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_2 = vqmovn_u32(result_val_2_unsigned);
5695 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_3 = vqmovn_u32(result_val_3_unsigned);
5696 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_4 = vqmovn_u32(result_val_4_unsigned);
5697 const uint16x8_t output_first_half =
5698 vcombine_u16(narrowed_val_1, narrowed_val_2);
5699 const uint16x8_t output_second_half =
5700 vcombine_u16(narrowed_val_3, narrowed_val_4);
5701 const uint8x8_t narrowed_first_half = vqmovn_u16(output_first_half);
5702 const uint8x8_t narrowed_second_half = vqmovn_u16(output_second_half);
5703 const uint8x16_t narrowed_result =
5704 vcombine_u8(narrowed_first_half, narrowed_second_half);
5705 vst1q_u8(output_data + i, narrowed_result);
5706 }
5707
5708#endif
5709 for (; i < size; ++i) {
5710 const int32_t input = input_data[i] - input_zeropoint;
5711 const int32_t output =
5712 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(input, effective_scale_multiplier,
5713 effective_scale_shift) +
5714 output_zeropoint;
5715 const int32_t clamped_output =
5716 std::max(std::min(output, kMaxOutput), kMinOutput);
5717 output_data[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(clamped_output);
5718 }
5719}
5720
5721template <>
5722inline void Requantize<uint8_t, int8_t>(const uint8_t* input_data, int32_t size,
5723 int32_t effective_scale_multiplier,
5724 int32_t effective_scale_shift,
5725 int32_t input_zeropoint,
5726 int32_t output_zeropoint,
5727 int8_t* output_data) {
5728 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Requantize/Uint8ToInt8");
5729
5730 static constexpr int32_t kMinOutput = std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min();
5731 static constexpr int32_t kMaxOutput = std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max();
5732
5733 int i = 0;
5734#ifdef USE_NEON
5735 // Constants.
5736 const int32x4_t input_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(-input_zeropoint);
5737 const int32x4_t output_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(output_zeropoint);
5738 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(kMinOutput);
5739 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(kMaxOutput);
5740
5741 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
5742 const uint8x16_t input_vec = vld1q_u8(input_data + i);
5743 const uint16x8_t first_half = vmovl_u8(vget_low_u8(input_vec));
5744 const uint16x8_t second_half = vmovl_u8(vget_high_u8(input_vec));
5745 int32x4x4_t input;
5746 input.val[0] = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_low_u16(first_half)));
5747 input.val[1] = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_high_u16(first_half)));
5748 input.val[2] = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_low_u16(second_half)));
5749 input.val[3] = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_high_u16(second_half)));
5750 input.val[0] = vaddq_s32(input.val[0], input_zero_point_dup);
5751 input.val[1] = vaddq_s32(input.val[1], input_zero_point_dup);
5752 input.val[2] = vaddq_s32(input.val[2], input_zero_point_dup);
5753 input.val[3] = vaddq_s32(input.val[3], input_zero_point_dup);
5754
5755 int32x4x4_t result = MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier4Rows(
5756 input, effective_scale_multiplier, effective_scale_shift);
5757
5758 result.val[0] = vaddq_s32(result.val[0], output_zero_point_dup);
5759 result.val[1] = vaddq_s32(result.val[1], output_zero_point_dup);
5760 result.val[2] = vaddq_s32(result.val[2], output_zero_point_dup);
5761 result.val[3] = vaddq_s32(result.val[3], output_zero_point_dup);
5762 result.val[0] =
5763 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[0], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5764 result.val[1] =
5765 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[1], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5766 result.val[2] =
5767 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[2], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5768 result.val[3] =
5769 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[3], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5770
5771 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_1 = vqmovn_s32(result.val[0]);
5772 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_2 = vqmovn_s32(result.val[1]);
5773 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_3 = vqmovn_s32(result.val[2]);
5774 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_4 = vqmovn_s32(result.val[3]);
5775 const int16x8_t output_first_half =
5776 vcombine_s16(narrowed_val_1, narrowed_val_2);
5777 const int16x8_t output_second_half =
5778 vcombine_s16(narrowed_val_3, narrowed_val_4);
5779 const int8x8_t narrowed_first_half = vqmovn_s16(output_first_half);
5780 const int8x8_t narrowed_second_half = vqmovn_s16(output_second_half);
5781 const int8x16_t narrowed_result =
5782 vcombine_s8(narrowed_first_half, narrowed_second_half);
5783 vst1q_s8(output_data + i, narrowed_result);
5784 }
5785
5786#endif
5787 for (; i < size; ++i) {
5788 const int32_t input = input_data[i] - input_zeropoint;
5789 const int32_t output =
5790 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(input, effective_scale_multiplier,
5791 effective_scale_shift) +
5792 output_zeropoint;
5793 const int32_t clamped_output =
5794 std::max(std::min(output, kMaxOutput), kMinOutput);
5795 output_data[i] = static_cast<int8_t>(clamped_output);
5796 }
5797}

5799template <>
5800inline void Requantize<int8_t, int8_t>(const int8_t* input_data, int32_t size,
5801 int32_t effective_scale_multiplier,
5802 int32_t effective_scale_shift,
5803 int32_t input_zeropoint,
5804 int32_t output_zeropoint,
5805 int8_t* output_data) {
5806 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Requantize/Int8ToInt8");
5807
5808 static constexpr int32_t kMinOutput = std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min();
5809 static constexpr int32_t kMaxOutput = std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max();
5810
5811 int i = 0;
5812#ifdef USE_NEON
5813 // Constants.
5814 const int32x4_t input_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(-input_zeropoint);
5815 const int32x4_t output_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(output_zeropoint);
5816 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(kMinOutput);
5817 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(kMaxOutput);
5818
5819 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
5820 const int8x16_t input_vec = vld1q_s8(input_data + i);
5821 const int16x8_t first_half = vmovl_s8(vget_low_s8(input_vec));
5822 const int16x8_t second_half = vmovl_s8(vget_high_s8(input_vec));

5824 input.val[0] = vmovl_s16(vget_low_s16(first_half));
5825 input.val[1] = vmovl_s16(vget_high_s16(first_half));
5826 input.val[2] = vmovl_s16(vget_low_s16(second_half));
5827 input.val[3] = vmovl_s16(vget_high_s16(second_half));
5828

5831 input.val[2] = vaddq_s32(input.val[2], input_zero_point_dup);
5832 input.val[3] = vaddq_s32(input.val[3], input_zero_point_dup);
5833
5834 int32x4x4_t result = MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier4Rows(
5835 input, effective_scale_multiplier, effective_scale_shift);
5836
5837 result.val[0] = vaddq_s32(result.val[0], output_zero_point_dup);
5838 result.val[1] = vaddq_s32(result.val[1], output_zero_point_dup);
5839 result.val[2] = vaddq_s32(result.val[2], output_zero_point_dup);
5840 result.val[3] = vaddq_s32(result.val[3], output_zero_point_dup);
5841 result.val[0] =
5842 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[0], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5843 result.val[1] =
5844 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[1], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5845 result.val[2] =
5846 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[2], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5847 result.val[3] =
5848 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[3], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5849
5850 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_1 = vqmovn_s32(result.val[0]);
5851 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_2 = vqmovn_s32(result.val[1]);
5852 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_3 = vqmovn_s32(result.val[2]);
5853 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_4 = vqmovn_s32(result.val[3]);
5854 const int16x8_t output_first_half =
5855 vcombine_s16(narrowed_val_1, narrowed_val_2);
5856 const int16x8_t output_second_half =
5857 vcombine_s16(narrowed_val_3, narrowed_val_4);
5858 const int8x8_t narrowed_first_half = vqmovn_s16(output_first_half);
5859 const int8x8_t narrowed_second_half = vqmovn_s16(output_second_half);
5860 const int8x16_t narrowed_result =
5861 vcombine_s8(narrowed_first_half, narrowed_second_half);
5862 vst1q_s8(output_data + i, narrowed_result);
5863 }
5864
5865#endif
5866 for (; i < size; ++i) {
5867 const int32_t input = input_data[i] - input_zeropoint;
5868 const int32_t output =
5869 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(input, effective_scale_multiplier,
5870 effective_scale_shift) +
5871 output_zeropoint;
5872 const int32_t clamped_output =
5873 std::max(std::min(output, kMaxOutput), kMinOutput);
5874 output_data[i] = static_cast<int8_t>(clamped_output);
5875 }
5876}
5877
5878template <>
5879inline void Requantize<uint8_t, uint8_t>(
5880 const uint8_t* input_data, int32_t size, int32_t effective_scale_multiplier,
5881 int32_t effective_scale_shift, int32_t input_zeropoint,
5882 int32_t output_zeropoint, uint8_t* output_data) {
5883 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Requantize/Uint8ToUint8");
5884
5885 static constexpr int32_t kMinOutput = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min();
5886 static constexpr int32_t kMaxOutput = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
5887
5888 int i = 0;
5889#ifdef USE_NEON
5890 // Constants.
5891 const int32x4_t input_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(-input_zeropoint);
5892 const int32x4_t output_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(output_zeropoint);
5893 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(kMinOutput);
5894 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(kMaxOutput);
5895
5896 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
5897 const uint8x16_t input_vec = vld1q_u8(input_data + i);
5898 const uint16x8_t first_half = vmovl_u8(vget_low_u8(input_vec));
5899 const uint16x8_t second_half = vmovl_u8(vget_high_u8(input_vec));
5900 int32x4x4_t input;
5901 input.val[0] = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_low_u16(first_half)));
5902 input.val[1] = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_high_u16(first_half)));
5903 input.val[2] = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_low_u16(second_half)));
5904 input.val[3] = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vmovl_u16(vget_high_u16(second_half)));
5905 input.val[0] = vaddq_s32(input.val[0], input_zero_point_dup);
5906 input.val[1] = vaddq_s32(input.val[1], input_zero_point_dup);
5907 input.val[2] = vaddq_s32(input.val[2], input_zero_point_dup);
5908 input.val[3] = vaddq_s32(input.val[3], input_zero_point_dup);
5909
5910 int32x4x4_t result = MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier4Rows(
5911 input, effective_scale_multiplier, effective_scale_shift);
5912
5913 result.val[0] = vaddq_s32(result.val[0], output_zero_point_dup);
5914 result.val[1] = vaddq_s32(result.val[1], output_zero_point_dup);
5915 result.val[2] = vaddq_s32(result.val[2], output_zero_point_dup);
5916 result.val[3] = vaddq_s32(result.val[3], output_zero_point_dup);
5917 result.val[0] =
5918 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[0], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5919 result.val[1] =
5920 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[1], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5921 result.val[2] =
5922 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[2], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5923 result.val[3] =
5924 vmaxq_s32(vminq_s32(result.val[3], max_val_dup), min_val_dup);
5925
5926 const uint32x4_t result_val_1_unsigned =
5927 vreinterpretq_u32_s32(result.val[0]);
5928 const uint32x4_t result_val_2_unsigned =
5929 vreinterpretq_u32_s32(result.val[1]);
5930 const uint32x4_t result_val_3_unsigned =
5931 vreinterpretq_u32_s32(result.val[2]);
5932 const uint32x4_t result_val_4_unsigned =
5933 vreinterpretq_u32_s32(result.val[3]);
5934
5935 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_1 = vqmovn_u32(result_val_1_unsigned);
5936 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_2 = vqmovn_u32(result_val_2_unsigned);
5937 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_3 = vqmovn_u32(result_val_3_unsigned);
5938 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_4 = vqmovn_u32(result_val_4_unsigned);
5939 const uint16x8_t output_first_half =
5940 vcombine_u16(narrowed_val_1, narrowed_val_2);
5941 const uint16x8_t output_second_half =
5942 vcombine_u16(narrowed_val_3, narrowed_val_4);
5943 const uint8x8_t narrowed_first_half = vqmovn_u16(output_first_half);
5944 const uint8x8_t narrowed_second_half = vqmovn_u16(output_second_half);
5945 const uint8x16_t narrowed_result =
5946 vcombine_u8(narrowed_first_half, narrowed_second_half);
5947 vst1q_u8(output_data + i, narrowed_result);
5948 }
5949
5950#endif
5951 for (; i < size; ++i) {
5952 const int32_t input = input_data[i] - input_zeropoint;
5953 const int32_t output =
5954 MultiplyByQuantizedMultiplier(input, effective_scale_multiplier,
5955 effective_scale_shift) +
5956 output_zeropoint;
5957 const int32_t clamped_output =
5958 std::max(std::min(output, kMaxOutput), kMinOutput);
5959 output_data[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(clamped_output);
5960 }
5961}
5962
5963inline void HardSwish(const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const float* input_data,
5964 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data) {
5965 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("HardSwish/Float");
5966 auto size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
5967 int i = 0;
5968#ifdef USE_NEON
5969 const float32x4_t zero = vdupq_n_f32(0.0f);
5970 const float32x4_t three = vdupq_n_f32(3.0f);
5971 const float32x4_t six = vdupq_n_f32(6.0f);
5972 const float32x4_t one_sixth = vdupq_n_f32(1.0f / 6.0f);
5973
5974 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
5975 // 4x partially unrolled version of the loop below. Refer to its comments.
5976 const float32x4_t in_0 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 0);
5977 const float32x4_t in_1 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 4);
5978 const float32x4_t in_2 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 8);
5979 const float32x4_t in_3 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 12);
5980 const float32x4_t in_scaled_0 = vmulq_f32(in_0, one_sixth);
5981 const float32x4_t in_scaled_1 = vmulq_f32(in_1, one_sixth);
5982 const float32x4_t in_scaled_2 = vmulq_f32(in_2, one_sixth);
5983 const float32x4_t in_scaled_3 = vmulq_f32(in_3, one_sixth);
5984 const float32x4_t in_reluish_0 =
5985 vminq_f32(six, vmaxq_f32(zero, vaddq_f32(in_0, three)));
5986 const float32x4_t in_reluish_1 =
5987 vminq_f32(six, vmaxq_f32(zero, vaddq_f32(in_1, three)));
5988 const float32x4_t in_reluish_2 =
5989 vminq_f32(six, vmaxq_f32(zero, vaddq_f32(in_2, three)));
5990 const float32x4_t in_reluish_3 =
5991 vminq_f32(six, vmaxq_f32(zero, vaddq_f32(in_3, three)));
5992 const float32x4_t product_0 = vmulq_f32(in_scaled_0, in_reluish_0);
5993 const float32x4_t product_1 = vmulq_f32(in_scaled_1, in_reluish_1);
5994 const float32x4_t product_2 = vmulq_f32(in_scaled_2, in_reluish_2);
5995 const float32x4_t product_3 = vmulq_f32(in_scaled_3, in_reluish_3);
5996 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 0, product_0);
5997 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 4, product_1);
5998 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 8, product_2);
5999 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 12, product_3);
6000 }
6001 for (; i <= size - 4; i += 4) {
6002 // The expression to be computed is:
6003 // out = one_sixth * in * min(six, max(zero, (in + three)))
6004 // We structure the AST to have two roughly balanced, independent branches:
6005 // - Multiplication: in_scaled = one_sixth * in.
6006 // - Addition and clamping: in_reluish = min(six, max(zero, (in + three))).
6007 // Then the remaining multiplication at the root of the tree.
6008 const float32x4_t in = vld1q_f32(input_data + i);
6009 const float32x4_t in_scaled = vmulq_f32(in, one_sixth);
6010 const float32x4_t in_reluish =
6011 vminq_f32(six, vmaxq_f32(zero, vaddq_f32(in, three)));
6012 const float32x4_t product = vmulq_f32(in_scaled, in_reluish);
6013 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, product);
6014 }
6015#endif
6016 for (; i < size; i++) {
6017 const float in = input_data[i];
6018 output_data[i] =
6019 in * std::min(6.0f, std::max(0.0f, in + 3.0f)) * (1.0f / 6.0f);
6020 }
6021}
6022
6023#ifdef USE_NEON
6024inline void SaturateAndStore(int16x8_t src, std::uint8_t* dst) {
6025 // Narrow values down to 8 bit unsigned, saturating.
6026 uint8x8_t res8 = vqmovun_s16(src);
6027 // Store results to destination.
6028 vst1_u8(dst, res8);
6029}
6030
6031inline void SaturateAndStore(int16x8_t src, std::int8_t* dst) {
6032 // Narrow values down to 8 bit unsigned, saturating.
6033 int8x8_t res8 = vqmovn_s16(src);
6034 // Store results to destination.
6035 vst1_s8(dst, res8);
6036}
6037#endif
6038
6039template <typename T>
6040inline void HardSwish(const HardSwishParams& params,
6041 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
6042 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
6043 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("HardSwish/Quantized");
6044
6045 const int flat_size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
6046
6047 int i = 0;
6048 // This code heavily uses NEON saturating left shifts (vqshl*) with shift
6049 // amounts that can be zero, in which case we rely on the correct behavior
6050 // of a left shift by zero returning just its first operand unmodified.
6051 // Unfortunately, the Intel arm_neon_sse.h implementation of vqshl* is
6052 // buggy in the case of zero shift amounts, see b/137199585. That is why
6053 // this NEON code path is restricted to true ARM NEON, excluding
6054 // arm_neon_sse.h. Anyway, the arm_neon_sse.h implementation of saturating
6055 // left shifts is slow scalar code, so there may not be much benefit in
6056 // running that over just plain reference code.
6057 //
6058 // TODO(b/137199585): revisit when this is fixed.
6059#ifdef __ARM_NEON
6060 const int16x8_t positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_minus_one =
6061 vdupq_n_s16(std::max(0, params.reluish_multiplier_exponent - 1));
6062 const int16x8_t positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_last_bit =
6063 vdupq_n_s16(params.reluish_multiplier_exponent > 0 ? 1 : 0);
6064 const int16x8_t negative_reluish_multiplier_exponent =
6065 vdupq_n_s16(std::min(0, params.reluish_multiplier_exponent));
6066 const int16x8_t constant_32767 = vdupq_n_s16(32767);
6067 const int16x8_t output_multiplier_exponent =
6068 vdupq_n_s16(params.output_multiplier_exponent);
6069 const int16x8_t output_zero_point = vdupq_n_s16(params.output_zero_point);
6070 // 4x unrolled version of the below NEON loop. Read that first.
6071 for (; i <= flat_size - 32; i += 32) {
6072 using cpu_backend_gemm::detail::Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint;
6073 const int16x8x2_t input_value_0_1 =
6074 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + i, params.input_zero_point);
6075 const int16x8x2_t input_value_2_3 = Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(
6076 input_data + i + 16, params.input_zero_point);
6077 const int16x8_t input_value_on_hires_input_scale_0 =
6078 vshlq_n_s16(input_value_0_1.val[0], 7);
6079 const int16x8_t input_value_on_hires_input_scale_1 =
6080 vshlq_n_s16(input_value_0_1.val[1], 7);
6081 const int16x8_t input_value_on_hires_input_scale_2 =
6082 vshlq_n_s16(input_value_2_3.val[0], 7);
6083 const int16x8_t input_value_on_hires_input_scale_3 =
6084 vshlq_n_s16(input_value_2_3.val[1], 7);
6085 const int16x8_t input_value_on_preshift_output_scale_0 =
6086 vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_value_on_hires_input_scale_0,
6087 params.output_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6088 const int16x8_t input_value_on_preshift_output_scale_1 =
6089 vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_value_on_hires_input_scale_1,
6090 params.output_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6091 const int16x8_t input_value_on_preshift_output_scale_2 =
6092 vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_value_on_hires_input_scale_2,
6093 params.output_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6094 const int16x8_t input_value_on_preshift_output_scale_3 =
6095 vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_value_on_hires_input_scale_3,
6096 params.output_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6097 int16x8_t reluish_value_0 = input_value_on_hires_input_scale_0;
6098 int16x8_t reluish_value_1 = input_value_on_hires_input_scale_1;
6099 int16x8_t reluish_value_2 = input_value_on_hires_input_scale_2;
6100 int16x8_t reluish_value_3 = input_value_on_hires_input_scale_3;
6101 reluish_value_0 = vqshlq_s16(
6102 reluish_value_0, positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_minus_one);
6103 reluish_value_1 = vqshlq_s16(
6104 reluish_value_1, positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_minus_one);
6105 reluish_value_2 = vqshlq_s16(
6106 reluish_value_2, positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_minus_one);
6107 reluish_value_3 = vqshlq_s16(
6108 reluish_value_3, positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_minus_one);
6109 reluish_value_0 = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(
6110 reluish_value_0, params.reluish_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6111 reluish_value_1 = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(
6112 reluish_value_1, params.reluish_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6113 reluish_value_2 = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(
6114 reluish_value_2, params.reluish_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6115 reluish_value_3 = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(
6116 reluish_value_3, params.reluish_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6117 reluish_value_0 = vqshlq_s16(reluish_value_0,
6118 positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_last_bit);
6119 reluish_value_1 = vqshlq_s16(reluish_value_1,
6120 positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_last_bit);
6121 reluish_value_2 = vqshlq_s16(reluish_value_2,
6122 positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_last_bit);
6123 reluish_value_3 = vqshlq_s16(reluish_value_3,
6124 positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_last_bit);
6125 reluish_value_0 =
6126 vrshlq_s16(reluish_value_0, negative_reluish_multiplier_exponent);
6127 reluish_value_1 =
6128 vrshlq_s16(reluish_value_1, negative_reluish_multiplier_exponent);
6129 reluish_value_2 =
6130 vrshlq_s16(reluish_value_2, negative_reluish_multiplier_exponent);
6131 reluish_value_3 =
6132 vrshlq_s16(reluish_value_3, negative_reluish_multiplier_exponent);
6133 reluish_value_0 = vrhaddq_s16(reluish_value_0, constant_32767);
6134 reluish_value_1 = vrhaddq_s16(reluish_value_1, constant_32767);
6135 reluish_value_2 = vrhaddq_s16(reluish_value_2, constant_32767);
6136 reluish_value_3 = vrhaddq_s16(reluish_value_3, constant_32767);
6137 const int16x8_t preshift_output_value_0 =
6138 vqdmulhq_s16(reluish_value_0, input_value_on_preshift_output_scale_0);
6139 const int16x8_t preshift_output_value_1 =
6140 vqdmulhq_s16(reluish_value_1, input_value_on_preshift_output_scale_1);
6141 const int16x8_t preshift_output_value_2 =
6142 vqdmulhq_s16(reluish_value_2, input_value_on_preshift_output_scale_2);
6143 const int16x8_t preshift_output_value_3 =
6144 vqdmulhq_s16(reluish_value_3, input_value_on_preshift_output_scale_3);
6145 int16x8_t output_value_0 =
6146 vrshlq_s16(preshift_output_value_0, output_multiplier_exponent);
6147 int16x8_t output_value_1 =
6148 vrshlq_s16(preshift_output_value_1, output_multiplier_exponent);
6149 int16x8_t output_value_2 =
6150 vrshlq_s16(preshift_output_value_2, output_multiplier_exponent);
6151 int16x8_t output_value_3 =
6152 vrshlq_s16(preshift_output_value_3, output_multiplier_exponent);
6153 output_value_0 = vaddq_s16(output_value_0, output_zero_point);
6154 output_value_1 = vaddq_s16(output_value_1, output_zero_point);
6155 output_value_2 = vaddq_s16(output_value_2, output_zero_point);
6156 output_value_3 = vaddq_s16(output_value_3, output_zero_point);
6157 SaturateAndStore(output_value_0, output_data + i);
6158 SaturateAndStore(output_value_1, output_data + i + 8);
6159 SaturateAndStore(output_value_2, output_data + i + 16);
6160 SaturateAndStore(output_value_3, output_data + i + 24);
6161 }
6162 // NEON version of reference_ops::HardSwish. Read that first.
6163 for (; i <= flat_size - 8; i += 8) {
6164 using cpu_backend_gemm::detail::Load8AndSubtractZeroPoint;
6165 const int16x8_t input_value =
6166 Load8AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + i, params.input_zero_point);
6167 const int16x8_t input_value_on_hires_input_scale =
6168 vshlq_n_s16(input_value, 7);
6169 const int16x8_t input_value_on_preshift_output_scale =
6170 vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_value_on_hires_input_scale,
6171 params.output_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6172 int16x8_t reluish_value = input_value_on_hires_input_scale;
6173 reluish_value = vqshlq_s16(reluish_value,
6174 positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_minus_one);
6175 reluish_value = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(reluish_value,
6176 params.reluish_multiplier_fixedpoint_int16);
6177 reluish_value = vqshlq_s16(reluish_value,
6178 positive_reluish_multiplier_exponent_last_bit);
6179 reluish_value =
6180 vrshlq_s16(reluish_value, negative_reluish_multiplier_exponent);
6181 reluish_value = vrhaddq_s16(reluish_value, constant_32767);
6182 const int16x8_t preshift_output_value =
6183 vqdmulhq_s16(reluish_value, input_value_on_preshift_output_scale);
6184 int16x8_t output_value =
6185 vrshlq_s16(preshift_output_value, output_multiplier_exponent);
6186 output_value = vaddq_s16(output_value, output_zero_point);
6187 SaturateAndStore(output_value, output_data + i);
6188 }
6189#endif
6190 // TODO(b/137208495): revisit when unit tests cover reference code.
6191 // Fall back to reference_ops::HardSwish. In general we have preferred
6192 // to duplicate such scalar code rather than call reference code to handle
6193 // leftovers, thinking that code duplication was not a big concern.
6194 // However, most of our unit tests happen to test only optimized code,
6195 // and the quantized HardSwish implementation is nontrivial enough that
6196 // I really want test coverage for the reference code.
6197 if (i < flat_size) {
6198 const RuntimeShape leftover_shape{flat_size - i};
6199 reference_ops::HardSwish(params, leftover_shape, input_data + i,
6200 leftover_shape, output_data + i);
6201 }
6202}
6203
6204template <typename T>
6205inline void IntegerExponentPow(const ArithmeticParams& params,
6206 const RuntimeShape& unextended_base_shape,
6207 const T* base_data, const int exponent,
6208 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape,
6209 T* output_data) {
6210 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(exponent, 1);
6211 if (exponent == 1) {
6212 // copy data over.
6213 std::memcpy(output_data, base_data,
6214 unextended_base_shape.FlatSize() * sizeof(T));
6215 } else {
6216 IntegerExponentPow(params, unextended_base_shape, base_data, exponent / 2,
6217 unextended_output_shape, output_data);
6218 Mul(params, unextended_base_shape, output_data, unextended_base_shape,
6219 output_data, unextended_output_shape, output_data);
6220 if (exponent % 2 == 1) {
6221 Mul(params, unextended_base_shape, base_data, unextended_base_shape,
6222 output_data, unextended_output_shape, output_data);
6223 }
6224 }
6225}
6226
6227template <typename T>
6228inline void BroadcastPow4D(const RuntimeShape& unextended_input1_shape,
6229 const T* input1_data,
6230 const RuntimeShape& unextended_input2_shape,
6231 const T* input2_data,
6232 const RuntimeShape& unextended_output_shape,
6233 T* output_data) {
6234 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("PowBroadcast");
6235
6236 if (unextended_input2_shape.FlatSize() == 1) {
6237 static const float epsilon = 1e-5;
6238 const T exponent = input2_data[0];
6239 const int int_exponent = static_cast<int>(std::round(exponent));
6240 if ((std::abs(input2_data[0] - int_exponent) < epsilon) &&
6241 (int_exponent >= 1)) {
6242 ArithmeticParams params;
6243 if (std::is_same<T, float>::value) {
6244 params.float_activation_max = std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
6245 params.float_activation_min = std::numeric_limits<float>::lowest();
6246 } else if (std::is_same<T, int>::value) {
6247 params.quantized_activation_max = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
6248 params.quantized_activation_min = std::numeric_limits<int>::lowest();
6249 }
6250 IntegerExponentPow(params, unextended_input1_shape, input1_data,
6251 int_exponent, unextended_output_shape, output_data);
6252 return;
6253 }
6254 }
6255 reference_ops::BroadcastPow4DSlow(unextended_input1_shape, input1_data,
6256 unextended_input2_shape, input2_data,
6257 unextended_output_shape, output_data);
6258}
6259
6260#ifdef USE_NEON
6261
6262inline void ScaleWithNewZeroPoint(const int32x4_t input,
6263 const float32x4_t scale_dup,
6264 const float32x4_t zero_times_scale_dup,
6265 float32x4_t* output) {
6266#ifdef __ARM_FEATURE_FMA
6267 *output = vfmaq_f32(zero_times_scale_dup, vcvtq_f32_s32(input), scale_dup);
6268#else
6269 *output = vaddq_f32(vmulq_f32(vcvtq_f32_s32(input), scale_dup),
6270 zero_times_scale_dup);
6271#endif
6272}
6273
6274#endif // USE_NEON
6275
6276inline void Dequantize(const tflite::DequantizationParams& op_params,
6277 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
6278 const uint8_t* input_data,
6279 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, float* output_data) {
6280 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Dequantize/Uint8");
6281 const int32 zero_point = op_params.zero_point;
6282 const double scale = op_params.scale;
6283 const int flat_size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
6284
6285 int i = 0;
6286#ifdef USE_NEON
6287 const float32x4_t scale_dup = vdupq_n_f32(static_cast<float>(scale));
6288 const float32x4_t zero_times_scale_dup =
6289 vdupq_n_f32(static_cast<float>(-zero_point * scale));
6290 for (; i <= flat_size - 8; i += 8) {
6291 const uint8x8_t input_u8 = vld1_u8(input_data + i);
6292 const uint16x8_t input_u16 = vmovl_u8(input_u8);
6293 const int16x8_t input_s16 = vreinterpretq_s16_u16(input_u16);
6294 const int16x4_t input_s16_low = vget_low_s16(input_s16);
6295 const int16x4_t input_s16_high = vget_high_s16(input_s16);
6296 const int32x4_t val_low = vmovl_s16(input_s16_low);
6297 const int32x4_t val_high = vmovl_s16(input_s16_high);
6298
6299 float32x4_t result_low, result_high;
6300 ScaleWithNewZeroPoint(val_low, scale_dup, zero_times_scale_dup,
6301 &result_low);
6302 ScaleWithNewZeroPoint(val_high, scale_dup, zero_times_scale_dup,
6303 &result_high);
6304
6305 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, result_low);
6306 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 4, result_high);
6307 }
6308#endif // NEON
6309 for (; i < flat_size; ++i) {
6310 const int32 val = input_data[i];
6311 const float result = static_cast<float>(scale * (val - zero_point));
6312 output_data[i] = result;
6313 }
6314}

6398template <typename T>
