6400 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
6401 const float* input_data,
6402 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
6403 reference_ops::AffineQuantize(op_params, input_shape, input_data,
6404 output_shape, output_data);
6405}
6406
6407template <>
6408inline void AffineQuantize(const tflite::QuantizationParams& op_params,
6409 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
6410 const float* input_data,
6411 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
6412 int8_t* output_data) {
6413 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Quantize/Int8");
6414 const int32 zero_point = op_params.zero_point;
6415 const double scale = static_cast<double>(op_params.scale);
6416 const int flat_size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
6417 static constexpr int32 min_val = std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min();
6418 static constexpr int32 max_val = std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max();
6419
6420 int i = 0;
6421#ifdef USE_NEON
6422 const float32x4_t reverse_scale_dup = vdupq_n_f32(1.0f / scale);
6423 const int32x4_t zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(zero_point);
6424 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(min_val);
6425 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(max_val);
6426
6427 for (; i <= flat_size - 8; i += 8) {
6428 const float* src_data_ptr = input_data + i;
6429 float32x4_t input_val_0 = vld1q_f32(src_data_ptr);
6430 float32x4_t input_val_1 = vld1q_f32(src_data_ptr + 4);
6431
6432 input_val_0 = vmulq_f32(input_val_0, reverse_scale_dup);
6433 input_val_1 = vmulq_f32(input_val_1, reverse_scale_dup);
6434
6435 int32x4_t casted_val_0 = RoundToNearest(input_val_0);
6436 int32x4_t casted_val_1 = RoundToNearest(input_val_1);
6437
6438 casted_val_0 = vaddq_s32(casted_val_0, zero_point_dup);
6439 casted_val_1 = vaddq_s32(casted_val_1, zero_point_dup);
6440
6441 // Clamp the values to fit the target type's range.
6442 casted_val_0 = vmaxq_s32(casted_val_0, min_val_dup);
6443 casted_val_1 = vmaxq_s32(casted_val_1, min_val_dup);
6444 casted_val_0 = vminq_s32(casted_val_0, max_val_dup);
6445 casted_val_1 = vminq_s32(casted_val_1, max_val_dup);
6446
6447 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_0 = vmovn_s32(casted_val_0);
6448 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_1 = vmovn_s32(casted_val_1);
6449 const int16x8_t combined_val = vcombine_s16(narrowed_val_0, narrowed_val_1);
6450 const int8x8_t combined_val_narrowed = vmovn_s16(combined_val);
6451 vst1_s8(output_data + i, combined_val_narrowed);
6452 }
6453#endif // NEON
6454
6455 for (; i < flat_size; ++i) {
6456 const float val = input_data[i];
6457 const int32 unclamped =
6458 static_cast<int32>(TfLiteRound(val / scale)) + zero_point;
6459 const int32 clamped = std::min(std::max(unclamped, min_val), max_val);
6460 output_data[i] = clamped;
6461 }
6462}
6463
6464template <>
6465inline void AffineQuantize(const tflite::QuantizationParams& op_params,
6466 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
6467 const float* input_data,
6468 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
6469 uint8_t* output_data) {
6470 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Quantize/Uint8");
6471 const int32 zero_point = op_params.zero_point;
6472 const double scale = static_cast<double>(op_params.scale);
6473 const int flat_size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
6474 static constexpr int32 min_val = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min();
6475 static constexpr int32 max_val = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
6476
6477 int i = 0;
6478#ifdef USE_NEON
6479 const float32x4_t reverse_scale_dup = vdupq_n_f32(1.0f / scale);
6480 const int32x4_t zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(zero_point);
6481 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(min_val);
6482 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(max_val);
6483
6484 for (; i <= flat_size - 8; i += 8) {
6485 const float* src_data_ptr = input_data + i;
6486 float32x4_t input_val_0 = vld1q_f32(src_data_ptr);
6487 float32x4_t input_val_1 = vld1q_f32(src_data_ptr + 4);
6488
6489 input_val_0 = vmulq_f32(input_val_0, reverse_scale_dup);
6490 input_val_1 = vmulq_f32(input_val_1, reverse_scale_dup);
6491
6492 int32x4_t casted_val_0 = RoundToNearest(input_val_0);
6493 int32x4_t casted_val_1 = RoundToNearest(input_val_1);
6494
6495 casted_val_0 = vaddq_s32(casted_val_0, zero_point_dup);
6496 casted_val_1 = vaddq_s32(casted_val_1, zero_point_dup);
6497
6498 // Clamp the values to fit the target type's range.
6499 casted_val_0 = vmaxq_s32(casted_val_0, min_val_dup);
6500 casted_val_1 = vmaxq_s32(casted_val_1, min_val_dup);
6501 casted_val_0 = vminq_s32(casted_val_0, max_val_dup);
6502 casted_val_1 = vminq_s32(casted_val_1, max_val_dup);
6503
6504 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_0 = vqmovun_s32(casted_val_0);
6505 const uint16x4_t narrowed_val_1 = vqmovun_s32(casted_val_1);
6506 const uint16x8_t combined_val =
6507 vcombine_u16(narrowed_val_0, narrowed_val_1);
6508 const uint8x8_t combined_val_narrowed = vmovn_u16(combined_val);
6509 vst1_u8(output_data + i, combined_val_narrowed);
6510 }
6511#endif // NEON
6512
6513 for (; i < flat_size; ++i) {
6514 const float val = input_data[i];
6515 const int32 unclamped =
6516 static_cast<int32>(TfLiteRound(val / scale)) + zero_point;
6517 const int32 clamped = std::min(std::max(unclamped, min_val), max_val);
6518 output_data[i] = clamped;
6519 }
6520}
6521
6522template <>
6523inline void AffineQuantize(const tflite::QuantizationParams& op_params,
6524 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
6525 const float* input_data,
6526 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
6527 int16_t* output_data) {
6528 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Quantize/Int16");
6529 const int32 zero_point = op_params.zero_point;
6530 const double scale = static_cast<double>(op_params.scale);
6531 const int flat_size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
6532 static constexpr int32 min_val = std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min();
6533 static constexpr int32 max_val = std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max();
6534
6535 int i = 0;
6536#ifdef USE_NEON
6537 const float32x4_t reverse_scale_dup = vdupq_n_f32(1.0f / scale);
6538 const int32x4_t zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s32(zero_point);
6539 const int32x4_t min_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(min_val);
6540 const int32x4_t max_val_dup = vdupq_n_s32(max_val);
6541
6542 for (; i <= flat_size - 8; i += 8) {
6543 const float* src_data_ptr = input_data + i;
6544 float32x4_t input_val_0 = vld1q_f32(src_data_ptr);
6545 float32x4_t input_val_1 = vld1q_f32(src_data_ptr + 4);
6546
6547 input_val_0 = vmulq_f32(input_val_0, reverse_scale_dup);
6548 input_val_1 = vmulq_f32(input_val_1, reverse_scale_dup);
6549
6550 int32x4_t casted_val_0 = RoundToNearest(input_val_0);
6551 int32x4_t casted_val_1 = RoundToNearest(input_val_1);
6552
6553 casted_val_0 = vaddq_s32(casted_val_0, zero_point_dup);
6554 casted_val_1 = vaddq_s32(casted_val_1, zero_point_dup);
6555
6556 // Clamp the values to fit the target type's range.
6557 casted_val_0 = vmaxq_s32(casted_val_0, min_val_dup);
6558 casted_val_1 = vmaxq_s32(casted_val_1, min_val_dup);
6559 casted_val_0 = vminq_s32(casted_val_0, max_val_dup);
6560 casted_val_1 = vminq_s32(casted_val_1, max_val_dup);
6561
6562 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_0 = vmovn_s32(casted_val_0);
6563 const int16x4_t narrowed_val_1 = vmovn_s32(casted_val_1);
6564 vst1_s16(output_data + i, narrowed_val_0);
6565 vst1_s16(output_data + i + 4, narrowed_val_1);
6566 }
6567#endif // NEON
6568
6569 for (; i < flat_size; ++i) {
6570 const float val = input_data[i];
6571 const int32 unclamped =
6572 static_cast<int32>(TfLiteRound(val / scale)) + zero_point;
6573 const int32 clamped = std::min(std::max(unclamped, min_val), max_val);
6574 output_data[i] = clamped;
6575 }
6576}
6577
6578// TODO(b/139252020): Replace GEMMLOWP_NEON with USE_NEON when the bug is fixed.
6579// The converted versions of gemmlowp::tanh and gemmlowp::logistic, done by
6580// arm_sse_2_neon.h, produce incorrect results with int16x8_t data types.
6581#ifdef GEMMLOWP_NEON
6582
6583inline int16x8x4_t SaturatingRounding(
6584 int16x8_t input_val_0, int16x8_t input_val_1, int16x8_t input_val_2,
6585 int16x8_t input_val_3, int input_left_shift, int input_multiplier) {
6586 // This performs what is expressed in the scalar code as
6587 // const int16 input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul(
6588 // static_cast<int16>(input_val_centered * (1 << input_left_shift)),
6589 // static_cast<int16>(input_multiplier));
6590 const int16x8_t left_shift_dup = vdupq_n_s16(input_left_shift);
6591 const int16x8_t input_val_shifted_0 = vshlq_s16(input_val_0, left_shift_dup);
6592 const int16x8_t input_val_shifted_1 = vshlq_s16(input_val_1, left_shift_dup);
6593 const int16x8_t input_val_shifted_2 = vshlq_s16(input_val_2, left_shift_dup);
6594 const int16x8_t input_val_shifted_3 = vshlq_s16(input_val_3, left_shift_dup);
6595 int16x8x4_t result;
6596 result.val[0] = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_val_shifted_0, input_multiplier);
6597 result.val[1] = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_val_shifted_1, input_multiplier);
6598 result.val[2] = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_val_shifted_2, input_multiplier);
6599 result.val[3] = vqrdmulhq_n_s16(input_val_shifted_3, input_multiplier);
6600 return result;
6601}
6602
6603// 4-bit fixed point is enough for tanh since tanh(16) is almost same with one,
6604// considering 7 digits under zero.
6605inline int16x8x4_t FixedPoint4Logistic(int16x8x4_t input_val) {
6606 // Invoke gemmlowp::logistic on FixedPoint wrapping int16x8_t
6607 using FixedPoint4 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 4>;
6608 using FixedPoint0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 0>;
6609 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4_0 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val.val[0]);
6610 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4_1 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val.val[1]);
6611 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4_2 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val.val[2]);
6612 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4_3 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val.val[3]);
6613
6614 // TODO(b/134622898) Implement a low accuracy version of logistic. In this
6615 // method, gemmlowp::tanh spends about 80% of the execution times. The
6616 // current implementation is rougly 12-bit accurate in the 16-bit fixed
6617 // point case. Until reaching to error bounds, there are rooms for
6618 // improvements.
6619 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0_0 = gemmlowp::logistic(input_val_f4_0);
6620 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0_1 = gemmlowp::logistic(input_val_f4_1);
6621 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0_2 = gemmlowp::logistic(input_val_f4_2);
6622 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0_3 = gemmlowp::logistic(input_val_f4_3);
6623
6624 // Divide by 2^7 as in the scalar code
6625 int16x8x4_t result;
6626 result.val[0] = vrshrq_n_s16(output_val_f0_0.raw(), 7);
6627 result.val[1] = vrshrq_n_s16(output_val_f0_1.raw(), 7);
6628 result.val[2] = vrshrq_n_s16(output_val_f0_2.raw(), 7);
6629 result.val[3] = vrshrq_n_s16(output_val_f0_3.raw(), 7);
6630 return result;
6631}
6632
6633// 4-bit fixed point is enough for tanh since tanh(16) is almost same with one,
6634// considering 11 digits under zero at least.
6635inline int16x8x4_t FixedPoint4Tanh(int16x8x4_t input_val) {
6636 // Invoke gemmlowp::logistic on FixedPoint wrapping int16x8_t
6637 using FixedPoint4 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 4>;
6638 using FixedPoint0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16x8_t, 0>;
6639 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4_0 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val.val[0]);
6640 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4_1 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val.val[1]);
6641 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4_2 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val.val[2]);
6642 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4_3 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val.val[3]);
6643
6644 // TODO(b/134622898) Implement a low accuracy version of logistic. In this
6645 // method, gemmlowp::tanh spends about 80% of the execution times. The
6646 // current implementation is rougly 12-bit accurate in the 16-bit fixed
6647 // point case. Until reaching to error bounds, there are rooms for
6648 // improvements.
6649 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0_0 = gemmlowp::tanh(input_val_f4_0);
6650 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0_1 = gemmlowp::tanh(input_val_f4_1);
6651 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0_2 = gemmlowp::tanh(input_val_f4_2);
6652 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0_3 = gemmlowp::tanh(input_val_f4_3);
6653
6654 // Divide by 2^7 as in the scalar code
6655 int16x8x4_t result;
6656 result.val[0] = vrshrq_n_s16(output_val_f0_0.raw(), 8);
6657 result.val[1] = vrshrq_n_s16(output_val_f0_1.raw(), 8);
6658 result.val[2] = vrshrq_n_s16(output_val_f0_2.raw(), 8);
6659 result.val[3] = vrshrq_n_s16(output_val_f0_3.raw(), 8);
6660 return result;
6661}
6662
6663inline uint8x16x2_t CalculateUnsignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
6664 int16x8x2_t input_val, int16x8_t range_radius_dup,
6665 int16x8_t neg_range_radius_dup) {
6666 const uint16x8_t mask_rightclamp_0 =
6667 vcgtq_s16(input_val.val[0], range_radius_dup);
6668 const uint16x8_t mask_rightclamp_1 =
6669 vcgtq_s16(input_val.val[1], range_radius_dup);
6670
6671 const uint16x8_t mask_leftclamp_0 =
6672 vcgeq_s16(input_val.val[0], neg_range_radius_dup);
6673 const uint16x8_t mask_leftclamp_1 =
6674 vcgeq_s16(input_val.val[1], neg_range_radius_dup);
6675
6676 uint8x16x2_t result;
6677 result.val[0] = vcombine_u8(vshrn_n_u16(mask_leftclamp_0, 8),
6678 vshrn_n_u16(mask_leftclamp_1, 8));
6679 result.val[1] = vcombine_u8(vshrn_n_u16(mask_rightclamp_0, 8),
6680 vshrn_n_u16(mask_rightclamp_1, 8));
6681 return result;
6682}
6683
6684inline uint8x16x2_t CalculateSignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
6685 int16x8x2_t input_val, int16x8_t range_radius_dup,
6686 int16x8_t neg_range_radius_dup) {
6687 const uint16x8_t mask_rightclamp_0 =
6688 vcgtq_s16(input_val.val[0], range_radius_dup);
6689 const uint16x8_t mask_rightclamp_1 =
6690 vcgtq_s16(input_val.val[1], range_radius_dup);
6691
6692 const uint16x8_t mask_leftclamp_0 =
6693 vcltq_s16(input_val.val[0], neg_range_radius_dup);
6694 const uint16x8_t mask_leftclamp_1 =
6695 vcltq_s16(input_val.val[1], neg_range_radius_dup);
6696
6697 uint8x16x2_t result;
6698 result.val[0] = vcombine_u8(vshrn_n_u16(mask_leftclamp_0, 8),
6699 vshrn_n_u16(mask_leftclamp_1, 8));
6700 result.val[1] = vcombine_u8(vshrn_n_u16(mask_rightclamp_0, 8),
6701 vshrn_n_u16(mask_rightclamp_1, 8));
6702 return result;
6703}
6704
6705inline void ClampWithRangeAndStore(uint8_t* output_dst, uint8x16_t input_val,
6706 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp) {
6707 // Store back to memory
6708 vst1q_u8(output_dst, vandq_u8(vorrq_u8(input_val, masks_clamp.val[1]),
6709 masks_clamp.val[0]));
6710}
6711
6712inline void ClampWithRangeAndStore(int8_t* output_dst, int8x16_t input_val,
6713 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp) {
6714 static const int8x16_t max_dup = vdupq_n_s8(127);
6715 static const int8x16_t min_dup = vdupq_n_s8(-128);
6716 // Store back to memory
6717 vst1q_s8(output_dst,
6718 vbslq_s8(masks_clamp.val[1], max_dup,
6719 vbslq_s8(masks_clamp.val[0], min_dup, input_val)));
6720}
6721
6722#endif // GEMMLOWP_NEON
6723
6724inline void Tanh16bitPrecision(const TanhParams& params,
6725 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
6726 const uint8* input_data,
6727 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
6728 uint8* output_data) {
6729 // Note that this is almost the exact same code as in Logistic().
6730 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Tanh/Uint8");
6731 const int32 input_zero_point = params.input_zero_point;
6732 const int32 input_range_radius = params.input_range_radius;
6733 const int16 input_multiplier = static_cast<int16>(params.input_multiplier);
6734 const int16 input_left_shift = static_cast<int16>(params.input_left_shift);
6735 const int size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
6736
6737 int c = 0;
6738 int16_t output_zero_point = 128;
6739
6740// TODO(b/139252020): Replace GEMMLOWP_NEON with USE_NEON when the bug is fixed.
6741// The converted versions of gemmlowp::tanh and gemmlowp::logistic, done by
6742// arm_sse_2_neon.h, produce incorrect results with int16x8_t data types.
6743#ifdef GEMMLOWP_NEON
6744 const int16x8_t range_radius_dup = vdupq_n_s16(input_range_radius);
6745 const int16x8_t neg_range_radius_dup = vdupq_n_s16(-input_range_radius);
6746 const int16x8_t output_zero_point_s16 = vdupq_n_s16(output_zero_point);
6747
6748 // Handle 32 values at a time
6749 for (; c <= size - 32; c += 32) {
6750 // Read input uint8 values, cast to int16 and subtract input_zero_point
6751 using cpu_backend_gemm::detail::Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint;
6752 const int16x8x2_t input_val_centered_0_1 =
6753 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + c, input_zero_point);
6754 const int16x8x2_t input_val_centered_2_3 =
6755 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + c + 16, input_zero_point);
6756
6757 // Prepare the bit masks that we will use at the end to implement the logic
6758 // that was expressed in the scalar code with branching:
6759 // if (input_val_centered < -input_range_radius) {
6760 // output_val = 0;
6761 // } else if (input_val_centered > input_range_radius) {
6762 // output_val = 255;
6763 // } else {
6764 // ...
6765 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp_0_1 = CalculateUnsignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
6766 input_val_centered_0_1, range_radius_dup, neg_range_radius_dup);
6767 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp_2_3 = CalculateUnsignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
6768 input_val_centered_2_3, range_radius_dup, neg_range_radius_dup);
6769
6770 int16x8x4_t input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRounding(
6771 input_val_centered_0_1.val[0], input_val_centered_0_1.val[1],
6772 input_val_centered_2_3.val[0], input_val_centered_2_3.val[1],
6773 input_left_shift, input_multiplier);
6774
6775 int16x8x4_t output_val_s16 = FixedPoint4Tanh(input_val_rescaled);
6776
6777 // Add the output zero point
6778 output_val_s16.val[0] =
6779 vaddq_s16(output_val_s16.val[0], output_zero_point_s16);
6780 output_val_s16.val[1] =
6781 vaddq_s16(output_val_s16.val[1], output_zero_point_s16);
6782 output_val_s16.val[2] =
6783 vaddq_s16(output_val_s16.val[2], output_zero_point_s16);
6784 output_val_s16.val[3] =
6785 vaddq_s16(output_val_s16.val[3], output_zero_point_s16);
6786
6787 // Cast output values to uint8, saturating
6788 uint8x16_t output_val_u8_0_1 = vcombine_u8(
6789 vqmovun_s16(output_val_s16.val[0]), vqmovun_s16(output_val_s16.val[1]));
6790 uint8x16_t output_val_u8_2_3 = vcombine_u8(
6791 vqmovun_s16(output_val_s16.val[2]), vqmovun_s16(output_val_s16.val[3]));
6792
6793 ClampWithRangeAndStore(output_data + c, output_val_u8_0_1, masks_clamp_0_1);
6794 ClampWithRangeAndStore(output_data + c + 16, output_val_u8_2_3,
6795 masks_clamp_2_3);
6796 }
6797#endif // GEMMLOWP_NEON
6798 // Leftover loop: handle one value at a time with scalar code.
6799 for (; c < size; ++c) {
6800 const uint8 input_val_u8 = input_data[c];
6801 const int16 input_val_centered =
6802 static_cast<int16>(input_val_u8) - input_zero_point;
6803 uint8 output_val;
6804 if (input_val_centered < -input_range_radius) {
6805 output_val = 0;
6806 } else if (input_val_centered > input_range_radius) {
6807 output_val = 255;
6808 } else {
6809 using gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul;
6810 const int16 input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul(
6811 static_cast<int16>(input_val_centered * (1 << input_left_shift)),
6812 static_cast<int16>(input_multiplier));
6813 using FixedPoint4 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16, 4>;
6814 using FixedPoint0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16, 0>;
6815 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val_rescaled);
6816 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0 = gemmlowp::tanh(input_val_f4);
6817 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
6818 int16 output_val_s16 = RoundingDivideByPOT(output_val_f0.raw(), 8);
6819 output_val_s16 += output_zero_point;
6820 if (output_val_s16 == 256) {
6821 output_val_s16 = 255;
6822 }
6823 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(output_val_s16, 0);
6824 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(output_val_s16, 255);
6825 output_val = static_cast<uint8>(output_val_s16);
6826 }
6827 output_data[c] = output_val;
6828 }
6829}
6830
6831inline void Tanh16bitPrecision(const TanhParams& params,
6832 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
6833 const int8* input_data,
6834 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
6835 int8* output_data) {
6836 // Note that this is almost the exact same code as in Logistic().
6837 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Tanh/Int8");
6838 const int32 input_zero_point = params.input_zero_point;
6839 const int32 input_range_radius = params.input_range_radius;
6840 const int16 input_multiplier = static_cast<int16>(params.input_multiplier);
6841 const int16 input_left_shift = static_cast<int16>(params.input_left_shift);
6842 const int size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
6843
6844 int c = 0;
6845// TODO(b/139252020): Replace GEMMLOWP_NEON with USE_NEON when the bug is fixed.
6846// The converted versions of gemmlowp::tanh and gemmlowp::logistic, done by
6847// arm_sse_2_neon.h, produce incorrect results with int16x8_t data types.
6848#ifdef GEMMLOWP_NEON
6849 const int16x8_t range_radius_dup = vdupq_n_s16(input_range_radius);
6850 const int16x8_t neg_range_radius_dup = vdupq_n_s16(-input_range_radius);
6851
6852 // Handle 32 values at a time
6853 for (; c <= size - 32; c += 32) {
6854 // Read input int8 values, cast to int16 and subtract input_zero_point
6855 using cpu_backend_gemm::detail::Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint;
6856 const int16x8x2_t input_val_centered_0_1 =
6857 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + c, input_zero_point);
6858 const int16x8x2_t input_val_centered_2_3 =
6859 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + c + 16, input_zero_point);
6860
6861 // Prepare the bit masks that we will use at the end to implement the logic
6862 // that was expressed in the scalar code with branching:
6863 // if (input_val_centered < -input_range_radius) {
6864 // output_val = -128;
6865 // } else if (input_val_centered > input_range_radius) {
6866 // output_val = 127;
6867 // } else {
6868 // ...
6869 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp_0_1 = CalculateSignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
6870 input_val_centered_0_1, range_radius_dup, neg_range_radius_dup);
6871 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp_2_3 = CalculateSignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
6872 input_val_centered_2_3, range_radius_dup, neg_range_radius_dup);
6873
6874 int16x8x4_t input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRounding(
6875 input_val_centered_0_1.val[0], input_val_centered_0_1.val[1],
6876 input_val_centered_2_3.val[0], input_val_centered_2_3.val[1],
6877 input_left_shift, input_multiplier);
6878
6879 int16x8x4_t output_val_s16 = FixedPoint4Tanh(input_val_rescaled);
6880
6881 // Cast output values to uint8, saturating
6882 int8x16_t output_val_s8_0_1 = vcombine_s8(
6883 vqmovn_s16(output_val_s16.val[0]), vqmovn_s16(output_val_s16.val[1]));
6884 int8x16_t output_val_s8_2_3 = vcombine_s8(
6885 vqmovn_s16(output_val_s16.val[2]), vqmovn_s16(output_val_s16.val[3]));
6886
6887 ClampWithRangeAndStore(output_data + c, output_val_s8_0_1, masks_clamp_0_1);
6888 ClampWithRangeAndStore(output_data + c + 16, output_val_s8_2_3,
6889 masks_clamp_2_3);
6890 }
6891#endif // GEMMLOWP_NEON
6892 // Leftover loop: handle one value at a time with scalar code.
6893 for (; c < size; ++c) {
6894 const int8 input_val_s8 = input_data[c];
6895 const int16 input_val_centered =
6896 static_cast<int16>(input_val_s8) - input_zero_point;
6897 int8 output_val;
6898 if (input_val_centered <= -input_range_radius) {
6899 output_val = -128;
6900 } else if (input_val_centered >= input_range_radius) {
6901 output_val = 127;
6902 } else {
6903 using gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul;
6904 const int16 input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul(
6905 static_cast<int16>(input_val_centered * (1 << input_left_shift)),
6906 static_cast<int16>(input_multiplier));
6907 using FixedPoint4 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16, 4>;
6908 using FixedPoint0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16, 0>;
6909 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val_rescaled);
6910 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0 = gemmlowp::tanh(input_val_f4);
6911 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
6912 int16 output_val_s16 = RoundingDivideByPOT(output_val_f0.raw(), 8);
6913 if (output_val_s16 == 128) {
6914 output_val_s16 = 127;
6915 }
6916 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(output_val_s16, -128);
6917 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(output_val_s16, 127);
6918 output_val = static_cast<int8>(output_val_s16);
6919 }
6920 output_data[c] = output_val;
6921 }
6922}
6923
6924inline void Logistic16bitPrecision(const LogisticParams& params,
6925 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
6926 const uint8* input_data,
6927 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
6928 uint8* output_data) {
6929 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Logistic/Uint8");
6930 const int32 input_zero_point = params.input_zero_point;
6931 const int32 input_range_radius = params.input_range_radius;
6932 const int32 input_multiplier = params.input_multiplier;
6933 const int16 input_left_shift = static_cast<int16>(params.input_left_shift);
6934 const int size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
6935
6936 int c = 0;
6937// TODO(b/139252020): Replace GEMMLOWP_NEON with USE_NEON when the bug is fixed.
6938// The converted versions of gemmlowp::tanh and gemmlowp::logistic, done by
6939// arm_sse_2_neon.h, produce incorrect results with int16x8_t data types.
6940#ifdef GEMMLOWP_NEON
6941 const int16x8_t range_radius_dup = vdupq_n_s16(input_range_radius);
6942 const int16x8_t neg_range_radius_dup = vdupq_n_s16(-input_range_radius);
6943
6944 // Handle 32 values at a time
6945 for (; c <= size - 32; c += 32) {
6946 // Read input uint8 values, cast to int16 and subtract input_zero_point
6947 using cpu_backend_gemm::detail::Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint;
6948 const int16x8x2_t input_val_centered_0_1 =
6949 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + c, input_zero_point);
6950 const int16x8x2_t input_val_centered_2_3 =
6951 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + c + 16, input_zero_point);
6952
6953 // Prepare the bit masks that we will use at the end to implement the logic
6954 // that was expressed in the scalar code with branching:
6955 // if (input_val_centered < -input_range_radius) {
6956 // output_val = 0;
6957 // } else if (input_val_centered > input_range_radius) {
6958 // output_val = 255;
6959 // } else {
6960 // ...
6961 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp_0_1 = CalculateUnsignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
6962 input_val_centered_0_1, range_radius_dup, neg_range_radius_dup);
6963 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp_2_3 = CalculateUnsignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
6964 input_val_centered_2_3, range_radius_dup, neg_range_radius_dup);
6965
6966 int16x8x4_t input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRounding(
6967 input_val_centered_0_1.val[0], input_val_centered_0_1.val[1],
6968 input_val_centered_2_3.val[0], input_val_centered_2_3.val[1],
6969 input_left_shift, input_multiplier);
6970
6971 int16x8x4_t output_val_s16 = FixedPoint4Logistic(input_val_rescaled);
6972
6973 // Cast output values to uint8, saturating
6974 uint8x16_t output_val_u8_0_1 = vcombine_u8(
6975 vqmovun_s16(output_val_s16.val[0]), vqmovun_s16(output_val_s16.val[1]));
6976 uint8x16_t output_val_u8_2_3 = vcombine_u8(
6977 vqmovun_s16(output_val_s16.val[2]), vqmovun_s16(output_val_s16.val[3]));
6978
6979 ClampWithRangeAndStore(output_data + c, output_val_u8_0_1, masks_clamp_0_1);
6980 ClampWithRangeAndStore(output_data + c + 16, output_val_u8_2_3,
6981 masks_clamp_2_3);
6982 }
6983#endif // GEMMLOWP_NEON
6984 // Leftover loop: handle one value at a time with scalar code.
6985 for (; c < size; ++c) {
6986 const uint8 input_val_u8 = input_data[c];
6987 const int16 input_val_centered =
6988 static_cast<int16>(input_val_u8) - input_zero_point;
6989 uint8 output_val;
6990 if (input_val_centered < -input_range_radius) {
6991 output_val = 0;
6992 } else if (input_val_centered > input_range_radius) {
6993 output_val = 255;
6994 } else {
6995 using gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul;
6996 const int16 input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul(
6997 static_cast<int16>(input_val_centered * (1 << input_left_shift)),
6998 static_cast<int16>(input_multiplier));
6999 using FixedPoint4 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16, 4>;
7000 using FixedPoint0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16, 0>;
7001 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val_rescaled);
7002 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0 = gemmlowp::logistic(input_val_f4);
7003 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
7004 int16 output_val_s16 = RoundingDivideByPOT(output_val_f0.raw(), 7);
7005 if (output_val_s16 == 256) {
7006 output_val_s16 = 255;
7007 }
7008 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(output_val_s16, 0);
7009 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(output_val_s16, 255);
7010 output_val = static_cast<uint8>(output_val_s16);
7011 }
7012 output_data[c] = output_val;
7013 }
7014}
7015
7016inline void Logistic16bitPrecision(const LogisticParams& params,
7017 const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
7018 const int8* input_data,
7019 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
7020 int8* output_data) {
7021 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Logistic/Int8");
7022 const int32 input_zero_point = params.input_zero_point;
7023 const int32 input_range_radius = params.input_range_radius;
7024 const int32 input_multiplier = params.input_multiplier;
7025 const int16 input_left_shift = static_cast<int16>(params.input_left_shift);
7026 const int size = MatchingFlatSize(input_shape, output_shape);
7027
7028 int c = 0;
7029 const int16 output_zero_point = 128;
7030// TODO(b/139252020): Replace GEMMLOWP_NEON with USE_NEON when the bug is fixed.
7031// The converted versions of gemmlowp::tanh and gemmlowp::logistic, done by
7032// arm_sse_2_neon.h, produce incorrect results with int16x8_t data types.
7033#ifdef GEMMLOWP_NEON
7034 const int16x8_t range_radius_dup = vdupq_n_s16(input_range_radius);
7035 const int16x8_t neg_range_radius_dup = vdupq_n_s16(-input_range_radius);
7036 const int16x8_t output_zero_point_dup = vdupq_n_s16(output_zero_point);
7037
7038 // Handle 32 values at a time
7039 for (; c <= size - 32; c += 32) {
7040 // Read input int8 values, cast to int16 and subtract input_zero_point
7041 using cpu_backend_gemm::detail::Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint;
7042 const int16x8x2_t input_val_centered_0_1 =
7043 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + c, input_zero_point);
7044 const int16x8x2_t input_val_centered_2_3 =
7045 Load16AndSubtractZeroPoint(input_data + c + 16, input_zero_point);
7046
7047 // Prepare the bit masks that we will use at the end to implement the logic
7048 // that was expressed in the scalar code with branching:
7049 // if (input_val_centered < -input_range_radius) {
7050 // output_val = -128;
7051 // } else if (input_val_centered > input_range_radius) {
7052 // output_val = 127;
7053 // } else {
7054 // ...
7055 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp_0_1 = CalculateSignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
7056 input_val_centered_0_1, range_radius_dup, neg_range_radius_dup);
7057 uint8x16x2_t masks_clamp_2_3 = CalculateSignedClampingWithRangeBitMasks(
7058 input_val_centered_2_3, range_radius_dup, neg_range_radius_dup);
7059
7060 int16x8x4_t input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRounding(
7061 input_val_centered_0_1.val[0], input_val_centered_0_1.val[1],
7062 input_val_centered_2_3.val[0], input_val_centered_2_3.val[1],
7063 input_left_shift, input_multiplier);
7064
7065 int16x8x4_t output_val_s16 = FixedPoint4Logistic(input_val_rescaled);
7066
7067 // Substract output zero point.
7068 output_val_s16.val[0] =
7069 vsubq_s16(output_val_s16.val[0], output_zero_point_dup);
7070 output_val_s16.val[1] =
7071 vsubq_s16(output_val_s16.val[1], output_zero_point_dup);
7072 output_val_s16.val[2] =
7073 vsubq_s16(output_val_s16.val[2], output_zero_point_dup);
7074 output_val_s16.val[3] =
7075 vsubq_s16(output_val_s16.val[3], output_zero_point_dup);
7076
7077 // Cast output values to int8, saturating
7078 int8x16_t output_val_s8_0_1 = vcombine_s8(
7079 vqmovn_s16(output_val_s16.val[0]), vqmovn_s16(output_val_s16.val[1]));
7080 int8x16_t output_val_s8_2_3 = vcombine_s8(
7081 vqmovn_s16(output_val_s16.val[2]), vqmovn_s16(output_val_s16.val[3]));
7082
7083 ClampWithRangeAndStore(output_data + c, output_val_s8_0_1, masks_clamp_0_1);
7084 ClampWithRangeAndStore(output_data + c + 16, output_val_s8_2_3,
7085 masks_clamp_2_3);
7086 }
7087#endif // GEMMLOWP_NEON
7088 // Leftover loop: handle one value at a time with scalar code.
7089 for (; c < size; ++c) {
7090 const int8 input_val_s8 = input_data[c];
7091 const int16 input_val_centered =
7092 static_cast<int16>(input_val_s8) - input_zero_point;
7093 int8 output_val;
7094 if (input_val_centered < -input_range_radius) {
7095 output_val = -128;
7096 } else if (input_val_centered > input_range_radius) {
7097 output_val = 127;
7098 } else {
7099 using gemmlowp::SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul;
7100 const int16 input_val_rescaled = SaturatingRoundingDoublingHighMul(
7101 static_cast<int16>(input_val_centered * (1 << input_left_shift)),
7102 static_cast<int16>(input_multiplier));
7103 using FixedPoint4 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16, 4>;
7104 using FixedPoint0 = gemmlowp::FixedPoint<int16, 0>;
7105 const FixedPoint4 input_val_f4 = FixedPoint4::FromRaw(input_val_rescaled);
7106 const FixedPoint0 output_val_f0 = gemmlowp::logistic(input_val_f4);
7107 using gemmlowp::RoundingDivideByPOT;
7108 int16 output_val_s16 = RoundingDivideByPOT(output_val_f0.raw(), 7);
7109 output_val_s16 -= output_zero_point;
7110 if (output_val_s16 == 128) {
7111 output_val_s16 = 127;
7112 }
7113 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(output_val_s16, -128);
7114 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(output_val_s16, 127);
7115 output_val = static_cast<int8>(output_val_s16);
7116 }
7117 output_data[c] = output_val;
7118 }
7119}
7120
7121// Transpose2D only deals with typical 2D matrix transpose ops.
7122// Perform transpose by transposing 4x4 blocks of the input, proceeding from
7123// left to right (down the rows) of the input, and then from top to bottom.
7124template <typename T>
7125inline void Transpose2D(const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
7126 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
7127 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 2);
7128 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 2);
7129
7130 const int d0 = input_shape.DimsData()[0];
7131 const int d1 = input_shape.DimsData()[1];
7132 const int kLines = 4;
7133 const int kSkipSize = (kLines - 1) * d1;
7134
7135 const T* input = input_data;
7136
7137 int i = 0;
7138 for (; i <= d0 - kLines; i += kLines) {
7139 T* output = output_data + i;
7140
7141 const T* input_ptr = input;
7142 optimized_ops_preload_l1_keep(input_ptr);
7143 input_ptr += d1;
7144 optimized_ops_preload_l1_keep(input_ptr);
7145 input_ptr += d1;
7146 optimized_ops_preload_l1_keep(input_ptr);
7147 input_ptr += d1;
7148 optimized_ops_preload_l1_keep(input_ptr);
7149
7150 int j = 0;
7151 for (; j <= d1 - kLines; j += kLines) {
7152 input_ptr = input;
7153 const T a00 = input_ptr[0];
7154 const T a01 = input_ptr[1];
7155 const T a02 = input_ptr[2];
7156 const T a03 = input_ptr[3];
7157 input_ptr += d1;
7158 const T a10 = input_ptr[0];
7159 const T a11 = input_ptr[1];
7160 const T a12 = input_ptr[2];
7161 const T a13 = input_ptr[3];
7162 input_ptr += d1;
7163 const T a20 = input_ptr[0];
7164 const T a21 = input_ptr[1];
7165 const T a22 = input_ptr[2];
7166 const T a23 = input_ptr[3];
7167 input_ptr += d1;
7168 const T a30 = input_ptr[0];
7169 const T a31 = input_ptr[1];
7170 const T a32 = input_ptr[2];
7171 const T a33 = input_ptr[3];
7172
7173 output[0] = a00;
7174 output[1] = a10;
7175 output[2] = a20;
7176 output[3] = a30;
7177 output += d0;
7178
7179 output[0] = a01;
7180 output[1] = a11;
7181 output[2] = a21;
7182 output[3] = a31;
7183 output += d0;
7184
7185 output[0] = a02;
7186 output[1] = a12;
7187 output[2] = a22;
7188 output[3] = a32;
7189 output += d0;
7190
7191 output[0] = a03;
7192 output[1] = a13;
7193 output[2] = a23;
7194 output[3] = a33;
7195 output += d0;
7196
7197 input += kLines;
7198 }
7199 if (j == d1) {
7200 input += kSkipSize;
7201 } else {
7202 for (int p = 0; p < kLines; ++p) {
7203 for (int q = 0; q < d1 - j; ++q) {
7204 *(output + q * d0 + p) = *(input + p * d1 + q);
7205 }
7206 }
7207 input += (d1 - j) + kSkipSize;
7208 }
7209 }
7210 for (; i < d0; ++i) {
7211 T* output = output_data + i;
7212 for (int j = 0; j < d1; ++j) {
7213 *output = *input;
7214 output += d0;
7215 ++input;
7216 }
7217 }
7218}
7219
7220template <>
7221inline void Transpose2D(const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
7222 const int32_t* input_data,
7223 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
7224 int32_t* output_data) {
7225 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 2);
7226 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 2);
7227
7228 const int d0 = input_shape.DimsData()[0];
7229 const int d1 = input_shape.DimsData()[1];
7230#ifdef USE_NEON
7231 const int kLines = 4;
7232 const int kSkipSize = (kLines - 1) * d1;
7233#endif
7234
7235 const int32_t* input = input_data;
7236
7237 int i = 0;
7238#ifdef USE_NEON
7239 for (; i <= d0 - kLines; i += kLines) {
7240 int32_t* output = output_data + i;
7241
7242 const int32_t* input_ptr = input;
7243 optimized_ops_preload_l1_keep(input_ptr);
7244 input_ptr += d1;
7245 optimized_ops_preload_l1_keep(input_ptr);
7246 input_ptr += d1;
7247 optimized_ops_preload_l1_keep(input_ptr);
7248 input_ptr += d1;
7249 optimized_ops_preload_l1_keep(input_ptr);
7250
7251 int j = 0;
7252 for (; j <= d1 - kLines; j += kLines) {
7253 input_ptr = input;
7254 int32x4_t a0 = vld1q_s32(input);
7255 input_ptr += d1;
7256 int32x4_t a1 = vld1q_s32(input_ptr);
7257 input_ptr += d1;
7258 int32x4_t a2 = vld1q_s32(input_ptr);
7259 input_ptr += d1;
7260 int32x4_t a3 = vld1q_s32(input_ptr);
7261
7262 int32x4x2_t tmp1 = vuzpq_s32(a0, a2);
7263 int32x4x2_t tmp2 = vuzpq_s32(a1, a3);
7264 int32x4x2_t tmp3 = vtrnq_s32(tmp1.val[0], tmp2.val[0]);
7265 int32x4x2_t tmp4 = vtrnq_s32(tmp1.val[1], tmp2.val[1]);
7266
7267 vst1q_s32(output, tmp3.val[0]);
7268 output += d0;
7269 vst1q_s32(output, tmp4.val[0]);
7270 output += d0;
7271 vst1q_s32(output, tmp3.val[1]);
7272 output += d0;
7273 vst1q_s32(output, tmp4.val[1]);
7274 output += d0;
7275 input += kLines;
7276 }
7277 if (j == d1) {
7278 input += kSkipSize;
7279 } else {
7280 for (int p = 0; p < kLines; ++p) {
7281 for (int q = 0; q < d1 - j; ++q) {
7282 *(output + q * d0 + p) = *(input + p * d1 + q);
7283 }
7284 }
7285 input += (d1 - j) + kSkipSize;
7286 }
7287 }
7288#endif
7289 for (; i < d0; ++i) {
7290 int32_t* output = output_data + i;
7291 for (int j = 0; j < d1; ++j) {
7292 *output = *input;
7293 output += d0;
7294 ++input;
7295 }
7296 }
7297}
7298
7299// TODO(b/173718660): see if we can reduce the number
7300// of lines of code in branching without affecting latency.
7301template <typename T>
7302inline void Transpose3D(const TransposeParams& params,
7303 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
7304 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
7305 int s1, s2, s3;
7306 s1 = input_shape.Dims(0);
7307 s2 = input_shape.Dims(1);
7308 s3 = input_shape.Dims(2);
7309
7310 int p1, p2, p3;
7311 if (params.perm[0] == 2) {
7312 p1 = 1;
7313 } else if (params.perm[1] == 2) {
7314 p2 = 1;
7315 } else {
7316 p3 = 1;
7317 }
7318
7319 if (params.perm[0] == 1) {
7320 p1 = s3;
7321 } else if (params.perm[1] == 1) {
7322 p2 = s3;
7323 } else {
7324 p3 = s3;
7325 }
7326
7327 if (params.perm[0] == 0) {
7328 p1 = s2 * s3;
7329 } else if (params.perm[1] == 0) {
7330 p2 = s2 * s3;
7331 } else {
7332 p3 = s2 * s3;
7333 }
7334
7335 int o_s[3];
7336 o_s[0] = input_shape.Dims(params.perm[0]);
7337 o_s[1] = input_shape.Dims(params.perm[1]);
7338 o_s[2] = input_shape.Dims(params.perm[2]);
7339
7340 for (int i1 = 0; i1 < o_s[0]; ++i1) {
7341 for (int i2 = 0; i2 < o_s[1]; ++i2) {
7342 for (int i3 = 0; i3 < o_s[2]; ++i3) {
7343 const int i = i1 * p1 + i2 * p2 + i3 * p3;
7344 const int o = i1 * o_s[1] * o_s[2] + i2 * o_s[2] + i3;
7345 output_data[o] = input_data[i];
7346 }
7347 }
7348 }
7349}
7350
7351template <typename T, int N>
7352void TransposeImpl(const TransposeParams& params,
7353 const RuntimeShape& input_shape, const T* input_data,
7354 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T* output_data) {
7355 const int dims_cnt = input_shape.DimensionsCount();
7356
7357 int dim0, dim1;
7358 if (transpose_utils::IsTranspose2DApplicable(params, input_shape, &dim0,
7359 &dim1)) {
7360 Transpose2D(RuntimeShape({dim0, dim1}), input_data,
7361 RuntimeShape({dim1, dim0}), output_data);
7362 return;
7363 }
7364
7365 // TODO(b/141217325): notably Eigen is better suited for
7366 // larger inputs whereas Transpose3D is generally
7367 // better for smaller ones.
7368 //
7369 // E.g. on Nexus 5, Eigen is better for size 96^3 and up
7370 // and Transpose3D is better for 72^3 and down.
7371 //
7372 // 96^3 is not mobile-friendly for certain usecases
7373 // (e.g. model used in beam search for seq2seq) but is in others.
7374 // Consider tradeoffs.
7375 if (dims_cnt == 3) {
7376 Transpose3D(params, input_shape, input_data, output_shape, output_data);
7377 return;
7378 }
7379
7380 // Reroute to the reference version if an optimized method for the given data
7381 // is not available.
7382 reference_ops::Transpose<T, N>(params, input_shape, input_data, output_shape,
7383 output_data);
7384}
7385
7386template <typename T, int N = 5>
7387void Transpose(const TransposeParams& unshrinked_params,
7388 const RuntimeShape& unshrinked_input_shape, const T* input_data,
7389 const RuntimeShape& unshrinked_output_shape, T* output_data) {
7390 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Transpose");
7391
7392 const int output_size = unshrinked_output_shape.DimensionsCount();
7393 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(unshrinked_input_shape.DimensionsCount(), N);
7394 TFLITE_DCHECK_LE(output_size, N);
7395 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_size, unshrinked_params.perm_count);
7396
7397 RuntimeShape shrinked_input_shape = RuntimeShape(unshrinked_input_shape);
7398 RuntimeShape shrinked_output_shape = RuntimeShape(unshrinked_output_shape);
7399 TransposeParams shrinked_params = unshrinked_params;
7400
7401 // Reduce any dimensions that have one size. Lower transpose op usually
7402 // performs better since memory access patterns will be improved.
7403 transpose_utils::RemoveOneSizeDimensions(
7404 &shrinked_input_shape, &shrinked_output_shape, &shrinked_params);
7405
7406 // Handle identity cases.
7407 // TODO(b/140779653): Add an optimization pass in the conversion process to
7408 // remove transpose op nodes where they do nothing like the below one.
7409 bool identical = true;
7410 for (int i = 0; i < shrinked_params.perm_count; ++i) {
7411 if (shrinked_params.perm[i] != i) {
7412 identical = false;
7413 break;
7414 }
7415 }
7416 if (identical) {
7417 memcpy(output_data, input_data,
7418 unshrinked_input_shape.FlatSize() * sizeof(T));
7419 return;
7420 }
7421
7422 // Reduce dimensions by flattening.
7423 if (shrinked_params.perm[0] == 0 && output_size >= 3) {
7424 RuntimeShape non_flatten_input_shape;
7425 RuntimeShape non_flatten_output_shape;
7426 TransposeParams non_flatten_params;
7427 const int total_size = shrinked_input_shape.FlatSize();
7428 const int non_flatten_size = transpose_utils::Flatten(
7429 shrinked_input_shape, shrinked_output_shape, shrinked_params,
7430 &non_flatten_input_shape, &non_flatten_output_shape,
7431 &non_flatten_params);
7432 TFLITE_DCHECK_NE(non_flatten_params.perm[0], 0);
7433
7434 for (int i = 0; i < total_size; i += non_flatten_size) {
7435 TransposeImpl<T, N>(non_flatten_params, non_flatten_input_shape,
7436 input_data + i, non_flatten_output_shape,
7437 output_data + i);
7438 }
7439 return;
7440 }
7441
7442 // Call non-flattened case.
7443 TransposeImpl<T, N>(shrinked_params, shrinked_input_shape, input_data,
7444 shrinked_output_shape, output_data);
7445}
7446
7447// Assume input1 & input2 have the same scale & zero point.
7448inline void MaximumElementwise(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
7449 const int8* input1_data, const int8* input2_data,
7450 int8* output_data) {
7451 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("MaximumElementwiseInt8/8bit");
7452 int i = 0;
7453#ifdef USE_NEON
7454 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
7455 const int8x16_t input1_val_original = vld1q_s8(input1_data + i);
7456 const int8x16_t input2_val_original = vld1q_s8(input2_data + i);
7457 const int8x16_t max_data =
7458 vmaxq_s8(input1_val_original, input2_val_original);
7459 vst1q_s8(output_data + i, max_data);
7460 }
7461#endif // USE_NEON
7462 for (; i < size; ++i) {
7463 const int8 input1_val = input1_data[i];
7464 const int8 input2_val = input2_data[i];
7465 output_data[i] = std::max(input1_val, input2_val);
7466 }
7467}
7468
7469inline void MaximumScalarBroadcast(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
7470 int8 input1_data, const int8* input2_data,
7471 int8* output_data) {
7472 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("MaximumScalarBroadcastInt8/8bit");
7473 int i = 0;
7474
7475#ifdef USE_NEON
7476 const int8x16_t input1_val_original = vdupq_n_s8(input1_data);
7477 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
7478 const int8x16_t input2_val_original = vld1q_s8(input2_data + i);
7479 const int8x16_t max_data =
7480 vmaxq_s8(input1_val_original, input2_val_original);
7481 vst1q_s8(output_data + i, max_data);
7482 }
7483#endif // USE_NEON
7484 for (; i < size; ++i) {
7485 const int8 input2_val = input2_data[i];
7486 output_data[i] = std::max(input1_data, input2_val);
7487 }
7488}

7490// Assume input1 & input2 have the same scale & zero point.
7491inline void MinimumElementwise(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
7492 const int8* input1_data, const int8* input2_data,
7493 int8* output_data) {
7494 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("MinimumElementwiseInt8/8bit");
7495 int i = 0;
7496#ifdef USE_NEON
7497 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
7498 const int8x16_t input1_val_original = vld1q_s8(input1_data + i);
7499 const int8x16_t input2_val_original = vld1q_s8(input2_data + i);
7500 const int8x16_t min_data =
7501 vminq_s8(input1_val_original, input2_val_original);
7502 vst1q_s8(output_data + i, min_data);
7503 }
7504#endif // USE_NEON
7505 for (; i < size; ++i) {
7506 const int8 input1_val = input1_data[i];
7507 const int8 input2_val = input2_data[i];
7508 output_data[i] = std::min(input1_val, input2_val);
7509 }
7510}

7512inline void MinimumScalarBroadcast(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
7513 int8 input1_data, const int8* input2_data,
7514 int8* output_data) {
7515 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("MinimumScalarBroadcastInt8/8bit");
7516 int i = 0;
7517
7518#ifdef USE_NEON
7519 const int8x16_t input1_val_original = vdupq_n_s8(input1_data);
7520 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
7521 const int8x16_t input2_val_original = vld1q_s8(input2_data + i);
7522 const int8x16_t min_data =
7523 vminq_s8(input1_val_original, input2_val_original);
7524 vst1q_s8(output_data + i, min_data);
7525 }
7526#endif // USE_NEON
7527 for (; i < size; ++i) {
7528 const int8 input2_val = input2_data[i];
7529 output_data[i] = std::min(input1_data, input2_val);
7530 }
7531}

7533template <typename Op>
7534inline void BroadcastMaximumDispatch(const ArithmeticParams& params,
7535 const RuntimeShape& input1_shape,
7536 const int8* input1_data,

7538 const int8* input2_data,
7539 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
7540 int8* output_data, Op op) {
7541 if (params.broadcast_category == BroadcastableOpCategory::kGenericBroadcast) {
7542 return reference_ops::MaximumMinimumBroadcastSlow(
7543 input1_shape, input1_data, input2_shape, input2_data, output_shape,
7544 output_data, op);
7545 }
7546
7547 BinaryBroadcastFiveFold(params, input1_shape, input1_data, input2_shape,
7548 input2_data, output_shape, output_data,
7549 MaximumElementwise, MaximumScalarBroadcast);
7550}

7570
7571template <typename T>
7572void CumsumImpl(const T* input_data, const RuntimeShape& shape, int axis,
7573 bool exclusive, bool reverse, T* output_data) {
7574 Eigen::array<Eigen::DenseIndex, 3> dims = {1, 1, 1};
7575
7576 for (int i = 0; i < axis; ++i) {
7577 dims[0] *= shape.Dims(i);
7578 }
7579 dims[1] = shape.Dims(axis);
7580 for (int i = axis + 1; i < shape.DimensionsCount(); ++i) {
7581 dims[2] *= shape.Dims(i);
7582 }
7583
7584 typedef Eigen::TensorMap<
7585 Eigen::Tensor<const T, 3, Eigen::RowMajor, Eigen::DenseIndex>,
7586 Eigen::Aligned>
7587 ConstTensor;
7588 typedef Eigen::TensorMap<
7589 Eigen::Tensor<T, 3, Eigen::RowMajor, Eigen::DenseIndex>, Eigen::Aligned>
7590 Tensor;
7591 ConstTensor input(input_data, dims);
7592 Tensor output(output_data, dims);
7593
7594 if (reverse) {
7595 Eigen::array<bool, 3> reverse_idx = {false, true, false};
7596 output =
7597 input.reverse(reverse_idx).cumsum(1, exclusive).reverse(reverse_idx);
7598 } else {
7599 output = input.cumsum(1, exclusive);
7600 }
7601}
7602
7603template <typename T>
7604void CumSum(const T* input_data, const RuntimeShape& shape, int axis,
7605 bool exclusive, bool reverse, T* output_data) {
7606 const int dim = shape.DimensionsCount();
7607 TFLITE_DCHECK_GE(dim, 1);
7608 CumsumImpl<T>(input_data, shape, axis, exclusive, reverse, output_data);
7609}
7610
7611inline void PReluScalarBroadcast(int size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
7612 float alpha, const float* input_data,
7613 float* output_data) {
7614 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("PreluScalarBroadcast/float");
7615 int i = 0;
7616
7617#ifdef USE_NEON
7618 const float32x4_t zero_dup = vdupq_n_f32(0.0f);
7619 const float32x4_t alpha_dup = vdupq_n_f32(alpha);
7620 for (; i <= size - 16; i += 16) {
7621 const float32x4_t input1 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i);
7622 const float32x4_t input2 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 4);
7623 const float32x4_t input3 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 8);
7624 const float32x4_t input4 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 12);
7625
7626 const float32x4_t temp1 = vmulq_f32(input1, alpha_dup);
7627 const float32x4_t temp2 = vmulq_f32(input2, alpha_dup);
7628 const float32x4_t temp3 = vmulq_f32(input3, alpha_dup);
7629 const float32x4_t temp4 = vmulq_f32(input4, alpha_dup);
7630
7631 const uint32x4_t mask1 = vcgeq_f32(input1, zero_dup);
7632 const uint32x4_t mask2 = vcgeq_f32(input2, zero_dup);
7633 const uint32x4_t mask3 = vcgeq_f32(input3, zero_dup);
7634 const uint32x4_t mask4 = vcgeq_f32(input4, zero_dup);
7635
7636 const float32x4_t result1 = vbslq_f32(mask1, input1, temp1);
7637 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, result1);
7638 const float32x4_t result2 = vbslq_f32(mask2, input2, temp2);
7639 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 4, result2);
7640 const float32x4_t result3 = vbslq_f32(mask3, input3, temp3);
7641 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 8, result3);
7642 const float32x4_t result4 = vbslq_f32(mask4, input4, temp4);
7643 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 12, result4);
7644 }
7645
7646 for (; i <= size - 4; i += 4) {
7647 const float32x4_t input = vld1q_f32(input_data + i);
7648 const float32x4_t temp = vmulq_f32(input, alpha_dup);
7649 const uint32x4_t mask = vcgeq_f32(input, zero_dup);
7650 const float32x4_t result = vbslq_f32(mask, input, temp);
7651 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, result);
7652 }
7653#endif // USE_NEON
7654 for (; i < size; ++i) {
7655 const float input = input_data[i];
7656 output_data[i] = input >= 0.f ? input : input * alpha;
7657 }
7658}
7659
7660inline void PReluElementWise(int flat_size, const ArithmeticParams& params,
7661 const float* alpha_data, const float* input_data,
7662 float* output_data) {
7663 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("PreluElementWise/float");
7664
7665 int i = 0;
7666#ifdef USE_NEON
7667 const float32x4_t zero_dup = vdupq_n_f32(0.0f);
7668 for (; i <= flat_size - 16; i += 16) {
7669 const float32x4_t input1 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i);
7670 const float32x4_t alpha1 = vld1q_f32(alpha_data + i);
7671 const float32x4_t input2 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 4);
7672 const float32x4_t alpha2 = vld1q_f32(alpha_data + i + 4);
7673 const float32x4_t input3 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 8);
7674 const float32x4_t alpha3 = vld1q_f32(alpha_data + i + 8);
7675 const float32x4_t input4 = vld1q_f32(input_data + i + 12);
7676 const float32x4_t alpha4 = vld1q_f32(alpha_data + i + 12);
7677
7678 const float32x4_t temp1 = vmulq_f32(input1, alpha1);
7679 const float32x4_t temp2 = vmulq_f32(input2, alpha2);
7680 const float32x4_t temp3 = vmulq_f32(input3, alpha3);
7681 const float32x4_t temp4 = vmulq_f32(input4, alpha4);
7682
7683 const uint32x4_t mask1 = vcgeq_f32(input1, zero_dup);
7684 const uint32x4_t mask2 = vcgeq_f32(input2, zero_dup);
7685 const uint32x4_t mask3 = vcgeq_f32(input3, zero_dup);
7686 const uint32x4_t mask4 = vcgeq_f32(input4, zero_dup);
7687
7688 const float32x4_t result1 = vbslq_f32(mask1, input1, temp1);
7689 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, result1);
7690 const float32x4_t result2 = vbslq_f32(mask2, input2, temp2);
7691 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 4, result2);
7692 const float32x4_t result3 = vbslq_f32(mask3, input3, temp3);
7693 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 8, result3);
7694 const float32x4_t result4 = vbslq_f32(mask4, input4, temp4);
7695 vst1q_f32(output_data + i + 12, result4);
7696 }
7697
7698 for (; i <= flat_size - 4; i += 4) {
7699 const float32x4_t input = vld1q_f32(input_data + i);
7700 const float32x4_t alpha = vld1q_f32(alpha_data + i);
7701
7702 const float32x4_t temp = vmulq_f32(input, alpha);
7703 const uint32x4_t mask = vcgeq_f32(input, zero_dup);
7704 const float32x4_t result = vbslq_f32(mask, input, temp);
7705 vst1q_f32(output_data + i, result);
7706 }
7707#endif // USE_NEON
7708 for (; i < flat_size; ++i) {
7709 const float input = input_data[i];
7710 const float alpha = alpha_data[i];
7711 output_data[i] = input >= 0.f ? input : input * alpha;
7712 }
7713}
7714
7715inline void BroadcastPReluDispatch(
7716 const ArithmeticParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
7717 const float* input_data, const RuntimeShape& alpha_shape,
7718 const float* alpha_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
7719 float* output_data, float (*func)(float, float)) {
7720 if (params.broadcast_category == BroadcastableOpCategory::kGenericBroadcast) {
7721 return reference_ops::BroadcastBinaryFunction4DSlow<float, float, float>(
7722 input_shape, input_data, alpha_shape, alpha_data, output_shape,
7723 output_data, func);
7724 }
7725
7726 BinaryBroadcastFiveFold(params, input_shape, input_data, alpha_shape,
7727 alpha_data, output_shape, output_data,
7728 PReluElementWise, PReluScalarBroadcast);
7729}
7730
7731// Returns the index with minimum value within `input_data`.
7732// If there is a tie, returns the smaller index.
7733template <typename T>
7734inline int ArgMinVector(const T* input_data, int size) {
7735 T min_value = input_data[0];
7736 int min_index = 0;
7737 for (int i = 1; i < size; ++i) {
7738 const T curr_value = input_data[i];
7739 if (curr_value < min_value) {
7740 min_value = curr_value;
7741 min_index = i;
7742 }
7743 }
7744 return min_index;
7745}
7746
7747// Returns the index with maximum value within `input_data`.
7748// If there is a tie, returns the smaller index.
7749template <typename T>
7750inline int ArgMaxVector(const T* input_data, int size) {
7751 T max_value = input_data[0];
7752 int max_index = 0;
7753 for (int i = 1; i < size; ++i) {
7754 const T curr_value = input_data[i];
7755 if (curr_value > max_value) {
7756 max_value = curr_value;
7757 max_index = i;
7758 }
7759 }
7760 return max_index;
7761}
7762
7763template <>
7764inline int ArgMinVector(const float* input_data, int size) {
7765 int32_t min_index = 0;
7766 float min_value = input_data[0];
7767 int32_t i = 1;
7768#ifdef USE_NEON
7769 if (size >= 4) {
7770 float32x4_t min_value_f32x4 = vld1q_f32(input_data);
7771 const int32_t index_init[4] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
7772 int32x4_t min_index_s32x4 = vld1q_s32(index_init);
7773 int32x4_t index_s32x4 = min_index_s32x4;
7774 int32x4_t inc = vdupq_n_s32(4);
7775 for (i = 4; i <= size - 4; i += 4) {
7776 // Increase indices by 4.
7777 index_s32x4 = vaddq_s32(index_s32x4, inc);
7778 float32x4_t v = vld1q_f32(&input_data[i]);
7779 uint32x4_t mask = vcltq_f32(v, min_value_f32x4);
7780 min_value_f32x4 = vminq_f32(min_value_f32x4, v);
7781 min_index_s32x4 = vbslq_s32(mask, index_s32x4, min_index_s32x4);
7782 }
7783 // Find min element within float32x4_t.
7784#ifdef __aarch64__
7785 min_value = vminvq_f32(min_value_f32x4);
7786#else
7787 float32x2_t min_value_f32x2 = vpmin_f32(vget_low_f32(min_value_f32x4),
7788 vget_high_f32(min_value_f32x4));
7789 min_value_f32x2 = vpmin_f32(min_value_f32x2, min_value_f32x2);
7790 min_value = vget_lane_f32(min_value_f32x2, 0);
7791#endif // __aarch64__
7792 // Mask indices of non-min values with max int32_t.
7793 float32x4_t fill_min_value_f32x4 = vdupq_n_f32(min_value);
7794 uint32x4_t mask = vceqq_f32(min_value_f32x4, fill_min_value_f32x4);
7795 int32x4_t all_set = vdupq_n_s32(std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
7796 min_index_s32x4 = vbslq_s32(mask, min_index_s32x4, all_set);
7797 // Find min index of min values.
7798#ifdef __aarch64__
7799 min_index = vminvq_s32(min_index_s32x4);
7800#else
7801 int32x2_t min_index_s32x2 = vpmin_s32(vget_low_s32(min_index_s32x4),
7802 vget_high_s32(min_index_s32x4));
7803 min_index_s32x2 = vpmin_s32(min_index_s32x2, min_index_s32x2);
7804 min_index = vget_lane_s32(min_index_s32x2, 0);
7805#endif // __aarch64__
7806 }
7807#endif // USE_NEON
7808 // Leftover loop.
7809 for (; i < size; ++i) {
7810 const float curr_value = input_data[i];
7811 if (curr_value < min_value) {
7812 min_value = curr_value;
7813 min_index = i;
7814 }
7815 }
7816 return min_index;
7817}
7818
7819template <>
7820inline int ArgMaxVector(const float* input_data, int size) {
7821 int32_t max_index = 0;
7822 float max_value = input_data[0];
7823 int32_t i = 1;
7824#ifdef USE_NEON
7825 if (size >= 4) {
7826 float32x4_t max_value_f32x4 = vld1q_f32(input_data);
7827 const int32_t index_init[4] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
7828 int32x4_t max_index_s32x4 = vld1q_s32(index_init);
7829 int32x4_t index_s32x4 = max_index_s32x4;
7830 int32x4_t inc = vdupq_n_s32(4);
7831 for (i = 4; i <= size - 4; i += 4) {
7832 // Increase indices by 4.
7833 index_s32x4 = vaddq_s32(index_s32x4, inc);
7834 float32x4_t v = vld1q_f32(&input_data[i]);
7835 uint32x4_t mask = vcgtq_f32(v, max_value_f32x4);
7836 max_value_f32x4 = vmaxq_f32(max_value_f32x4, v);
7837 max_index_s32x4 = vbslq_s32(mask, index_s32x4, max_index_s32x4);
7838 }
7839 // Find max element within float32x4_t.
7840#ifdef __aarch64__
7841 max_value = vmaxvq_f32(max_value_f32x4);
7842#else
7843 float32x2_t max_value_f32x2 = vpmax_f32(vget_low_f32(max_value_f32x4),
7844 vget_high_f32(max_value_f32x4));
7845 max_value_f32x2 = vpmax_f32(max_value_f32x2, max_value_f32x2);
7846 max_value = vget_lane_f32(max_value_f32x2, 0);
7847#endif // __aarch64__
7848 // Mask indices of non-max values with max int32_t.
7849 float32x4_t fill_max_value_f32x4 = vdupq_n_f32(max_value);
7850 uint32x4_t mask = vceqq_f32(max_value_f32x4, fill_max_value_f32x4);
7851 int32x4_t all_set = vdupq_n_s32(std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
7852 max_index_s32x4 = vbslq_s32(mask, max_index_s32x4, all_set);
7853 // Find min index of max values.
7854#ifdef __aarch64__
7855 max_index = vminvq_s32(max_index_s32x4);
7856#else
7857 int32x2_t max_index_s32x2 = vpmin_s32(vget_low_s32(max_index_s32x4),
7858 vget_high_s32(max_index_s32x4));
7859 max_index_s32x2 = vpmin_s32(max_index_s32x2, max_index_s32x2);
7860 max_index = vget_lane_s32(max_index_s32x2, 0);
7861#endif // __aarch64__
7862 }
7863#endif // USE_NEON
7864 // Leftover loop.
7865 for (; i < size; ++i) {
7866 const float curr_value = input_data[i];
7867 if (curr_value > max_value) {
7868 max_value = curr_value;
7869 max_index = i;
7870 }
7871 }
7872 return max_index;
7873}
7874
7875// Specializes ArgMinMax function with axis=dims-1.
7876// In this case, ArgMinMax reduction is applied on contiguous memory.
7877template <typename T1, typename T2, bool is_arg_max>
7878inline void ArgMinMaxLastAxis(const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
7879 const T1* input_data,
7880 const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
7881 T2* output_data) {
7882 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 2);
7883 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 1);
7884 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.Dims(0), output_shape.Dims(0));
7885
7886 int outer_size = input_shape.Dims(0);
7887 int axis_size = input_shape.Dims(1);
7888 for (int outer = 0; outer < outer_size; ++outer) {
7889 if (is_arg_max) {
7890 output_data[outer] = static_cast<T2>(
7891 ArgMaxVector<T1>(input_data + outer * axis_size, axis_size));
7892 } else {
7893 output_data[outer] = static_cast<T2>(
7894 ArgMinVector<T1>(input_data + outer * axis_size, axis_size));
7895 }
7896 }
7897}
7898
7899template <typename T1, typename T2, typename T3>
7900inline void ArgMinMax(const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const T1* input1_data,
7901 const T3* input2_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
7902 T2* output_data, const bool is_arg_max) {
7903 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("ArgMinMax");
7904
7905 TFLITE_DCHECK_GT(input1_shape.DimensionsCount(), 0);
7906 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input1_shape.DimensionsCount() - 1,
7907 output_shape.DimensionsCount());
7908 int axis = input2_data[0];
7909 if (axis < 0) {
7910 axis += input1_shape.DimensionsCount();
7911 }
7912 const int axis_size = input1_shape.Dims(axis);
7913
7914 int outer_size = 1;
7915 for (int i = 0; i < axis; ++i) {
7916 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input1_shape.Dims(i), output_shape.Dims(i));
7917 outer_size *= input1_shape.Dims(i);
7918 }
7919
7920 int inner_size = 1;
7921 const int dims_count = input1_shape.DimensionsCount();
7922 for (int i = axis + 1; i < dims_count; ++i) {
7923 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input1_shape.Dims(i), output_shape.Dims(i - 1));
7924 inner_size *= input1_shape.Dims(i);
7925 }
7926
7927 // Call specialized function when axis=dims-1. So far, only float32 is
7928 // optimized so reroute to specialized function only when T1 is float32.
7929 if (inner_size == 1 && std::is_same<T1, float>::value) {
7930 if (is_arg_max) {
7931 ArgMinMaxLastAxis<T1, T2, /*is_arg_max=*/true>(
7932 {outer_size, axis_size}, input1_data, {outer_size}, output_data);
7933 } else {
7934 ArgMinMaxLastAxis<T1, T2, /*is_arg_max=*/false>(
7935 {outer_size, axis_size}, input1_data, {outer_size}, output_data);
7936 }
7937 return;
7938 }
7939
7940 reference_ops::ArgMinMax(input1_shape, input1_data, input2_data, output_shape,
7941 output_data, is_arg_max);
7942}
7943
7944template <typename T1, typename T2, typename T3>
7945void ArgMax(const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const T1* input1_data,
7946 const T3* input2_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
7947 T2* output_data) {
7948 ArgMinMax(input1_shape, input1_data, input2_data, output_shape, output_data,
7949 /*is_arg_max=*/true);
7950}
7951
7952// Convenience version that allows, for example, generated-code calls to be
7953// the same as other binary ops.
7954// For backward compatibility, reference_ops has ArgMax function.
7955template <typename T1, typename T2, typename T3>
7956inline void ArgMax(const RuntimeShape& input1_shape, const T1* input1_data,
7957 const RuntimeShape& input2_shape, const T3* input2_data,
7958 const RuntimeShape& output_shape, T2* output_data) {
7959 // Drop shape of second input: not needed.
7960 ArgMax(input1_shape, input1_data, input2_data, output_shape, output_data);
7961}
7962
7963inline void Conv3D(const Conv3DParams& params, const RuntimeShape& input_shape,
7964 const float* input_data, const RuntimeShape& filter_shape,
7965 const float* filter_data, const RuntimeShape& bias_shape,
7966 const float* bias_data, const RuntimeShape& output_shape,
7967 float* output_data, const RuntimeShape& im2col_shape,
7968 float* im2col_data,
7969 const RuntimeShape& transposed_filter_shape,
7970 float* transposed_filter_data,
7971 CpuBackendContext* cpu_backend_context) {
7972 const int stride_depth = params.stride_depth;
7973 const int stride_height = params.stride_height;
7974 const int stride_width = params.stride_width;
7975 const int dilation_depth_factor = params.dilation_depth;
7976 const int dilation_height_factor = params.dilation_height;
7977 const int dilation_width_factor = params.dilation_width;
7978 const float output_activation_min = params.float_activation_min;
7979 const float output_activation_max = params.float_activation_max;
7980 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(input_shape.DimensionsCount(), 5);
7981 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(filter_shape.DimensionsCount(), 5);
7982 TFLITE_DCHECK_EQ(output_shape.DimensionsCount(), 5);
7983
7984 ruy::profiler::ScopeLabel label("Conv3D");
7985
7986 // NB: the float 0.0f value is represented by all zero bytes.
7987 const uint8 float_zero_byte = 0x00;
7988 const float* gemm_input_data = nullptr;
7989 const RuntimeShape* gemm_input_shape = nullptr;
7990 const int filter_width = filter_shape.Dims(2);
7991 const int filter_height = filter_shape.Dims(1);
7992 const int filter_depth = filter_shape.Dims(0);
7993 const bool need_dilated_im2col = dilation_width_factor != 1 ||
7994 dilation_height_factor != 1 ||
7995 dilation_depth_factor != 1;
7996 const bool need_im2col = stride_depth != 1 || stride_height != 1 ||
7997 stride_width != 1 || filter_depth != 1 ||
7998 filter_height != 1 || filter_width != 1;
7999
8000 if (need_dilated_im2col) {
8001 DilatedIm2col3D(params, filter_depth, filter_height, filter_width,
8002 float_zero_byte, input_shape, input_data, im2col_shape,
8003 im2col_data);
8004 gemm_input_data = im2col_data;
8005 gemm_input_shape = &im2col_shape;
8006 } else if (need_im2col) {
8007 TFLITE_DCHECK(im2col_data);
8008 Im2col3D(params, filter_depth, filter_height, filter_width, float_zero_byte,
8009 input_shape, input_data, im2col_shape, im2col_data);
8010 gemm_input_data = im2col_data;
8011 gemm_input_shape = &im2col_shape;
8012 } else {
8013 TFLITE_DCHECK(!im2col_data);
8014 gemm_input_data = input_data;
8015 gemm_input_shape = &input_shape;
8016 }
8017
8018 // Transpose the filter tensor.
8019 TransposeParams transpose_params;
8020 transpose_params.perm_count = 5;
8021 transpose_params.perm[0] = 4;
8022 transpose_params.perm[1] = 0;
8023 transpose_params.perm[2] = 1;
8024 transpose_params.perm[3] = 2;
8025 transpose_params.perm[4] = 3;
8026 Transpose<float, 5>(transpose_params, filter_shape, filter_data,
8027 transposed_filter_shape, transposed_filter_data);
8028
8029 const int gemm_input_dims = gemm_input_shape->DimensionsCount();
8030 int m = FlatSizeSkipDim(*gemm_input_shape, gemm_input_dims - 1);
8031 int n = output_shape.Dims(4);
8032 int k = gemm_input_shape->Dims(gemm_input_dims - 1);
8033
8034 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<float> lhs_params;
8035 lhs_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kRowMajor;
8036 lhs_params.rows = n;
8037 lhs_params.cols = k;
8038 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<float> rhs_params;
8039 rhs_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kColMajor;
8040 rhs_params.rows = k;
8041 rhs_params.cols = m;
8042 cpu_backend_gemm::MatrixParams<float> dst_params;
8043 dst_params.order = cpu_backend_gemm::Order::kColMajor;
8044 dst_params.rows = n;
8045 dst_params.cols = m;
8046 cpu_backend_gemm::GemmParams<float, float> gemm_params;
8047 gemm_params.bias = bias_data;
8048 gemm_params.clamp_min = output_activation_min;
8049 gemm_params.clamp_max = output_activation_max;
8050 cpu_backend_gemm::Gemm(lhs_params, transposed_filter_data, rhs_params,
8051 gemm_input_data, dst_params, output_data, gemm_params,
8052 cpu_backend_context);
8053}
